<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="HEB" stage="Rev" version="C">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 04:06:24Z" when="2009-10-02 04:06:24Z" stage="Draft">Draft into Kupang Malay by Barbara Grimes; team advisors; this book, B. Grimes; Neva Miller SIL commentary is point for initial comparison, if there are questions re: exegesis; other resources: Ex. Summ. GNT; SSA; Tatar BT; Revised July/Aug 04 with June Jacob, Mus Zacharias and Thresia Mauboy; Chuck did readthrough for editorial and mesolectal issues, but not exegetical; UNS checked in Kupang by Mus 10,11,13 Sept 2004 (details below); back translation by Chuck; consultant checked by Marge Crofts, with June as interpreter, Oct. 2004; some minor cleanup by Chuck noted with **; reviewed, terms for Christ and devil checked, notes added, Sept 2005; NT cleanup by Chuck, passing exegetical stuff by Marge Crofts (Bruce, Ellingworth); read thru also by Adriana; more exegetical tightening in 2009 from working with Tetun Belu and Dhao (version S)</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 11:13:16Z" when="2014-02-24 11:13:16Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: October 2004 in Kupang; Consultant: Marge Crofts, approved. Report: Transl Cons ReporKMepis.doc.</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-22 02:06:49Z" when="2015-01-22 02:06:49Z" stage="Rev">Smoothing read through for Kupang mini-Bible with Chuck, Lena, Rina, Oma, at UBB. BackTrans also adjusted a bit.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Ibrani</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Surat kasi orang<bt>Letter to the</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Ibrani<bt>Ibrani people</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">yang baru parcaya sang Yesus Kristus<bt>who have only recently believed in YK</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">deng kasi tenga dong pung nene-moyang pung agama<bt>and left the religion of their forefathers</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;The most widely held view is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">"The most widely held view is that the Epistle is addressed to Jewish Christians to warn them against apostasy to Judaism" New Bible Dict p.459; Miller</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah su kirim Dia pung Ana yang lebe hebat dari Dia pung jubir lama dong<bt>God has sent His Child, is more amazing that His old/former spokespeople (= *prophets)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Dolu-dolu Tuhan Allah pake Dia pung jubir dong, ko omong deng kotong pung nene-moyang orang Ibrani.<bt>Previously/long ago, God used His spokespeople, to speak with/to our-inc Ibrani forefathers/ancestors.</bt><note reference="1:1a" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kata <span class="Italic">Ibrani</span> ni, nama laen kasi bangsa Yahudi. Orang Yahudi yang parcaya sang Yesus Kristus, orang subu bilang, &lt;&lt;orang Kristen Ibrani&gt;&gt;, tagal dong su laen dari dong pung sodara Yahudi yang masi pegang atoran agama Yahudi yang lama.<bt>This word <span class="Italic">Ibrani</span>, is another name for the Yahudi ethnic group. The Yahudi people who believed in YK, people referred to as "Ibrani Kristen people", because they were different from their Yahudi siblings who continued to hold to the old Yahudi religious regulations.</bt></note>Dia pake cara macam-macam ko omong banya kali deng dong.<bt>He used various ways to speak many times with them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV misses it by backgrounding the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">CEV misses it by backgrounding the agency of God</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: At many times and in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: At many times and in many ways in the past, God, who spoke to our ancestors by the prophets,</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:1b" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tuhan Allah kasi tau Dia pung pasán dong, deng pake cara macam-macam. Conto ke: Dia kasi tau sang Abraham pake janji, sang Musa pake atoran agama, sang Daud pake lagu puji, sang Yeremia pake umpama.<bt>God told His messages using various ways. For example: He told to Abraham using promises, to Musa using religious regulations, to Daud using songs of praise, to Yeremia using examples/parables/allegories.</bt></note><v n="2" />Ma sakarang Dia su kirim Dia pung Ana, ko omong langsung deng kotong.<bt>But now He has sent His Child, to speak directly with us-inc. [EXEG: “in these last days” Miller, Ex. Summ.] [NOTE to daughter translations: Don't skew by overemphasize “langsung” as “face-to-face”, since that is both wrong, and not the point. Most recipients of this letter probably never had a direct encounter with the physical Jesus.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) added note on exeg"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) added note on exeg</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dari mula-mula, Tuhan Allah su pili ame Dia pung Ana,<bt>From the (very) beginning, God had chosen this Child of His,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko parenta sama-sama deng Dia.<bt>to rule/govern together with Him. [EXEG: “placed as heir” = rule together TH]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Waktu Dia bekin ame langit deng bumi, deng dia pung isi samua-samua,<bt>When He made/created the heaven/sky and earth, and all its contents,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia pung Ana ni ju ada bekin sama-sama deng Dia.<bt>This Child of His was also (doing the) creating together with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: in these last days has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: in these last days has spoken to us by (his) Son, whom he [placed/made/appointed/chose] heir of all things, through whom also he made the [universe/worlds].</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="3" />Tuhan pung Ana ni, kasi tunju Dia pung Bapa pung hebat,<bt>This Child of God, exhibits/shows His Father's amazingness/glory/majesty, [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke matahari pung sinar yang tapontas dari carmín.<bt>just like the rays/shining of the sun which bounce/reflect off a mirror.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Te Dia satu model parsís ke Dia pung Bapa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He is an exact model/type/form as His Father.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng dari Dia pung Kata-kata yang hebat,<bt>And from His incredible Words/Sayings,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia kasi jalan samua yang ada di langit deng di bumi.<bt>He set-in-motion everything which exists in heaven and on earth.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia ju buka jalan,<bt>He also opened the way,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko hapus buang orang pung sala-sala dong,<bt>to wipe away people's wrongs,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko biar dong jadi barisi.<bt>so that they could be/become clean/holy/pure.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ais Dia pulang pi sorga,<bt>Then He went back to heaven,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** pulang pi (2009b)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** pulang pi (2009b)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko dudu di Tuhan Allah pung sablá kanan,<bt>to sit at God's right side,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">di tampa yang paling hormat.<bt>in the place of highest respect.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who being the [brightness/radiance/reflection] of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who being the [brightness/radiance/reflection] of his [God's] glory, and the exact [image/likeness/representation/stamp] of his [God's] [person/being/nature], and [upholding/sustaining/bearing [support &amp; movement]] all things by his powerful word, [when/after] he had [purged/cleansed/ provided purification from] our sins, sat down on the right side of the Majesty on high. Chrysostom: phws, ek phwtos: Brightness, radiance, reflection.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah pung Ana paling hebat, lebe dari ana bua di sorga<bt>God's Child is absolutely incredible, more than the *angels (underlings in heaven)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Tuhan Allah pung ana bua di sorga memang hebat. Ma Dia pung Ana yang paling hebat, lebe dari dong samua. Tuhan Allah pung pangkat, paling tinggi. Deng Dia su kasi Dia pung pangkat sandiri sang Dia pung Ana. Andia ko Dia pung Ana, lebe tinggi dari ana bua di sorga dong.<bt>God's angels in heaven really are incredible. But His Child who is most/absolutely incredible, even more than all of them. God has the highest rank. And He has already given His own rank to His Child. That is why His Child is more/greater than His angels. [EXEG: ‘name’ = rank; TH, Ex. Summ. CEG word studies]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Being made so much [greater/superior"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Being made so much [greater/superior [of dignity, worth, advantage, power, possibly goodness; kind not degree] than the angels, just as he has by inheritance obtained a [more excellent/outstanding/greater/superior] name than theirs.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Tuhan Allah parná omong sang Dia pung Ana bilang,<bt>God once spoke to His Child saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ini hari, Beta angka sang Lu ko pegang parenta.&gt;&gt;<bt>"Today, I am elevating/appointing You to rule." [DISCOURSE: CHECK parallel quote in KM Acts 13:32-33 quoting Ps. 2:7; /Ini hari, Beta angka sang Lu ko pegang parenta./ "Today, I lift You up/install You in order to hold authority." Ps 2:6 provides context of coronation for making sense out of this verse. As is, it is incoherent, as in most English translations. This fits this context better as well. One commentator notes “5:5. Citing again Psalm 2:7 (see comment on Heb 1:5), the writer proves from it that *Christ's royal coronation was God's initiative. In the next verse he links this kingship with the high priesthood.” (form CR) Bruce also links this to “enthronement” in same quote at 5:5, and here at 1:5 says this same quote may “have preserved the text of a coronation liturgy used by the Davidic dynasty”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** revised, note expanded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** revised, note expanded</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Ini hari, Beta kasi tau, bilang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">&lt;&lt;Ini hari, Beta kasi tau, bilang, Lu ni, Beta pung Ana.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:5a" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 2:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tuhan Allah ju omong bilang,<bt>God also spoke saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta ni, Dia pung Bapa.<bt>"I am His Father.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Dia tu, Beta pung Ana.&gt;&gt;<bt>And He is My Child."</bt><note reference="1:5b" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Samuel 7:14, 1 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 17:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tuhan Allah omong memang bagitu so'al Dia pung Ana, ma Dia sonde parná omong bagitu so'al Dia pung ana bua di sorga.<bt>God spoke beforehand like that about His Child, but He never spoke that way about His angels in heaven. [EXEG: negative to emph positive, Miller and common translation principle]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: To which of the angels"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: To which of the angels did he ever say, "You are my Son. Today I have given you birth." And again, "I will be a Father to him, and he will be a Son to me."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Waktu Tuhan Allah kirim datang Dia pung Ana yang paling hebat, Dia ju parenta Dia pung ana bua di sorga bilang,<bt>When God sent His Child who is so amazing, He also commanded His angels in heaven saying, [EXEG: Gk /palin/ ‘again, furthermore’ Ex.Summ.; whole verse referring to incarnation (Ex. Summ 1.1); ‘firstborn’ = supreme over all, not first in sequence, LN, TH, ICC, TNTC (see also Colossians).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;We! Ana bua dong!<bt>"We! (You) angels!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bosong musti pi kasi hormat,<bt>You-pl must show honour/respect,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng sémba sang Beta pung Ana doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>and worship My Child now/imperative!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And again, when he brings"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And again, when he brings his firstborn into the world, he says, "Let all God's angels worship him."</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 32:43; Lukas 2:13-14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Tuhan Allah ju omong so'al Dia pung ana bua di sorga bilang,<bt>God has also spoken about His angels in heaven saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta bekin Beta pung ana bua di sorga dong,<bt>"I make My underlings/angels in heaven,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">jadi kincang sama ke angin.<bt>to be/become swift like (the) wind. [EXEG: see discussion in Miller.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta bekin Beta pung hamba dong,<bt>I make My servants2 (mesolectal for parallelism), [NOTE: it is not /doulos/ here, so hamba OK]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">jadi sama ke api.&gt;&gt;<bt>to be/become like fire. [NOTE to daughter translations: if a word like ‘powerful’ does not collocate with ‘fire’ just leave it as is. Don't force it with manyala, kuat, karás or something that doesn't collocate or have support. Better to just leave vague.]</bt><note reference="1:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 104:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tuhan Allah omong bagitu, tagal dong tu, cuma Dia pung tukang suru-suru sa.<bt>God spoke like that, because they are only/merely His servants (people who habitually take orders).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And he says of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And he says of the angels, "Who makes his angels winds, and his [religious servants/ministers] a flame of fire."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma Dia omong laen lai kasi Dia pung Ana sandiri bilang,<bt>But He spoke differently altogether to His own Child saying, [EXEG: Gk /pros/ here can be ‘of, about’ (NRSV, CEV) or ‘to’ (NLT, Ex. Summ., LN). Because the rest of 8-9 is 2s direct address, in these lgs here it has to be ‘to’, not ‘about’, even though the higher level contrast is ‘about the angels’ – ‘about His Son’.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lu ni, Tuhan Allah.<bt>"You-sg here are God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lu nanti dudu di korsi parenta sampe salamanya.<bt>You will sit in the seat of government until forever.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lu nanti pegang kuasa ko parenta deng hati lurus.<bt>You will hold power/authority to rule/govern with a straight/honest/right liver.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Regularize &quot;scepter&quot; from similar quotations. LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">Regularize "scepter" from similar quotations. LITERALLY: But he says to the Son: "O God, your throne is forever and ever. The sceptre of your kingdom is a sceptre of [righteousness/justice].]<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="9" />Lu pung hati sanáng lia orang yang idop lurus.<bt>Your liver is happy seeing people who live straight/honest/right.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ma Lu pung hati susa lia orang yang idop pakane'o.<bt>But Your liver is troubled seeing people who live bent/twisted/evil. [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK UNS's sense of /pakane'o/ in Rote sense of "twisted morally", or Sabu sense of "twisting that causes delays in reaching your goal". Should it be /babengko/?]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Andia ko Lu pung hati sanáng,<bt>That is why Your liver is happy, [EXEG: “oil of gladness” Who is joyful? Some say joyful situation, Many say Christ/You is joyful (Bruce, Miller, CEV, TH, implied by NLT, NIC)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) My liver changed to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) My liver changed to Your liver</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko Beta po'a minya di Lu pung kapala,<bt>so I pour oil on Your head,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko angka sang Lu jadi Raja lebe dari yang laen dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>to appoint You to be King more than the others." [NOTE: Not clear to me. (Chuck).] [EXEG: (CR): I can see a connection that because He loves right and hates wrong God anoints Him in a situation of intense joy. How to bring this out?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You have loved righteousness, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You have loved righteousness, and hated lawlessness. Therefore your God has annointed you with the oil of gladness above your comrades."</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:8-9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 45:7-8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Tuhan Allah ju omong sang Dia pung Ana bilang,<bt>God also speaks/spoke to His Child saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ana, ó!<bt>"Child, ó!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lu ni, Bos yang su parenta memang dari dolu.<bt>You-sg are the Boss/master who has governed from before.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lu ni, yang suru ko langit ada memang.<bt>You are the one who commanded so that the sky/heaven existed straight away.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lu ni, yang parenta ko bumi jadi memang.<bt>You are the one who commanded so that the earth existed straight away.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And, &quot;You Lord, in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And, "You Lord, in the beginning, have laid the foundation of the earth, and the heavens are the work of your hands.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11-12" />Nanti langit deng bumi puruk buang.<bt>Sky/heaven and earth will completely decay.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nanti langit deng bumi ilang buang.<bt>Sky/heaven and earth will completely disappear.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Ma Lu sandiri idop tarús-tarús.<bt>But You yourself will live forever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They will [be ruined/be destroyed],"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They will [be ruined/be destroyed], but you remain. They will become old like a garment.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti Lu angka buang langit deng bumi,<bt>You will get rid of sky/heaven and earth,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke orang angka buang pakean puruk.<bt>like a person gets rid of filthy (also implies worn) clothes.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti Lu ganti langit deng bumi,<bt>You will replace/change sky/heaven and earth,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke orang ganti pakean baru.<bt>like a person replaces/changes (to wear) new clothes.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma Lu sandiri sonde bagitu.<bt>But You yourself are not like that (or: that will not happen to You).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal Lu idop sampe salamanya.&gt;&gt;<bt>Because You live forever."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You will [roll/fold] them up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You will [roll/fold] them up like a robe, and will change them like clothes. But you are the same, and your years will not come to an end."</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:10-12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 102:26-28</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Tuhan Allah ju omong sang Dia pung Ana bilang,<bt>God also spoke to His Child saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ana, é!<bt>"Child, é!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Mari dudu sini, di tampa paling hormat,<bt>Come sit here in the place of highest honour,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">di Beta pung sablá kanan ni.<bt>at My right side.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti Beta bekin sang Lu pung musu dong,<bt>I will make (can also have sense of bother/mistreat/deal with) Your enemies,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sampe dong ta'alok sang Lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>to the point that they surrender/submit to You."</bt><note reference="1:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tuhan Allah omong memang bagitu so'al Dia pung Ana, ma Dia sonde parná omong bagitu so'al Dia pung ana bua di sorga.<bt>God spoke beforehand like that about His Child, but He never spoke like that about His angels in heaven.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But to which of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But to which of the angels did he ever say, "Sit on my right side, until I make your enemies your footstool"?</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Dia pung ana bua dong memang pantíng. Te Dia utus sang dong, ko pi urus Dia pung orang samua yang nanti Dia kasi salamat dari dong pung sala-sala. Biar bagitu, ma Tuhan Allah pung Ana, masi lebe dari dong samua.<bt>His angels really are important. Cuz (elaboration) He commissioned/sent them to go manage/handle matters/take care of all His people whom He will *save/rescue from their wrongs. Even that being the case, nevertheless God's Child is still more than all of them. [EXEG: CR comment on ov: “angels...to show the way of *salvation to them.” “Angels seldom if ever show people the way of salvation.” Changed to better match “to minister for those who shall be heirs of salvation?”. Gk is complex for local lgs in that Object:Undergoer of “minister to” is also Subject:Undergoer of “salvation”. GENRE: summary/recap: TH, Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) revised 2nd sentence, note"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) revised 2nd sentence, note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Are they not all ministering"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Are they not all ministering spirits, sent out to minister for those who shall be heirs of salvation?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te Dia utus sang dong, ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Te Dia utus sang dong, ko pi urus Dia pung orang samua, ko kasi tunju jalan salamat sang dong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang tola buang Tuhan pung kabar salamat yang hebat<bt>Don't throw away God's message of great salvation</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Tagal itu, kotong musti pegang kuat-kuat apa yang kotong su dengar so'al Tuhan Allah pung Ana, ko kotong jang lupa buang.<bt>Because of that, we-inc must hold firmly to what we have heard about God's Child, so that we do not forget it (serial verb construction here could imply: with unfortunate consequences).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore we ought to pay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore we ought to pay strict attention to the things we have heard, lest at any time we would [drift away/be carried away]. dia touto may be proleptic to meépote, not back to Ch. 1.<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>perissotéroos: more, a strong comparative. More than what? "Pay attention more than we did before" doesn't fit the context. "More than we pay attention to the message given by angels" is most likely. Also possible, the intensive meaning "pay particular attention" akousthéisin: the truths we have heard, handed down from Jesus. The writer of Hebrews doesn't use the term "Gospel", but that's what he's talking about<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>pararyóomen: the opposite of "stick wit" o "tink plenny", used of a ship drifting away. It implies that if we don't stick with the truth from Jesus, we'll get away from it and end up in trouble. It's like passing up an opportunity that you won't get again</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dolu Tuhan pake Dia pung ana bua dari sorga, ko kasi tau Dia pung pasán sang kotong pung nene-moyang dong. Dia pung batúl, kotong bisa parcaya itu pasán samua, te itu batúl tarús. Kalo dong langgar Dia pung parenta, dong pasti kaná hukuman yang pantas.<bt>Formerly God2 used His angels, to tell/explain His message to our-inc ancestors. In truth, we can believe/trust that entire message, cuz (elaboration) it is continually true. When they transgressed those commands of His, they definitely got an appropriate punishment. [EXEG: see Ex. Summ. for complexity of Gk ‘firm, binding, authoritative, valid, trustworthy...’]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** just punishment (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** just punishment (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="endikon: appropriate, based on justice. R"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">endikon: appropriate, based on justice. R 3:8 God goin punish da peopo dat tink lidat! LITERALLY: For since the word spoken through angels was [firm/solid/steadfast], and every transgression and disobedience received a just [reward/retribution/punishment],<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Memang dolu bagitu. Ma sakarang Tuhan pung Ana su buka jalan baru ko kasi salamat sang manusia. Dia su kasi tau ini jalan salamat yang hebat sang Dia pung orang yang layani sang Dia di bumi. Ais dong kasi tau sang kotong, ko kotong parcaya. Ma kalo kotong sonde toe, na, kotong su paya batúl ni!<bt>That's really how it used to be. But now God2's Child has already opened a new way to save humans. He has already told/explained/made known this incredible way of salvation to His people who serve Him on earth. So they told us-inc, so we believe. But if we don't care about it, na, we are in serious-trouble!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: How shall we escape, if"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: How shall we escape, if we [neglect/do not pay attention to] such a great salvation, which at the first began to be spoken through the Lord, and was confirmed to us by those that heard him.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te Tuhan Allah ju kasi kuasa ko dong bekin tanda heran macam-macam. Dia ju kasi turun Dia pung Roh sang dong, ko dong bekin banya hal laen iko Dia pung mau. Tagal itu samua, andia ko kotong tau bilang, itu jalan salamat tu, memang batúl.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God also gives power/authority so they can do various sorts of amazing signs (= *miracles). He also sent/sends down His Spirit to them, so they can do many other things according to His will. Because of all that, that is why we know that that way of salvation is really true/correct.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: God also bore witness, with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: God also bore witness, with signs and wonders, and various [miracles/powers], and gifts of the Holy Spirit, according to his own will.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Akurang ko Tuhan Allah pung Ana bekin randá diri ko jadi manusia?<bt>Why did/does God's Child lower Himself to become human?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Beta ada omong so'al dunya model baru yang nanti mau datang. Ma Tuhan Allah sonde parná kasi tau Dia pung ana bua di sorga dong bilang, nanti dong yang urus itu dunya. Te manusia yang nanti urus.<bt>I am speaking about the new model/form of the world which is going to come. But God never told His angels that later they would be the one to run/look after the world. Cuz (reason) humans would be the ones to look after it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For God has not put"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For God has not put the world to come, of which we speak, under subjection to the angels. perì hées lalóumen: It's the new order we are talking about<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Di Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi, ba'i Daud parná tanya so'al manusia pung harga bilang,<bt>In God's Holy Writings, Gf/Ff Daud once asked about the value/worth of humans saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah!<bt>"God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Akurang ko Tuhan taro mata sang manusia?<bt>Why does God2 pay attention (Idiom: place eyes) to humans?</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Akurang ko Tuhan sayang sang dong?<bt>Why does God2 love them?</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te dong cuma manusia biasa sa!<bt>Since they are merely normal humans!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hyios anthroopou: not Jesus' title, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">hyios anthroopou: not Jesus' title, but equivalent to "a human" LITERALLY: Instead, it was testified somewhere, "What is man, that you think about him, the son of man that you care for him?<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="7" />Ma Tuhan su kasi kuasa sang dong,<bt>But God2 has given power/authority to them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko dong jadi amper sama deng ana bua di sorga.<bt>so they are almost the same as angels (in heaven). [EXEG: Gk “somewhat, only a little” can mean 1) small degree, or 2) short time. (see Ex. Summ.) We take the first (TH, Miller = rank/power a bit less), in all honesty because the second is extremely hard to mirror in these lgs. /tahan/ “briefly, momentarily, temporarily” and its equivalents modify verbs, not comparisons. E.g. ‘stay briefly’, ‘stop briefly’. So to try and match second would skew the focus with a whole proposition. Note that the element of ‘temporarily’ and restored to glory are explicit in vs. 9, so the overall point comes through. “glory and honor” are one thing = rule over creation, Ex. Summ.] [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK that this means “a little lower than”. ALT: /sonde sama deng/ “not the same as” should also carry the intended meaning, as it implies lower in a hierarchy in these lgs.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) notes added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) notes added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan ju kasi hormat sang dong,<bt>God2 also gives respect/honour to them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng angka sang dong,<bt>and elevates/appoints them,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You made him a little"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You made him a little lower than the angels. You crowned him with glory and honor, [and set him over the works of your hands.]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">
      <v n="8" />ko dong parenta samua yang Tuhan su bekin.&gt;&gt;<bt>so they would rule/govern everything that God2 had made."</bt><note reference="2:6-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 8:5-7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Jadi iko ba'i Daud pung tulisan tu, Tuhan Allah bekin manusia jadi bos, ko dong urus samua yang Dia su bekin. Padahal kotong balóm parná tau manusia satu ju yang parenta samua-samua bagitu.<bt>So (consequently), according to Gf/Ff Daud's writings, God made humans boss/master, so they could manage/look after everything which He had made. Whereas in fact, we-inc have never known a single human who has ruled/governed everything like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You have put all things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You have put all things in subjection under his feet." For in that he [God] put all in subjection under him [people], he [God] left nothing that is not put under him [people]. But now we do not see all things put under him [people] yet.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ma ada Satu yang bisa parenta samua-samua. Dia tu, andia Yesus. Dia datang tenga tahan di bumi, ko jadi manusia yang pikol sangsara sampe mati. Dia mati bagitu, ko kasi tunju Tuhan Allah pung hati bae sang manusia. Ais itu ju, Tuhan Allah puji-puji sang Dia deng angka nae tinggi-tinggi sang Dia, ko Dia parenta samua yang Tuhan Allah su bekin.<bt>But there is One who can govern everything. He is Yesus. He came (and) lived temporarily on earth, to become a human who bore diificulty/suffering to the point of death. He died like that to show/demonstrate God's goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to humans. After that, God kept praising Him and elevate/exalt Him, so He (could) govern everything that God had made. [EXEG: Gk genitive “suffering of death” = objective gen, Careful to lean on the side of his death resulting from his suffering, not that he suffered his whole life. When did “glory and honor” happen? death, then exaltation (Miller, Ex. Summ.)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note expanded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note expanded</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But we see Jesus, who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But we see Jesus, who was made a little lower than the angels, through the suffering of death, crowned with glory and honor; so that he by the grace of God should taste death for every person.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Jadi pantas Tuhan Allah kasi Yesus pikol sangsara, ko biar Yesus bisa buka jalan salamat kasi sang manusia. Te Tuhan Allah mau ko banya orang bisa idop sama-sama deng Dia di sorga. Te Tuhan Allah yang bekin samua-samua. Deng samua yang idop, ada tagal Dia.<bt>So it is appropriate that God had Yesus bear suffering, so that Yesus could open the way of salvation for humans. Cuz (elaboration) wanted for many people could live together with Him in heaven. Cuz (elaboration) God is the one who created everything. And everything that lives, exists because of Him. [EXEG: “bring many sons to glory” = many people to eternal life (Miller, Ex. Summ)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** deleted /cari jalan/ (2009), note"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** deleted /cari jalan/ (2009), note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For it was fitting for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For it was fitting for him [God], for whom are all things, and through whom are all things, in bringing many sons to glory, to make the leader of their salvation perfect through sufferings. éprepen: not a strong expression, as if God were compelled to do something. fitting, appropriate<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>di' hòn: for whom, the reason why something happens, the person for whose sake something is done; the justifying reason why something exists. TEV equates this with creation, but the connection isn't clear. Check if Pidgin "everyting fo him" can mean "in favor of him" or "on his side"; if so, there may be an ambiguity di' hóu: by whom, the cause or origin of something, or the means by which it happens; the means of existence; he made it happen. TEV equates this with preservation, but the connection isn't clear<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>archeegòn: path-opener, way-breaker, pioneer; "open da road"? implies that he goes ahead of the others teleióosai: suggests the exaltation of Jesus: cause Jesus to have the position that was rightly his because of the way in which he suffered, or cause Jesus to be everything he was meant to be because of the way he had suffered. Does not imply that he was imperfect or inadequate to start with, but that suffering made him completely effective in that people could relate to him fully<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Tuhan Allah pasti tarima bae sang orang yang Yesus bekin jadi barisi, ko dong jadi Tuhan pung ana-ana. Tuhan Allah ju, Yesus pung Bapa. Deng bagitu, Yesus deng dong, satu Bapa. Andia ko Yesus su sonde malu pange sang dong bilang,<bt>God will surely accept people whom Yesus makes become clean/holy [NOTE: unmarked for aspect], so they become God2's children/underlings. God is also Yesus' Father. In that way, Yesus and them have the same Father. That is why Yesus is not ashamed to call them, [EXEG: Pretty unanimous agreement that Jesus is the agent doing the sanctifying in this verse, so corrected from ov that implied people living holy was what made them acceptable.] [NOTE to daughter translations: don't try to force the Gk word play on “those sanctified” and “the one sanctifying”. NLT, CEV, etc.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** clarified relationship and “holy”; corrected"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** clarified relationship and “holy”; corrected 1st sentence so Yesus is the agent of sanctifying the people (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo orang iko itu jalan barisi,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Kalo orang iko itu jalan barisi, Tuhan Allah pasti tarima bae sang dong, ko dong jadi Dia pung ana-ana. Tagal Tuhan Allah ju Yesus pung Bapa, andia ko Yesus su sonde malu pange sang dong, bilang,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Bosong ni, Beta pung sodara sandiri.&gt;&gt;<bt>"You-pl here, are My own siblings."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sodara &gt; adi-kaka ??"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">sodara &gt; adi-kaka ??</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For both he who sanctifies"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For both he who sanctifies and those who are sanctified are all one. For that reason he is not ashamed to call them 'brothers'. hagiázoon: setting apart for God (Gute Nachricht) or purifying from sin ethically and ritually (TEV) reflect two related senses of the word. GN's argument is that "bring to glory" in 10 is a broad concept like "all out for God". TEV's argument is that "salvation" and "perfect" (of completing the consecration ceremony for priests, LXX Lev. 4:5 "and the priest who is now anointed and (teteleiooménos) perfect shall take some of the blood and ..." and 8:33 "you shall not go out of the Tent for seven days, until the day is fulfilled, the day of your (teleioóseoos) perfection. Seven days (teleioósei) purify your hands") suggest the priest's work of ritually purifying people from sin<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>ex henòs: single origin, masculine or neuter. Neuter would be "one origin"; masculine would be "the same father (= God)" or "from one stock, common humanity". In either case it refers to Jesus and the people he is saving ouk epaischýnetai: not as though he is doing something he shouldn't, but as though some people criticize him for calling us his brothers and sisters, but he stands up for us and insists that's the way it is<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Te Yesus su kasi tau Dia pung Bapa bilang,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) Yesus has already told His Father saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta mau kasi tau sang Beta pung sodara dong,<bt>"I want to tell/explain to My siblings,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">so'al Bapa pung bae!<bt>about Father's goodness!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta mau manyanyi di dong pung teng-tenga,<bt>I want to sing in their midst,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">so'al Bapa pung hebat!&gt;&gt;<bt>about Father's greatness!" [NOTE: not “glory” here. Gk no object of praise.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Saying, &quot;I will declare your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Saying, "I will declare your name to my brothers. In the middle of the congregation I will sing praise to you." tò ónomá sou: tell people what you are really like<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>tóis adelphóis mou: more than Jesus's immediate family -- all his followers hymneésoo: sing praise, perhaps with more emphasis on who a person is than on what that person has done, which is a little more on the order of thanksgiving<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 22:23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Yesus ju omong tarús bilang,<bt>Yesus also continued speaking saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta akan taro Beta pung parcaya tarús sang Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;<bt>"I will continue to place my trust in God." [EXEG: trust, rather than belief relating to salvation here. Miller, NRSV, NLT]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais Yesus ju omong lai bilang,<bt>And Yesus also spoke again saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lia dolo! Beta ada di sini,<bt>"Have a look! I am here,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana dong,<bt>together with God's children,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang Dia su sarakan kasi Beta, ko Beta urus.&gt;&gt;<bt>whom He has turned over/surrendered to Me, for Me to manage/look after." [EXEG: Gk ‘given’ here = entrusted, deposited (Miller, LN, BAGD)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And again, &quot;I will put"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And again, "I will put my trust in him." And again, "Look! I and the children which God has given me." ésomai pepoithoòs: future perfect embodies a stative participle with passive force and effect on the topic. "Me, I goin trus God" misses that highly marked form, while "God, he da guy" locks on to the stativeness of it, at the cost of downplaying the marked position of egoò<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>édooken: not Jesus's children in a physical sense. In the context, it's God's other children he is talking about, as the next verse picks up</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 8:17, 18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Tagal Tuhan pung ana-ana dong, manusia biasa, andia ko Yesus ju musti jadi manusia sama ke dong. Te Dia musti jadi manusia dolo, baru Dia bisa mati. Lewat Dia pung mati tu, baru Dia bisa pi rampas kuasa dari setan dong pung bos. Te bos jahat tu, yang pegang kuasa ko urus hal-hal yang ta'ika deng so'al mati.<bt>Because God2's children are normal humans, that is why Yesus also had to become human like them. Cuz (elaboration) He needed to first become human before He could die. By means of His death, only-then could He go snatch away power/authority of the *devil (=boss of the evil spirits). Cuz (elaboration) that evil boss, is the one who has the power to manage things which are connected/tied to death.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="haimatos kai sarkos: &quot;skin an blood&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">haimatos kai sarkos: "skin an blood" is the expression Pidgin speakers can relate to. LITERALLY: Therefore, since the children are partakers of flesh and blood, he himself likewise partook of the same, that through death he might destroy him that had the power of death, that is the devil.<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>parapleesíoos metéschen: took on their nature in just the same way katargeéseei: render something inoperative, rather than destroy it physically. It happens when a superior force enters its realm and takes over<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>krátos échonta tóu thanátou: dominion over the realm of death (Herodotus uses the genitive in this way)</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Deng dia ju bekin manusia taku so'al mati, sampe dong iko dia pung mau-mau, sama ke budak. Ma sakarang Yesus su bisa kasi bebas sang manusia dari dong pung rasa taku.<bt>And he also made humans afraid about dying, to the point that they follow his desires, just like slaves. But now Yesus can already free humans from that fear of theirs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Consistent with metaphorical references to slaves"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">Consistent with metaphorical references to slaves in Romans. LITERALLY: And release those, who were slaves all their lives because of their fear of death.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Te su jalás bilang, Yesus sonde datang ko tolong sang Tuhan pung ana bua di sorga. Ma Dia datang ko tolong sang kotong, andia ba'i Abraham pung turunan.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) it is already clear, Yesus did not come to help God2's angels. But He came to help us-inc, that is Gf/Ff Abraham's descendants.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For surely he did not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For surely he did not [concern himself with/help] angels, but with the offspring of Abraham.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Tagal itu, Yesus jadi parsís sama ke kotong yang su jadi Dia pung sodara. Deng bagitu, Dia bisa jadi kotong pung kapala agama paling tinggi, ko tolong kotong iko Tuhan Allah pung mau. Dia ju kasi tunju Dia pung rasa kasian sang kotong. Deng Dia omong apa, na, Dia bekin iko.<bt>Because of that, Yesus became exactly like us-inc who are His siblings. In that way, He can be our highest priest, to help us follow God's will. He also wants to show His mercy/pity to us. And what ever He says, He does it. [EXEG &amp; KEY TERMS: should be "high priest" here, rather than "priest". KM Key Terms paradigm from other books is /kapala agama/ (head of religion) = "priest", &gt; /kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos/ (bosses of the Yahudi priests) = "chief priests", -- /kapala agama dong pung bos besar/ (big boss of the head of religion) = "high priest". This parallels terminological sets of other hierarchical structures. This book sometimes uses for "high priest" /kapala agama paling tinggi/ (highest head of religion), which may work in the context of this book of Hebrews, but takes it out of the terminological set. Question for consideration of team: In some contexts with high repetition of "high priest" can one start with the full form /kapala agama dong pung bos besar/ (big boss of the head of religion) = "high priest", and then track it through that passage with a reduced form /itu kapala agama tu/ "that (aforementioned) priest"?] [EXEG: “merciful and faithful high priest” = sympathy with humans and faithful to God (Miller)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="high priest *** (2009) 2nd note"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">high priest *** (2009) 2nd note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So he had to be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So he had to be made like his brothers in every way, in order to be a merciful and faithful high priest in his service to God, to make reconciliation for the sins of the people. hothen: his qualifications for the job<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>adelphóis: all other human beings hiláskesthai: not to cool down somebody who is angry, but to deal with the sin problem that has been getting in the way of people getting it right with God<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dolu kotong pung nene-moyang dong minta kapala agama dong pung bos bésar bekin korban, ko Tuhan hapus buang dong pung sala-sala dong. Sakarang Yesus sandiri su jadi korban ko Tuhan hapus buang kotong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>Formerly our ancestors asked the *high priest to make a *sacrifice, so God2 would throw away their wrongs. Now Yesus himself has become a sacrifice so that God wipes away our wrongs.</bt><v n="18" />Waktu Yesus idop di ini dunya, Dia dapa sangsara bam-banya. Ada ju yang buju-buju Dia, ko Dia bekin sala. Biar bagitu ju, ma Dia sonde jato. Tagal itu, kalo ada yang buju-buju kotong ko bekin sala, na, Yesus su bisa tolong kotong ko kotong jang jato.<bt>When Yesus was alive on this earth, He got/experienced many difficulties/sufferings. There were also those who (tried to) tempt/persuade Him to do wrong. Even that being the case, nevertheless He did not fall. Because if that, if there are those who (try to) tempt/persuade us-inc to do wrong, na, Yesus is already able to help us so we don't fall. [EXEG: The Gk seems to allow for two readings, 1) there were beings/people/forces/issues that tested/tempted Him, and 2) He also struggled with internally generated testing/temptations. My reading of LN makes it lean slightly more to the former. In these lgs without clear passives, we've accounted for both readings by being deliberately vague/broad There were also THOSE who (tried to) tempt/persuade Him to do (doublet) wrong. “Those” is simply a relativiser “who/which”, so it can cover volitional or inanimate beings/people/forces/issues, and can cover external or internal. Like the Gk, the default reading falls to external, but allows for internally generated temptations as well.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because he himself has suffered"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because he himself has suffered when he was tempted, he is able to help those who are tempted.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah pung Ana lebe hebat dari ba'i Musa<bt>God's Child is more amazing than Gf/Ff Musa</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Jadi bagini, sodara dong! Tuhan Allah su pili ame sang bosong, deng cap bosong orang hati barisi, ko bosong nanti idop sama-sama deng Dia di sorga. Tagal itu hal dong samua, bosong musti pikir alus-alus so'al Yesus. Te kotong su mangaku bilang, Dia tu, Tuhan Allah pung Utusan, deng Dia ju kotong pung Kapala Agama Paling Tinggi.<bt>So it's like this, siblings! God has chosen you-pl and stamped/branded/ categorised you as clean/holy livered people, so that you will live together with Him in heaven! Because of all those things, you-pl must think carefully/in detail about Yesus. [EXEG: CR: “Therefore” refers back to what he said in chapt 2, or maybe even 1 &amp; 2. Because of what He said about Jesus, who He is, they are urged to consider Him. “...since Jesus qualified through becoming human and going through temptations successfully, consider His trustworthiness.” (Miller). Book Theme is Who He is. The reduced “because of that” here seems to say they should consider Him because of who they are. A: Discourse complication: Gk can front the connector before the complex vocative, which points backward to a larger chunk. Local lgs here have to front the vocative, and put the connector later with the “consider Jesus” bit, which has the higher level effect of skewing the focus, even though that is what the Gk is also leading into. To force the reader to look higher than the previous sentence from this reduced adverbial clause, we changed it to: because of all those things.] Cuz (backgrounded reason) we-inc have confessed/ acknowledged that He is God's Emissary/ commissioned one/apostle, and He is also our-inc High Priest. [EXEG: 2:11 seems to focus on the process of sanctification, with the agency of Jesus fairly clearly in focus. The adjectival modifier here in 3:1 seems to be focusing on the result or the status, and is fairly well backgrounded in the balance of things. Our current rendering gets both ‘holy’ and ‘partners/partakers’ (CEV seems to miss the latter element completely). But in the context with Jesus as apostle and high priest, I think you're essentially right-it's not so much about our living holy, but about us being ascribed/branded as holy, and therefore have a right to have a share in “the heavenly calling”. Commentators are divided as to whether this is “making them fit to enter God’s presence (in heaven)” (NTC), or “set apart for God’s service (here on earth)” (HNTC). Most versions are also vague on that point. Bruce, CR. Miller says “heavenly calling” = leads them to God.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** botong &gt; bosong ; (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** botong &gt; bosong ; (2009) 1st main sentence revised considerably; note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, holy brothers, who share"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, holy brothers, who share the heavenly calling, consider Jesus, the Apostle and High Priest of our profession. "Head Priest" for a specific individual, "head priest" for the office in general.<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>epouraníou: from God in Heaven, or a call to go to Heaven. The epì prefix may localize it to a call to go to heaven, though UBS doesn't favor this view apóstolon: ambassador, one sent on a special mission. TEV downplays it as "whom God sent". In Pidgin we have usually said "send um all ova da place", but here is the only place in the New Testament where it is applied to Jesus coming to the world<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>archieréa tées homologías heemóon: the genitive ties our confession loosely to Jesus as High Priest, so "head pries fo us guys" may be needed to make the connection</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong ni, su idop barisi sama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Bosong ni, su idop barisi sama ke botong, deng nanti bosong ju idop deng Tuhan Allah di sorga.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Waktu Tuhan Allah utus sang Yesus, Yesus bekin iko Tuhan pung mau samua. Deng bagitu, Dia jadi sama ke ba'i Musa. Te ba'i Musa ju bekin iko Tuhan Allah pung mau, waktu dia layani kotong pung nene-moyang dolu-dolu dong.<bt>When God sent/commissioned Yesus, Yesus did according to all of God's will. In that way, He was like Gf/Ff Musa. Cuz (elaboration) Gf Musa also did according to God's will, when he served our-inc ancestors long ago.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He [Jesus] was faithful to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He [Jesus] was faithful to the one [God] who appointed him, just as Moses was faithful in all his [God's] household. pistòn: God could trust him completely to carry out his instructions, especially as priest. Note the initial position, highlighting the quality. "Faithful" embraces not only the idea of carrying out an assignment, but of being the kind of person you could trust to carry it out<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>poieésanti: designate, give him an assignment. The UBS suggestion of "choose" won't work here, because Pidgin "pick" implies that there were other candidates</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 12:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Biar bagitu ju, ma Yesus lebe hebat dari ba'i Musa. Te Yesus tu, sama ke kapala ruma tangga. Deng su jalás, kapala ruma tangga lebe hebat dari tukang suru-suru dalam itu ruma.<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless Yesus is greater/more amazing that Gf Musa. Cuz (elaboration) that Yesus, is like a head of household. And it is already clear, the head of household is greater/more amazing than the servants/workers in that house. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [NOTE to daughter translations: although this is literally “builder” here, Miller notes that in this verse the Gk has the sense of “founder” of a family who founds, builds and furnishes a family/clan. The Kupang may not be the best fit enough here, so see if your language can do better.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For this one [Jesus] was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For this one [Jesus] was worthy of more glory than Moses, just as the one who builds a house has more honor than the house. oíkou: house, but fits better with "take care God's ohana" in Verse 2. So in Verse 3 it probably shouldn't be just the building. "Start one ohana" works. The key is that Moses was part of the ohana he was helping. Verses 3 and 4 play on different senses of the Greek word; Pidgin doesn't match those senses. "God's house" in the sense of the Jerusalem temple isn't even in focus in either part<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>dóxees: glory; Jesus gets more credit than Moses timeèn: the builder is honored more than the house, or the founder of the lineage is honored more than the lineage that comes from him<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Tiap orang bangun dia pung ruma tangga sandiri-sandiri. Ma Tuhan Allah bangun samua-samua.<bt>Each person builds his own (separate) household. But God builds everything. [NOTE to daughter translations: try to preserve the “build” verb if possible, but don't force the collocation if it doesn't work. Try bekin. Or manage.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="all the banguns could go to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">all the banguns could go to bekin</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For every house is built"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For every house is built by someone. But God is the builder of everything.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Jadi ba'i Musa bekin iko Tuhan Allah pung mau, waktu dia jadi tukang suru-suru kasi Tuhan pung isi ruma. Te itu waktu, dia kasi tau memang apa yang nanti Tuhan Allah mau bekin.<bt>So (consequently), Gf Musa did according to God's will, when he became a servant/worker to God2's household. Cuz (elaboration) at that time, he foretold what God was going to do. [NOTE: TB not helpful here, so don't derail discussions by consulting it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Moses was indeed faithful as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Moses was indeed faithful as a servant in all his house, for a testimony of those things which were to be spoken later. oikooi: "peopo" rather than "ohana" because he calls them "bruddas an sistas," which is more personal.<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>pistòs: as in Verse 2, not just that he actually did it, but that God could trust him to do it hoos therápoon: a trustworthy servant who worked for God<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Yesus ju bekin iko Tuhan Allah pung mau, ma Dia bukan tukang suru-suru sama ke ba'i Musa. Tagal Dia tu, Kristus, Tuhan Allah pung Ana yang Dia su pili memang dari dolu, ko mau kirim datang di ini dunya. Deng Kristus tau urus batúl-batúl Dia pung Bapa pung isi ruma. Jadi kalo kotong pegang kuat-kuat kotong pung parcaya, deng kotong baharap tarús sang Kristus, kotong ju bisa maso jadi Dia pung isi ruma.<bt>Yesus also did according to God's will, but He was not a servant/worker like Gf Musa. Because He was/is the Kristus, God's Child whom He had chosen beforehand from long ago, to be sent here to this world. And Kristus knows how to correctly/properly manage/oversee His Father's household. So (consequently), if we-inc hold firmly to our beliefs, and we continue to hope in Kristus, we also can enter to become His household.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But Christ as a son"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But Christ as a son over his [God's] house, whose house we are, if we hold fast the [confidence/courage] and the [pride/ boasting] [of/in] [the hope/what we hope for]. dè: Christ unexpectedly in contrast to Moses<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>hoos huiòs: not "was God's Son" but "Christ was in the character of a son in charge of the family home or family line. He's still following out the household or lineage metaphor parresían: openness and freedom with which believers approach God, and as a consequence, the courage with which they approach even enemies<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>kaúcheema tées elpídos: boasting, pride, here not in a negative sense from pride, but more positive, like boldness and confidence -- we know what's going to happen, and we feel very positive about telling people about it.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang bale balakang kasi tenga bosong pung parcaya sama ke nene-moyang dong, tagal dong sonde bisa maso barenti cape di tana yang Tuhan Allah su janji<bt>Don't face back leaving your belief like the ancestors', because it didn't jadi for them to enter the rest (Idiom: stop tiredness) in that land that God had promised</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Tagal itu, bosong musti pasang talinga ko dengar bae-bae apa yang Tuhan Allah pung Roh Barisi su omong bilang,<bt>Because of that, you-pl must fasten ears to listen carefully to what it is that God's Holy Spirit has said that,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***botong &gt; bosong (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***botong &gt; bosong (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ini hari, kalo bosong dengar Tuhan Allah pung omong,<bt>"This day, if you-pl listen to what God has to say,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So, as the Holy Spirit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So, as the Holy Spirit says, "Today if you will hear his voice, dió: in view of all this, as a result of what I have just been telling you, linking in a general way with what has gone before<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>eàn: more like English "when" than "if" -- he's about to tell them what God said, and he wants them to obey it phoonées autóu: In the context of Verse 6, probably Christ's voice, rather than the voice of God. "Hearing his voice" doesn't mean "hear the sound but pay no attention"; it refers to the content, not the medium, and stands in antithesis to "don't be stubborn", so it must mean "hear and heed" or "pay attention and change" or "listen to what he says"<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="8" />bosong jang kapala batu,<bt>you-pl should not be stubborn (Idiom: rock head),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sama ke itu orang dong,<bt>like those people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang jalan pi-datang sampe ampa pulu taon di tampa sunyi.<bt>who went going-coming for 40 years in the empty land.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te dong sonde mau toe lai sang Musa,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) they didn't want to pay attention to/give consideration to Musa anymore,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sampe Tuhan Allah sandiri amper-amper<bt>to the point that God himself very nearly</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">su sonde bisa sabar deng dong lai.<bt>lost patience with them. [EXEG: from Ex. Summ. that they tested God's patience. Gk peirasmóu: pushed God hard to see if he would let them get away with what they were doing. (JEG)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do not be stubborn as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do not be stubborn as you were in the rebellion, during the time of testing in the wilderness, parapikrasmóoi: rebellion against Moses' leadership<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>peirasmóu: pushed God hard to see if he would let them get away with what they were doing</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="9-10" />Bayangkan sa!<bt>Just imagine!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ampa pulu taon Beta bekin tanda heran macam-macam<bt>(For) 40 years I made various sorts of *amazing signs</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">di dong pung mata biji!<bt>before their eyeballs!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma dong maen coba-coba sang Beta tarús.<bt>But they kept (trying to) test my metal/character/ patience continually. (to see what He is made of/how respond)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When your ancestors tested me,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When your ancestors tested me, tried me, and saw my actions forty years. dokimasíaai: put to the test<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>éidon tà érga mou: either "in spite of the fact that they had seen the good I had done them for forty years past" or "and they saw the harm I did to them for the next forty years". The latter fits in better with Verse 17. mou: There is a shift from "the Holy Spirit saying" in Verse 7 to "God saying" in Verse 9<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Andia ko Beta ju mara sang dong bilang,<bt>That is why I was also angry with them saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Bosong ni, su talalu!<bt>'You-pl here are too much!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te bosong su bale balakang kasi tenga Beta pung jalan,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) You have turned your back and abandoned My way (=rejection),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko iko bosong pung jalan yang babengko sa!&gt;<bt>so you could follow your own crooked path!'</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So I was angry with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So I was angry with that generation, and said, "[Their hearts are always going astray/ they are always disloyal], and they [have not known my ways/ refuse to obey my commands]. planóontai: stray from the path, go the wrong way, make the wrong choice, are disloyal to me<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>téei kardíaai: their minds and wills are directed away from God's will</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="11" />Beta su sonde tahan lia bosong pung jahat bagitu lai.<bt>I cannot stand to watch your evil like that anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia ko Beta kutuk sang bosong bilang,<bt>That is why I curse you saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">&lt;Bosong su sonde bole maso lai ko barenti cape sama-sama deng Beta.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>'You may no longer enter to rest together with Me.'"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So I swore in my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So I swore in my wrath, 'They will never enter into my rest.' eiseleúsontai: enter. Could refer to entering the land where they would rest<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>katápausin: resting place; not to be equated with eireénee. Relaxing and strengthening after hardship, or finding peace and prosperity after a period of trial and testing</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:7-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 95:7-11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Jadi sodara dong! Ati-ati ko jang sampe ada dari bosong yang bekin jahat, sampe dia sonde parcaya lai, ais bale balakang kasi tenga sang Tuhan Allah yang idop tarús.<bt>So (consequently) siblings! Be careful so it doesn't get to the point that there are those among you-pl who do evil, to the point that he does not believe anymore, and then turns his back and abandons God who lives continually.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Brothers, [pay attention/be careful] that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Brothers, [pay attention/be careful] that none of you have an evil, heart of unbelief that turns away from the living God.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Lebe bae, tiap hari bosong bekin kuat satu deng satu pung hati. Jang batunggu lai! Tagal bosong gampang kaná tipu ko bekin sala, sampe bosong ju jadi kapala batu, deng sonde toe sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>It is better, each day you strengthen/encourage each other's livers. Don't delay anymore! Because you-pl are easily decieved to do wrong/sin, to the point that you also become stubborn, and don't pay attention to/care for God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But encourage each other every"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But encourage each other every day as long as it is called 'Today', that no one be hardened by the deceitfulness of sin. allá: in contrast to having an evil heart<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>apáteei tées hamartías: you do something wrong, and that deceives you and gets you off the track</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Kotong su bisa jadi tamán satu kaki deng Yesus Kristus, asal kotong baharap tarús sang Dia, sama ke waktu kotong baru mulai parcaya sang Dia.<bt>We-inc are already able to become an intimite/fast friend (Idiom: one-legged friend) with Yesus Kristus, as long as we continue to hope in Him, just like when we had just begun to believe in Him. [EXEG: “partakers/partners of/with Christ” Miller, Ex. Summ)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For we have been made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For we have been made [partakers in /sharers in] Christ, if we hold firm to the end the confidence we had at first. métochoi: partners, like the fishermen in Luke 5:7. Used in 1:9, 3:1, 6:4, and 12:8, in the sense of sharing a common experience. It doesn't mean "divvying up the inheritance", which is one sense of "share" in English<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Te Tuhan pung Roh Barisi ju omong bagitu bilang,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2's Holy Spirit has spoken like that saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ini hari, kalo bosong dengar Tuhan Allah pung omong,<bt>"This day, if/when you-pl hear what God is saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bosong jang kapala batu, sama ke itu orang dong,<bt>you-pl should not be stubborn, like those people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang jalan pi-datang sampe ampa pulu taon di tampa sunyi,<bt>who went going-coming for 40 years in the empty land,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te dong malawan sang Musa.&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz (reason) they opposed/rebelled against Musa.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As was said, &quot;Today if"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As was said, "Today if you will hear his voice, do not harden your hearts as in the rebellion." This needs to be word for word the same as 7b-8a. It's a resumption of the quotation, this timing leading up to "rebelled", which is where Verse 16 takes off<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="te dong sonde mau toe lai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">te dong sonde mau toe lai sang Musa.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 95:7-8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Naa, sakarang beta mau tanya bagini: itu orang dong yang su dengar sang Musa, ais bale balakang kasi tenga sang dia tu, sapa? Sapa lai, kalo bukan kotong pung nene-moyang yang Musa sandiri baru antar bawa kaluar dari tana Masir.<bt>Naa, now I want to ask like this: those people who had been listening to Musa, and then turned their backs abandoning him, who were they? Who else (would it be), if it is not our ancestors whom Musa himself had just recently brought out from the land of Masir.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who were they who heard"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who were they who heard and rebelled? Wasn't it all who were led out of Egypt by Moses?</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Ais, itu orang yang bekin Tuhan Allah pung hati panas sampe ampa pulu taon tu, sapa? Sapa lai, kalo bukan kotong pung nene-moyang. Te dong idop babengko di tampa sunyi, sampe dong mati, ais dapa kubur di situ.<bt>And then, those people who made God's liver hot (=angry) for 40 years, who were they? Who else (would it be), if it was not our ancestors. Cuz (elaboration) they lived crooked in the empty land, until they died, and then were buried there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And with whom was he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And with whom was he angry for forty years? Wasn't it those who sinned, [whose bodies were left/ who fell down dead] in the wilderness?</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ais, itu orang dong yang kaná kutuk dari Tuhan Allah sampe sonde bole maso di itu tana, ko barenti cape sama-sama deng Dia tu, sapa? Sapa lai, kalo bukan kotong pung nene-moyang. Te dong sonde mau dengar sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Then, those people who were cursed by God to the point they were not allowed to enter into that land, to rest together with Him, who were they? Who else (would it be), if it was not our ancestors. Cuz (elaboration) they didn't want to listen to/obey God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And to whom did God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And to whom did God swear that they would never enter his rest but to those who did not believe.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:16-18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 14:1-35</note><v n="19" />Jadi su jalás, to! Kotong pung nene-moyang sonde dapa maso di itu tana, ko barenti cape sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah, tagal dong sonde parcaya sang Dia.<bt>So (consequently), it is already clear. Our ancestors couldn't enter into that land, to rest together with God, because they did not believe/trust in Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And we see that they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And we see that they could not enter in because of unbelief.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo kotong parcaya sang Yesus Kristus, kotong bisa idop badame deng Tuhan Allah, sama ke kotong ada barenti cape deng Dia<bt>If we believe in Yesus Kristus, we can live at peace with God, just like we are resting with Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Ma sakarang kotong musti pikir panjang, tagal Tuhan masi janji bilang, Dia pung orang dong bisa barenti cape sama-sama deng Dia. Jadi, jang sampe ada dari bosong yang tola buang apa yang Tuhan su janji.<bt>But now we must think long (Idiom: = think through the implications), because God2 still promises that His people can rest together with Him. So (consequently), may it not come to the point that there are those among you-pl who throw away what God2 has already promised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: A promise was left to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: A promise was left to us of entering into his rest. Therefore let us fear, lest, any of you be found to have come short of it. katápausin: place of rest, quoting 3:11<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>dokéei: not "seem", but "turn out, be judged by God to have failed" autóu: God's rest -- if expressed with "give", it still doesn't necessarily require "you guys", unless that's more natural in Pidgin<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Te kotong su dapa dengar itu kabar bae, sama ke kotong pung nene-moyang dong ju dapa dengar. Ma tagal dong sonde parcaya itu kabar, dong sonde dapa ontong apa-apa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we-inc have heard that good news, just like our ancestors also heard (it). But becuase they didn't believe that news, they go no benefit/advantage/profit whasoever. [EXEG: “there is an implication, because of the ‘we had the Gospel preached to us too’, that unlike them, we believed it. That is spelled out in the next verse.” (JEG, Deibler)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the Good News was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the Good News was announced to us just as to them. But the message that was heard did not profit them, because it was not mixed with faith by those who heard it. pístei: there is an implication, because of the "we had the Gospel preached to us too", that unlike them, we believed it. That is spelled out in the next verse<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ma kalo kotong parcaya, kotong bisa barenti cape sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah. Te dolu, Dia su janji bagitu deng kotong pung nene-moyang, ma ais Dia mara deng kasi tau sang dong bilang,<bt>But if we believe, we can rest together with God. Cuz formerly, He had promised like that to our ancestors, but then (later) He was angry and told them saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta su sonde tahan lia bosong pung jahat bagitu lai.<bt>"I cannot stand any longer to watch your evil.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Andia ko Beta kutuk sang bosong bilang,<bt>That is why I curse you saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Bosong su sonde bole maso lai,<bt>'You are no longer allowed to enter,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko barenti cape sama-sama deng Beta.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>to rest together with Me.'" [EXEG: same as 3:11]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Padahal kotong tau kata, waktu Tuhan bekin ame langit deng bumi, Dia su ator memang ko Dia pung orang dong bisa barenti cape, ko idop sama-sama deng Dia.<bt>Whereas we know that when God2 created the sky and earth, He had set it up beforehand so that His people could rest, to live together with Him. [EXEG: we know there is a place (Deibler); OV jadi -- padahal. What relationship is indicated by Gk /ka toi/ ‘although/namely’? 1. It indicates a concession [EXEG: EGT, Lg, Ln, Mil, My, NIC, NIGTC, TH, WBC, Wst]: he said that they would not enter his rest, although his works were completed.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For we who have believed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For we who have believed do enter into rest. As he said, "As I have sworn in my wrath, they will never enter into my rest," although the works were finished from the foundation of the world. geneethéntoon: the things he was going to do were already in place, planned ahead. Not, God finished working at creation, and hasn't done anything since<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 95:11</note><v n="4" />Di carita so'al Tuhan Allah bekin langit deng bumi, ada tatulis so'al Tuhan Allah barenti cape bilang,<bt>In the story about God creating heaven and earth, it is written about God resting saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tuhan karjá abis samua,<bt>"[After] God2 had finished doing/working all that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ju dia pung beso, pas deng hari katuju,<bt>then the following day, right on the seventh day,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Dia barenti.&gt;&gt;<bt>He stopped work/rested."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because it says in a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because it says in a certain place of the seventh day like this: "God rested the seventh day from all his works." pou: somewhere, in a part of the text he doesn't feel he needs to identify for these readers<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 2:2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Deng di bagian laen lai, Tuhan Allah omong sang kotong pung nene-moyang dong bilang,<bt>And in a different section, God spoke to our-inc ancestors saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Bosong su sonde bole maso lai,<bt>"You-pl may no longer enter,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko barenti cape sama-sama deng Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>to rest together with Me." [EXEG: same as 3:11]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And in this place again,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And in this place again, "They will never enter into my rest." en toútooi pálin: in the same quotation from the Old Testament that I was just discussing<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 95:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Jadi Tuhan Allah mau ko Dia pung orang dong barenti cape ko idop sama-sama deng Dia. Ma kotong pung nene-moyang yang dengar lebe dolo itu kabar bae, dong sonde bisa maso, tagal dong sonde bekin iko Tuhan pung mau.<bt>So (consequently), God wants for His people to rest to live together with Him. But our ancestors who first heard that good news, they could not enter, because they did not follow/obey God2's will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore since it is left"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore since it is left for some to enter in, and those to whom it was first announced did not enter because of unbelief, katápausin: still the same quotation first given in 3:11 being repeated<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ma lama-lama, Tuhan pili waktu yang laen, ko Dia pung orang bisa maso barenti cape sama-sama deng Dia. Te Dia pake ba'i Daud ko omong bilang,<bt>But eventually, God2 chose a different time, for His people to be able to enter (and) rest together with Him. Cuz (elaboration) He used Gf Daud to speak saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ini hari, kalo bosong dengar Tuhan Allah pung omong,<bt>"This day, if/when you-pl hear God speaking,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">jang bekin bosong pung hati karás ke batu,<bt>don't make your livers hard like rock (=cold-hearted, unreceptive, hard-hearted),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ma dengar bae-bae su.&gt;&gt;<bt>but listen carefully [+coaxing imperative]." [EXEG: Gk here slightly different than in 3:15]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText=", 3:18 *** note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">, 3:18 *** note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Again, he set a certain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Again, he set a certain day, saying by David after so long a time in the place already quoted, "Today, if you hear his voice, do not harden your hearts."</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 95:7-8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Waktu ba'i Daud omong bilang, &lt;&lt;ini hari&gt;&gt;, dia sonde tunju itu hari waktu Yosua antar bawa nene-moyang dong pung ana-cucu maso pi tana Kana'an. Te waktu ba'i Daud omong bagitu, dong samua su lama mati.<bt>When Gf Daud spoke saying, "this day", he was not pointing to that day when Yosua lead the ancestors children/offspring entering into the land of Kana'an. Cuz (elaboration) when Gf Daud spoke like that, all of them were long dead.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** ana-ana &gt; ana-cucu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** ana-ana &gt; ana-cucu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For if Joshua had given"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For if Joshua had given them rest, he would not have talked later about another day. ouk àn ... elálei: God is probably the subject, but may not need to be made explicit<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 31:7, Yosua 22:4</note><v n="9" />Tagal itu, kotong tau bilang, Tuhan su ator waktu yang laen, ko Dia pung orang dong bisa barenti cape, ko idop sama-sama deng Dia.<bt>Because of that, we know that, God2 had arranged a different time, for His people to be able to rest, to live together with Him. [EXEG: “there remains” = there still remains (NRSV, NLT, TH)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So there remains a sabbath"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So there remains a sabbath rest for the people of God. sabbatismòs: may have been invented by the author, from Hebrew shavat. A rest like when God rested on the seventh day. Another angle is that you could say that all human history has been part of God's rest day, but not all humans have gotten in on the resting part. It's still talking about resting, but shifts the emphasis to the time, and away from Joshua's actual occupation of the Promised Land<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Deng orang yang maso ko barenti cape sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah, dia su barenti dari dia pung karjá, sama ke Tuhan ju barenti dari Dia pung karjá pas di hari katuju, waktu Dia su bekin abis ini dunya.<bt>And a person who enters to rest together with God, s/he has ceased from his work, just like God2 also stopped His work right at the seventh day, when He had finished creating this world. [EXEG: ‘ceased working’ does not mean ceased to work for his salvation. Miller says: When God rested at creation all things were perfectly adjusted to His purpose, and He could pronounce all things good, God’s rest indicates a harmony, not a cessation from physical labor. God’s rest is marked by a completion of preparation through adjustment and harmony.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For he who has entered"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For he who has entered into his rest, has also ceased from his own works just as God did from his own. CHIASM: This one seems not to work, and needs to be recast as a parallelism, possibly because it's short and obvious. Other chiasms don't necessary cause trouble, especially if they are long enough.<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>autóu: God causes people to rest. It isn't their doing ho gàr eiselthoòn: not a reference to a specific person, but anybody who fits the qualifications. Pidgin's nonspecific "you" seems less awkward here than "anybody" or "whoeva" or "somebody" or "peopo", because the others are third person and they get crossed up with God, who is also third person<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>katápausin: getting away from the "land where they can rest" meaning and into more of a "situation in which you can rest" meaning, now that we've left Joshua</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 2:2</note><v n="11" />Jadi pasang kaki ko bosong bisa maso barenti cape ko idop sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah. Jang sampe ada yang sonde dapa maso, tagal dia sonde mau dengar Tuhan pung Kata-kata, sama ke kotong pung nene-moyang tu.<bt>So strive/struggle/work hard (Idiom: fasten feet) so you-pl can enter (and) rest together with God. May it not be that there are those who are not able to enter, because s/he does not want to listen to/obey God2's Words/Saying, like those ancestors of ours-inc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore let us make every"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore let us make every effort to enter into that rest, so that nobody will fall by following the same example of unbelief.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Te Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata dong kasi tunju jalan idop yang batúl. Dong ada pung kuasa ko maso pi dalam kotong pung hati, ko nilei kotong pung pikiran deng kotong pung mau-mau samua. Te itu Kata-kata dong memang idop, deng lebe tajam dari satu parang yang maso pi dalam daging ko potong urat balá tulang, ko kasi tabuka samua.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God's Words/Sayings show the true/correct/real way of life. They have the power/authority to enter deeply into our-inc livers, to evaluate/assess/test all our thoughts and our desires. Cuz (elaboration) those Words/Sayings really are living, and are sharper than a sword/machete which enters deeply into meat/flesh to cut tendons (and) split bones, to reveal/expose everything.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nilei = ukur"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">nilei = ukur</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the Word of God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the Word of God is alive/living, and active/ effective, and sharper than any two-edged sword, penetrating even to the separating/dividing of soul and spirit, and of joints and marrow, and is a discerner/judge of the thoughts/reflections/ideas and intentions/attitudes/ motives of the heart. distomos: Check Revelation, match 1:16 and 2:12.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Di langit deng bumi samua, sonde ada yang bisa tasambunyi dari Tuhan Allah, te Dia bisa lia samua-samua deng jalás. Nanti kotong musti pi mangada sang Dia, ko lapor samua yang kotong su bekin.<bt>Throughout the whole sky and earth, there is nothing which can be hidden from God, cuz (reason) He can see everything clearly. And later we must go before Him (as in reprting to an authority), to report on everything we have done.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There is no creature that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There is no creature that is [hidden/covered] before him, but everything is uncovered and open/exposed to his eyes to whom we have to [give account/deal]. pròs hòn heemíin ho lógos: includes the idea of a reckoning, more than just a statement that God will be our judge. UBS suggests it's not just talking about the final judgment, but the continual process of living without being able to hide anything from God<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus su jadi Kapala Agama Paling Tinggi yang lebe hebat dari kapala agama model lama dong<bt>Yesus has become a *High Priest who is more impressive than priests of the old model</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Kotong musti pegang kuat-kuat kotong pung parcaya, tagal Tuhan Allah pung Ana, Yesus, su jadi kotong pung kapala agama paling tinggi. Te Dia su ada di Tuhan Allah pung muka di sorga, ko bela sang kotong.<bt>We-inc must hold firmly to our belief, because God's Child, Yesus, has become our *highest priest [NOTE: see discussion at Heb. 2:17]. Cuz (elaboration) He is already in front of God in heaven, to defend (oral, legal) us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CONSIDER /kapala agama paling tinggi/ &gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">CONSIDER /kapala agama paling tinggi/ &gt; /kapala agama dong pung Bos Besar/ so it fits in paradigm of *priest /kapala agama/ &gt; **chief priest /kapala agama dong pung bos/ &gt; ***high priest /kapala agama dong pung bos besar/, and resonates with other hierarchies; as a Front Translation, it also encourages consistency in daughter translations; I acknowledge we don't have an elegant solution here yet.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Since we have a great"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Since we have a great high priest, who has gone into heaven, Jesus the Son of God, let us hold firmly to what we profess/confess. archieréa: this is not new information. It's a return to 2:17, picking up an argument. It shouldn't be highlighted<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>mégan: outstanding, prominent dieleelythóta: one who has gone clear through to the ultimate Heaven, another way of talking about the presence of God. Like Matthew, this writer would rather not mention God by name if he doesn't have to<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>homologías: stating publicly what we believe, going on record that we trust Christ</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Dia bisa bela bae-bae sang kotong, tagal Dia mangarti bilang, kotong ni, manusia. Kalo ada yang buju-buju ko bekin sala, na, kotong gampang jato. Yesus ju kaná goda yang sama parsís ke kotong, ma Dia sonde parná jato.<bt>He is able to defend us very well, because He understand that we are human. If there are (those) who (try to) persuade/goad (us) to do wrong/sin, we fall/succumb easily. Yesus has also experienced tempting/testing/ been bothered exactly like us, but He as never fallen.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** last sentence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** last sentence</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For we do not have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For we do not have a high priest who cannot sympathize with the feeling of our weaknesses, but one who was in every way tempted like we are, but did not sin.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus ju kaná buju-buju sama deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Yesus ju kaná buju-buju sama deng kotong, ma Dia sonde parná jato.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Tagal itu, mari ko kotong barani deka-deka deng Tuhan Allah di Dia pung korsi parenta. Te Dia tu, hati bae. Jadi kalo kotong sambayang sang Dia, na, pasti Dia mau kasi tunju Dia pung rasa kasian ko tolong sang kotong pas waktu.<bt>Because of that, let's be bold/have the courage to approach God on His governing/ruling chair. Cuz (elaboration) He is good/gracious/kind/generous. So (consequently), if/when we pray to Him, na, surely He will show/demonstrate His mercy to us and help us at the right time. [EXEG: throne of grace is metonymy for God, but church society knows the phrase/picture too well, so we preserve it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore let us come boldly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore let us come boldly before the throne of grace, that we may obtain mercy, and find grace to help in time of need. tóoi thrónooi tées cháritos: another indirect way of speaking about God. It's God who is gracious, and he is the one we approach; the throne is incidental<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>eúkairon: right at the time we need it, not delayed boeétheian: meet our need, or other people's -- it is left open<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tagal itu, kotong sonde taku pi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Tagal itu, kotong sonde taku pi minta tolong di Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi. Kalo kotong sambayang sang Dia, na, Dia pasti kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae, deng tolong sang kotong pas waktu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Orang yang dong su angka ko jadi kapala agama paling tinggi, dia pung tugas musti tolong orang ko urus dong pung hubungan deng Tuhan Allah. Dia musti tarima dong pung persembahan deng dong pung binatang korban, ko sarakan kasi sang Tuhan. Dia ju musti kasi korban binatang ko Tuhan hapus buang orang pung sala-sala dong.<bt>The person whom they elevated/appointed to become the *high priest, his job/responsibility was to help people to manage/look after their relationship with God. He must receive their *offerings (frozen morphology: given things) and their animal sacrifices/animals for sacrifice, to turn over/surrender them to God2. He must also sacrifice animals so God2 would wipe away people's wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** tightened exegesis"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** tightened exegesis</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For every high priest is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For every high priest is chosen from among men and is appointed to represent them in matters related to God, to offer gifts and sacrifices for sins.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang yang dong su angka ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Orang yang dong su angka ko jadi kapala agama paling tinggi, dia pung tugas musti tolong orang ko dong bisa bahubungan deng Tuhan Allah. Dia musti tarima dong pung pemberian deng dong pung binatang korban, ko sarakan kasi sang Tuhan. Dia ju musti kasi korban itu binatang ko Tuhan hapus buang itu orang pung sala-sala dong.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Kalo ada orang yang sonde kanál jalan idop yang batúl, ko, orang yang su serong dari itu jalan, na, itu kapala agama sonde bekin susa sang dong. Dia pung hati bae sang dong, tagal dia ju manusia yang gampang jato sama ke dong.<bt>If there is a person who doesn't know/recognise the true way of life, or (there is) a person who has gone off-track/deviated from that way, na, that *priest doesn't make trouble for them. He is kind/gracious/good to them, because he also is a human who can fall easily just like them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV undertranslated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">CEV undertranslated</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="metriopathew: moderate one's feeling, deal gently,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">metriopathew: moderate one's feeling, deal gently, capacity for calm and gentle judgment, moderation, leniency [make gentle kine] planaw: go astray, be misled, wander about, be deluded, be deceived<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: He is able to deal gently with those who are ignorant and are going astray, since he himself is subject to weakness.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Tagal dia ju manusia yang jato sama ke dong, andia ko itu kapala agama ju musti kasi korban binatang ko Tuhan hapus buang dia pung sala sandiri.<bt>Because he is also a human who falls (morally) like them, that is why that *priest must also make an animal sacrifice so God2 will wipe away his own wrong/s.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This is why he has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This is why he has to make sacrifices for his own sins, as well as for the sins of the people.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 9:7</note><v n="4" />Orang sonde bole angka dia pung diri ko jadi kapala agama paling tinggi. Te cuma Tuhan Allah sa yang ada pung hak ko pili orang bagitu, sama ke dolu-dolu waktu Dia angka sang Musa pung kaka Harun.<bt>A person may not elevate/appoint himself to become *high piest. Cuz (reason) only God is the one who has the rights to choose a person like that, just like long ago when He elevated/appointed Musa's older-sibling Harun.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: No one takes this honor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: No one takes this honor upon himself; he must be called by God, just as Aaron was.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 28:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Bagitu ju deng Kristus. Dia sonde angka Dia pung diri ko jadi kapala agama paling tinggi. Te dolu Tuhan Allah sandiri yang angka sang Dia bilang,<bt>It is the same way with Kristus. He did not appoint Himself to become *highest priest. Cuz (elaboration) long ago, God himself is the one who appointed Him saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lu ni, Beta pung Ana,<bt>“You are My Child.,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ini hari, Beta angka sang Lu ko pegang parenta.&gt;&gt;<bt>today I have appointed you to rule/hold government.” [EXEG: this verse quoting Ps. 2:7 in KM Acts 13:32-33 builds on the context of coronation from Ps. 2:6. Otherwise, outside of adoption or coronation, why would anyone make this non-sensical statement that is incoherent in most English translations? One commentator notes “5:5. Citing again Psalm 2:7 (see comment on Heb 1:5), the writer proves from it that *Christ's royal coronation was God's initiative. In the next verse he links this kingship with the high priesthood.” (from CR) Bruce also links this to “enthronement” here, and at 1:5 says this same quote may “have preserved the text of a coronation liturgy used by the Davidic dynasty”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note expanded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note expanded</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So Christ also did not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So Christ also did not take upon himself the glory of becoming a high priest. But God said to him, "You are my Son; today I have become your Father."</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 2:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Di bagian laen di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi, Dia ju omong bilang,<bt>In a different place in God2's Holy Writings, He also said,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lu jadi kapala agama yang satu model deng Melkisedek dolu-dolu tu,<bt>"You are/will become a *priest of the same type/model/kind as the Melkisedek of long ago, [NOTE to daughter translations: if what was assumed general knowledge to Jews, but not to your crowd needs clarification, try: /yang satu model deng satu orang yang idop dolu-dolu, andia Melkisedek./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note (ALT) added, restructured"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** note (ALT) added, restructured</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;Lu ni jadi kapala agama tarús-tarús"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">&lt;Lu ni jadi kapala agama tarús-tarús sampe salamanya,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma Lu jadi kapala agama sampe salamanya.&gt;&gt;<bt>but (contrary to expectation) you will be a priest forever."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And it says in another"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And it says in another place, "You are a priest forever, of the [priestly] order of Melchizedek."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sama ke kapala agama Melkisedek yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">sama ke kapala agama Melkisedek yang dolu-dolu tu.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Waktu Yesus pung idop di ini dunya su mau abis, Dia sambayang sonde pake barenti deng manangis makarereu, minta tolong sang Tuhan Allah ko kasi kuat sang Dia. Te Dia tau bilang, Tuhan pung kuasa bisa kasi salamat sang Dia. Ju Tuhan Allah dengar sang Yesus, tagal Dia iko batúl-batúl Tuhan pung mau.<bt>When Yesus' life on this earth was about to end, He prayed without ceasing with cries of grief, asking help from God to strengthen Him. Cuz (elaboration) He knew that God2's power/authority could same Him. And, God listened to Yesus, because He truly followed/obeyed God2's will. [EXEG: “save him from death” = strength for deliverance (Miller, ICC).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: During the days of Jesus'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: During the days of Jesus' life on earth, he offered up prayers and petitions with loud cries and tears to the One who could save him from death, and he was heard because of his reverent submission.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 26:36-46, Markus 14:32-42, Lukas 22:39-46</note><v n="8" />Te Yesus tu, Tuhan Allah pung Ana. Biar bagitu ju, ma Dia musti dapa sangsara, ko Dia balajar iko Tuhan pung mau.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) that Yesus is/was God's Child. Even that being the case, nevertheless He also had to experience difficulty/suffering, so He could learn to follow/obey God2's will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Although he was a son,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Although he was a son, he learned obedience from what he suffered.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ais Dia memang bekin iko batúl-batúl Tuhan pung mau samua. Andia ko sakarang Dia su jadi Pohon Salamat kasi samua orang yang parcaya sang Dia, ko dong bisa idop tarús-tarús deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>So He really did truly follow/obey all of God2's will. That is why now He has become the Tree/Source of Salvation for all people who believe in Him, so they can live continually with God. [EXEG: “being made perfect/fully equipped/complete”. Ideas from Gk /teleos/ in the range of “completely, perfectly, fully” are particularly hard to reflect well in these lgs. We usually wind up having to be a bit more generic in reflecting the concept. Being a Malay-based creole, Kupang can sometimes get away with /sampurna/ or /langkáp/, but many speakers also reject those as Indonesian, and not Kupang. Here the reduplicated /batúl-batúl/ is what carries/emphasizes the point that this is “truly” or “fully” (lit. truly-truly) obeying the will of God. It's undertranslated, but it's there. Some daughter translations may be able to do better.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="I (CEG) think Pohon here works"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">I (CEG) think Pohon here works for Bhs. Daera, but not for KM; should it be Akar? Jawab UNS bilang "Pohon"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Being made perfect, he became"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Being made perfect, he became the source of eternal salvation fo all who obey him.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Te Tuhan su angka sang Yesus jadi kapala agama, yang satu model deng kapala agama Melkisedek dolu-dolu.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2 has already appointed Yesus to be *priest, who is the same model/type/kind as the priest Melkisedek from long ago.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And was designated by God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And was designated by God to be high priest, just like Melchizedek.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang angka buang bosong pung parcaya sang Kristus<bt>Don't throw away your belief in Kristus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Masi ada banya hal yang beta mau omong so'al Kristus deng Melkisedek, ma beta susa kasi jalás itu hal dong, tagal bosong masi sama ke ana kici bodo yang balóm bisa mangarti deng batúl.<bt>There are still many things which I want to say about Kristus and Melkisedek, but it is difficult for me to clarify those things, because you-pl are still like ignorant/unskilled small children who are not yet able to fully understand. [EXEG: hard of hearing = immature (Miller)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We have much to say"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We have much to say about this, but it is hard to explain because you have become [slow to learn / dull of hearing].</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Padahal bosong ni su lama parcaya. Iko dia pung batúl, bosong su musti jadi guru, ko bisa ajar orang laen. Ma tau-tau te bosong masi sama ke ana mea yang balóm bisa makan, te baru bisa minum susu sa. Bosong masi parlú orang ko ajar sang bosong hal-hal dasar dari Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi.<bt>Whereas in fact, you have already believed for a long time. What should be the case, is that you-pl should already be teachers, so you could teach other people. But contrary to what one would expect, you are still like infants (red children) who are not yet able to eat, cuz you're barely able to just drink milk. You still need people to teach you basic things/issues from the *Scriptures.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="choosing here to use bodo in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">choosing here to use bodo in the sense of unskilled - (which is often said of babies) the opposite of which is pintar - skilled</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For by this time you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For by this time you ought to be teachers, but you need someone to teach you the beginning truths of God's Word all over again. You need milk, not solid food!</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Beta bisa banding sang bosong deng ana mea bagitu, tagal bosong balóm mangarti batúl ajaran dasar so'al Kristus, ko bosong bisa idop lurus.<bt>I can compare you to infants like that, because you are still ignorant/unskilled, and do not yet truly understand the basic teachings about Kristus so that you can live straight/righteous.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Everyone who uses milk, being"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Everyone who uses milk, being still an infant, is not acquainted with the teaching about righteousness.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:12-13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 3:2</note><v n="14" />Ma kalo ana mea su bésar datang, dia sonde minum susu lai, ma dia makan makanan yang karás. Itu sama ke orang yang su balajar sampe mangarti batúl Tuhan pung ajaran, ko biar dia tau mana yang bae, deng mana yang jahat dong.<bt>But if/when an infant grows up, he doesn't drink milk anymore but eat solid food. That is like a person who has learned/studied to the point that s/he truly understands God2's teachings so that s/he knows which (of choices) is/are good, and which is/are evil.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But solid food is for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But solid food is for the [mature / grown up], who by constant use have trained themselves to distinguish good from evil.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Jadi bosong musti balajar ajaran yang lebe dalam, tagal bosong su balajar cukup lama ajaran dasar dong so'al Kristus. Andia ko sakarang, su sonde usa balajar ulang-ulang ajaran dasar so'al orang musti kasi tenga dong pung sala-sala dong; ajaran so'al orang parcaya sang Tuhan Allah;<bt>So (consequently), you-pl must learn/study the lessons/teachings in greater depth, because you have been learning for sufficient time the basic teachings about Kristus. That is why now, you should not need to study over and over the basic teachings about people having to leave behind/abandon their wrongs; teachings about people believing in God;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, let us leave the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, let us leave the elementary teachings about Christ and go on to maturity. Let us not lay again the foundation of repentance from acts that lead to death, and of faith in God,</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />ajaran so'al sarani; ajaran so'al taro tangan ko orang tarima Tuhan pung Roh Barisi; ajaran so'al Tuhan Allah nanti kasi idop kambali orang mati; deng ajaran so'al orang nanti mangada sang Tuhan, ko tarima Dia pung putusan bilang, sapa yang bole idop tarús deng Dia, deng sapa yang sonde.<bt>teachings about *baptism; teachings about placing hands to receive God2's Holy Spirit; teachings about God later causing dead people to live; and teachings about people later standing before God2 to receive His decision/judgement about who may live continually with Him, and who not. [EXEG: HS has support from Ex.Summ, and Miller, but may be a bit narrow.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nt mua tangan = idiom for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">nt mua tangan = idiom for ordain, officially install</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: instruction about baptisms, the laying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: instruction about baptisms, the laying on of hands, the resurrection of the dead, and eternal judgment.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ma kalo Tuhan kasi isin, na, mari kotong nae kalás sa. Te beta mau ajar hal yang lebe dalam.<bt>But if/when God2 give permission/allows it, na, let's go up to the next class. Cuz (elaboration) I want to teach things that are deeper. [EXEG: NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And this we will do,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And this we will do, if God permits.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4-6" />Padahal, ada orang yang su mangarti Kristus pung ajaran, deng dong su rasa Tuhan Allah pung hati bae, sampe Dia kirim datang Dia pung Roh yang Barisi kasi sang dong. Dong su tau Tuhan pung Kata-kata, deng dong su rasa Dia pung kuasa yang Dia nanti pake kalo dunya su kiamat. Biar bagitu ju, ma dong su angka buang dong pung parcaya, deng su bale balakang ko kasi tenga sang Kristus. Tagal itu, sonde mungkin ada jalan ko dong bisa kambali minta ampon, ais idop babae deng Tuhan Allah lai. Te kalo orang sonde mau tobat bagitu, itu sama ke dong sandiri yang paku bekin mati ulang Tuhan pung Ana di kayu palang, ais dong olok-olok sang Dia di orang banya dong pung muka.<bt>Whereas in fact, there are people who already understand Kristus' teachings, and they have already felt/experienced God's goodness/grace/ kindness/ generosity, to the point that He sent His Holy Spirit to them. They already know God2's Words/Sayings, and they have already felt/experienced His power/authority with His will later use when the world ends. But even that being the case, they have thrown away/gotten rid of their beliefs, and have turned their backs to abandon Kristus. Because of that, it is not likely/possible that there is a way for them to come back and ask forgiveness (focus on social action), and then live right.relationship with God anymore. Cuz (elaboration) if a person doesn't want to repent like that, that is like they themselves are the ones who nail to death again God2's Child on the *cross, and then they mocked/ridiculed Him before many people. [EXEG: NLT, CEV; note re-crucify.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="light and truth? OK in doublet."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">light and truth? OK in doublet. LITERALLY: It is impossible for those who have once been enlightened, who have tasted the heavenly gift, who have shared in the Holy Spirit,<span class="Italic">(4) </span>LITERALLY: who have tasted the goodness of the word of God and the powers of the coming age, LITERALLY: if they fall away, to be brought back to repentance, because on their own account they are crucifying the Son of God all over again, and subjecting him to public disgrace.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Orang macam bagitu, sama ke tana yang kasi kaluar hasil yang sonde bae. Padahal kalo ujan su datang, tana yang bae bisa kasi kaluar hasil yang ada pung guna kasi orang tani. Ais Tuhan Allah kasi turun berkat, ko bekin itu tana pung hasil batamba banya.<bt>People of that sort, are like land that produces/yields produce which isn't good. When in fact, when the rain comes, good land can yield produce that is useful for the farmer. Then God sends down blessings, to make that land's produce increase greatly. [EXEG: explicitly comparing those who apostate with bad land -- example from Kankaney BT; ES (Meyer, Miller p.174) = this is an analogy contrasting opposite results. the land is the same land.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Land that drinks in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Land that drinks in the rain often falling on it, and that produces a crop useful to those for whom it is cultivated, receives the blessing of God.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ma itu orang yang bale balakang sang Kristus, sama ke tana yang kasi kaluar duri sa. Deng itu duri dong sonde ada pung guna apa-apa. Sonde lama ju, Tuhan Allah datang ko kasi jato hukum di itu tana. Ais Dia bakar buang itu hasil yang sonde ada pung guna apa-apa.<bt>But that person who turns his back on Kristus, is like land that just yields thorns. And those thorns have no use whatsoever. In a short time, God will come to make punishment fall on that land. Then He will burn off that produce which has no use whatsoever. [EXEG: culture clash: in this region burning land makes it fertile and ‘blessed, not cursed’, so burn ‘the useless products’ of the bad land. (Deibler).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But land that produces thorns"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But land that produces thorns and thistles is worthless, and is in danger of being cursed. In the end it will be burned.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sonde lama ju, Tuhan Allah datang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Sonde lama ju, Tuhan Allah datang ko kasi jato hukum di itu tana.</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 3:17-18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Sodara sayang dong! Biar beta omong sadiki karás bagitu, ma beta ju tau bilang, bosong sonde bale balakang sang Kristus. Te bosong su parcaya sang Dia, deng bosong pung idop ju ada hasil yang bae.<bt>Dear siblings! Even though I am speaking a little harshly like that, nevertheless I also know that you have not turned your backs on Kristus. Cuz (elaboration) you-pl have believed in Him, and your lives also have good yield/produce.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Dear friends, even though we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Dear friends, even though we speak like this, we are confident of better things in your case--things that accompany salvation.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Jadi inga te Tuhan Allah pung hati lurus, deng Dia sonde lupa bosong pung karingat. Te bosong su karjá karás ko tolong Dia pung orang, deng sayang sang dong. Dari dolu, memang bosong su kasi jalan Dia pung karjá. Deng bosong masi ada bekin bagitu.<bt>So (consequently), remember God's straight/right/ just liver, and He doesn't forget your sweat/efforts. Cuz (elaboration) you-pl have worked hard to help His people, and love them. From long ago, you really have carried out His work. And you are still doing that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: God is not unjust; he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: God is not unjust; he will not forget your work, and the love you have shown him as you have helped his people, and continue to help them.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ma sakarang, beta mau ko bosong samua karjá lebe karás lai, ko bekin iko tarús bagitu sampe abis. Deng bagitu, bosong nanti tarima samua hal bae yang bosong ada baharap dari Tuhan Allah.<bt>But now, I want you to work even harder, to keep doing that until the end/it is finished. In that way, you will later receive every good thing that you are hoping for from God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We want each of you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We want each of you to show this same diligence to the very end, in order to make your hope sure.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Asal bosong jang jadi pamalas! Bosong musti conto orang dong yang su lama parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Te dong baharap tarús-tarús sang Dia, sampe dong tarima ame apa yang Dia su janji.<bt>As long as you don't become lazy! You-pl must example (transitive verb) people who have believed in God for a long time. Cuz (elaboration) they keep hoping/trusting in Him, until they have received what He has already promised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="noothroi: contrasts with spoudeen in 11,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">noothroi: contrasts with spoudeen in 11, meaning eagerness LITERALLY: We do not want you to become lazy, but to imitate those who through faith and patience inherit what has been promised.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13-16" />Conto ke kotong pung ba'i Abraham. Dolu-dolu Tuhan Allah ika janji deng dia pake sumpa. Kalo manusia angka sumpa, dia biasa pake Tuhan Allah pung nama, ko Tuhan jadi dia pung saksi, tagal Tuhan tu, lebe dari dia. Deng kalo ada parkara, samua orang tau bilang, itu orang pung omong tu, batúl, tagal dia su sumpa pake Tuhan Allah pung nama na. Itu memang manusia pung cara. Ma waktu Tuhan Allah bekin sumpa deng ba'i Abraham, Dia pake Dia pung nama sandiri, tagal sonde ada yang lebe dari Dia. Dia janji bilang,<bt>For example, our-inc Gf Abraham. Long ago, God bound a promise with him using an oath. When a human takes an oath, s/he usually used God's name, to God2 is his witness, because God2 is more than him. And if there is a dispute, everyone knows that what that person is saying is true, because s/he has sworn an oath using God's name. That is the way of humans. But when God made an oath with Gf Abraham, He used His own name, because there is none who is greater than Him. He promised that,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When God made his promise"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When God made his promise to Abraham, since there was no one greater fo him to swear by, he swore by himself,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta nanti kasi berkat bam-banya,<bt>"I will give many blessings,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sang lu deng lu pung turunan.<bt>to you-sg and your descendants.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti dong tamba banya,<bt>They will later increase (in number),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sampe sonde ada orang yang bisa itong ame sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>to the point that there is nobody who can (successfully) count them."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: saying, &quot;I will surely bless"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: saying, "I will surely bless you, and give you many descendants."</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:13-16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 22:16-17</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tuhan Allah janji abis bagitu, ju ba'i Abraham parcaya deng baharap tarús sang Dia, biar lama-lama baru dia tarima ame apa yang Tuhan su janji.<bt>[When] God had finished promising like that, then Gf Abraham believed and kept hoping/trusting in Him, even if/though it would be a long time before he received what God2 had promised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And so after waiting patiently,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And so after waiting patiently, Abraham received what was promised. LITERALLY: People swear by someone greater than themselves, and the oath confirms what is said and puts an end to all argument.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Deng bagitu, kotong su tau kalo Tuhan bekin janji deng Dia pung orang, Dia ika itu janji pake sumpa, ko jamin bilang, apa yang Dia janji, memang batúl deng sonde oba.<bt>In that way, we-inc know if God2 makes a promise with His people, He binds that promise using an oath, to guarantee that, what He promises, is really true and doesn't change.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because God wanted to make"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because God wanted to make the unchanging nature of his purpose very clear to the heirs of what was promised, he confirmed it with an oath.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Te ada dua hal yang sonde bisa baroba. Yang partama, andia Tuhan pung janji. Deng yang kadua, andia Dia pung sumpa yang Dia pake ko jamin itu janji. Jadi kalo Tuhan su janji satu hal, pasti Dia bekin iko, tagal Dia sonde mungkin omong kosong. Andia ko kotong sonde usa kawatir deng Dia pung janji.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) there are two things that cannot change. The first, is God's promise. And the second, is His oath which He used to guarantee that promise. So (consequently), when God2 has promised somethings, He will certainly do according to it, because it is not likely/possible that (He) lies/decieves/empty talk/BS. That is why we-inc do not need to worry about His promise.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="running away to God: provides a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">running away to God: provides a positive emphasis. LITERALLY: God did this so that, by two unchangeable things in which it is impossible for God to lie, we who have fled to take hold of the hope offered to us, may be greatly encouraged.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Kotong su lari pi cari salamat di Dia, jadi sakarang kotong tenga tunggu ko baharap tarús sang Dia sa.<bt>We have run/rushed to Him to find salvation, so now we only need to keep waiting and keep hoping/trusting in Him.</bt><v n="19" />Deng bagitu, kotong pung hati su aman, sama ke satu parahu yang su kaluar dari galombang, ko sandar di tampa balabu. Te kotong baharap sang Yesus Kristus yang su jadi kotong pung kapala agama paling tinggi. Dolu, pas deng orang Yahudi dong pung hari bae, kapala agama paling tinggi maso lewat kaen gorden yang pele Kamar yang Paling Barisi, ko mangada sang Tuhan Allah di situ.<bt>In that way, our livers are safe/secure, like a boat which has come out of the waves, to come to rest at an anchorage. Cuz (elaboration) we hope in YK who has become our*highest priest. Formerly, on the Jewish holiday/feast day, the *high priest entered via/past the cloth curtain blocking off (as door curtain) the Most Holy Room, to front up to God there. [EXEG: the anchor skewed focus for MTTs &amp; UNSs; throw out an anchor at sea during a storm and the boat is still tossed about. Build picture of a boat finding shelter FROM the storm in a protected anchorage. UNSs]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We have this hope as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We have this hope as an anchor for the soul, firm and secure. It enters the inner sanctuary behind the curtain,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dolu, pas deng orang Yahudi dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Dolu, pas deng orang Yahudi dong pung hari bae, kapala agama paling tinggi buka kaen gorden di tampa sambayang, ko maso mangada sang Tuhan Allah di Dia pung Kamar yang Paling Barisi.</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 16:2</note><v n="20" />Ma sakarang Yesus su maso lebe dolo ko buka jalan kasi kotong. Te Dia ju kapala agama paling tinggi, yang satu model ke Melkisedek dolu-dolu tu. Ma Yesus lebe hebat dari kapala agama model lama, tagal Dia sonde parná barenti kasi jalan Dia pung karjá.<bt>But now Yesus has entered ahead (of us) to open a way. Cuz (elaboration) He is also *high priest, who is of the same type/model as that Melkisedek from long ago. But He is greater/more impressive than the old model head priest/s, because He never ceased/s to carry out His work.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="1st sent awkward. /Ma kotong sakarang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">1st sent awkward. /Ma kotong sakarang su ada Yesus/ &gt; /Ma sakarang kotong su ada Yesus/ or delete 1st /kotong/</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: where Jesus, who went before"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: where Jesus, who went before us, has entered on our behalf. He has become a high priest forever, after the priestly order of Melchizedek.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma sakarang Yesus su pi lebe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Ma sakarang Yesus su pi lebe dolo ko buka jalan kasi kotong. Te Dia ju kapala agama. Ma Dia lebe hebat dari kapala agama model lama, tagal Dia sonde parná barenti kasi jalan Dia pung karjá, sama ke Melkisedek yang dolu-dolu tu.</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:4</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Melkisedek tu, satu kapala agama yang lebe tinggi dari kapala agama Lewi deng dia pung turunan dong<bt>Melkisedek is a priest who is higher than the priest Lewi and his descendants</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1-3" />Dolu-dolu, Melkisedek jadi raja kota Salem. Dia ju kapala agama kasi orang yang sémba sang Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi. Dia pung nama pung arti, andia &lt;&lt;Raja Hati Lurus&gt;&gt;. Deng Raja Salem pung arti, &lt;&lt;Raja Dame&gt;&gt;. Sonde ada yang tau Melkisedek ni pung asal-usul. Sonde ada yang tau dia pung bapa, dia pung mama, deng dia pung nene-moyang dong. Sonde ada yang tau dia pung lahir, deng dia pung mati. Orang cuma tau dia tu, raja kota Salem, deng kapala agama kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Ma dia ju sama ke Tuhan Allah pung Ana, tagal dia ju kapala agama yang kasi jalan tarús-tarús dia pung karjá.<bt>Long ago, Melkisedek was the raja of the city of Salem. He was also *priest for people who worshipped the Highest God. His name means, "Raja with the Straight Liver". And the Raja Salem means "Raja of Peace". There is nobody who knows Melkisedek's origins. There is nobody who knows his father, his mother, and his ancestors. There is nobody who knows his birth, and his death. People only know that he was raja of the city of Salem, and *priest to/for God. But he is also like God's Child, because he is also a priest who continually carries out his work. [DISCOURSE: reorganized for background-foreground issues.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="[DISCUSS UNS suggestion needing clarification for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">[DISCUSS UNS suggestion needing clarification for /kapala agama kasi Tuhan Allah/. &gt; /kasi sang/? /kasi pi/? Problem with suggestion to change to /dari Tuhan/ is it is clearly mesolectal.]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Satu kali, ada barapa raja yang datang deng dong pung tantara dong, ko rampas ame barang dari ba'i Abraham pung tamán-tamán. Ais itu, ba'i Abraham pi baparáng sama-sama deng dia pung tamán dong, sampe dong bekin kala itu raja dong. Ju ba'i Abraham dong ame kambali itu barang samua. Waktu ba'i Abraham su jalan pulang, ju Melkisedek kaluar dari kota Salem ko pi sambut sang dia. Ais dia omong kasi berkat sang ba'i Abraham bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi kasi berkat sang lu.&gt;&gt; Ais itu ju, ba'i Abraham bagi kasi sang Melkisedek satu bagian dari sapulu bagian, dari samua barang yang dia su rampas ame kambali. Dia kasi bagitu, tagal Melkisedek tu, kapala agama dari Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi.<bt>One time, there were several rajas who came with their soldiers, to snatch away things from Gf Abraham's friends. Then Gf Abraham also went warring together with his friends, to the point that they caused those rajas to be defeated. Then Gf Abraham (collective) took back all those things. When Gf Abraham had returned home, then Melkisedek came out from the city of Salem to greet him. And he spoke giving blessing to Gf Abraham saying, "May the Highest God, give blessing to you-sg." After that, Gf Abraham divided out to Melkisedek one from ten parts [NOTE: I think this is mesolectal. For use as Front Translation they probably need /satu bagian dari sapulu bagian/ "one part from ten parts" as we have used elsewhere], from all the things which he had retrieved. He gave like that, because Melkisedek was priest of the Highest God.]</bt><note reference="7:1-3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 14:17-20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Naa, pikir bae-bae so'al Melkisedek ni! Ba'i Abraham bagi kasi sang dia satu bagian dari sapulu bagian, dari samua barang yang paling bae, yang dia su ame kambali. Jadi su jalás, Melkisedek tu, orang bésar.<bt>Naa, think carefully about this Melkisedek! Gf Abraham divided out to him one of ten parts, from all the best things, which he had taken back. So it is clear, that Melkisedek was an important person. [NOTE to daughter translations: be careful about trying to force the “even Abraham” since in these lgs it would most likely contrast with Melchisedek, which is not the point of the Gk here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Just think how great he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Just think how great he was: Even the patriarch Abraham gave him a tenth of the [plunder / spoils]!</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Padahal itu waktu, Tuhan Allah balóm angka orang ko jadi kapala agama. Sampe ba'i Abraham pung cece Lewi ada, baru Tuhan Allah angka sang dia deng dia pung turunan dong, ko jadi kapala agama kasi ba'i Abraham pung turunan samua. Ais itu di ba'i Musa pung jaman, Tuhan Allah ju kasi turun atoran bilang, orang dari suku Lewi ada hak tarima satu bagian dari sapulu bagian hasil dari dong pung sodara suku laen dong di Isra'el.<bt>When in fact, at that time, God had not yet elevated/appointed people to be *priest. Until Gf Abraham's great-grandchild Lewi, only-then did God appoint him and his descendants to be *priests to all of Gf Abraham's descendants. After that in gfather Musa's time, God also sent down/established a regulation that people from the tribe of Lewi have the rights to receive one of ten parts of produce/yield from their siblings of other tribes in Isra'el. [NOTE to daughter translations: If you have a term for “great grandchild (minus 4 generations)” CHECK to see that it is actually known by the younger generations.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now the law requires the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now the law requires the descendants of Levi who become priests to collect a tenth from the people--that is their brothers--even though their brothers are descended from Abraham.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 18:21</note><v n="6" />Ma Melkisedek tu, bukan Lewi pung turunan. Biar bagitu ju, ma ba'i Abraham bagi kasi sang dia satu bagian dari sapulu bagian, tagal dia anggap Melkisedek tu, orang hebat. Itu waktu, ba'i Abraham su tarima janji dari Tuhan Allah ko kasi berkat sang dia. Biar bagitu, ma Melkisedek ju omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi, kasi berkat sang lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>But that Melkisedek, was not Lewi's descendant. Even that being the case, nevertheless Gf Abraham gave him one of ten parts, because he considered Melkisadek to be an amazing/impressive person. At that time, Gf Abraham had already received the promise from God to bless him. Even that being the case, nevertheless Melkisedek also spoke saying, "May the Highest God, give blessings to you-sg."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: [The one without genealogy from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: [The one without genealogy from them / This man, however, did not trace his descent from Levi, yet he] received a tenth from Abraham and blessed him who had the promises.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ini ni, ju bukti bilang, Melkisedek tu, orang bésar. Tagal orang yang omong kasi berkat, pasti lebe bésar dari orang yang tarima berkat.<bt>This is also proof that Melkisedek was an important person. Because the person who speaks giving blessing is surely more important/greater than the person who receives the blessing.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And without doubt the lesser"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And without doubt the lesser person is blessed by the greater.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Kapala agama dong samua ada pung hak ko tarima ame satu bagian dari sapulu bagian. Ma tagal dong cuma manusia biasa, lama-lama ju dong mati. Kapala agama Melkisedek ju tarima satu bagian dari sapulu bagian. Ma dia idop tarús, tagal Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi sonde kasi tau bilang, dia mati.<bt>All *priests have the right to receive one of ten parts. But because they are only normal humans, eventually they also die. The priest Melkisedek also received one of ten parts. But he lived continually, because God2's Holy Writings do not tell that he died.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In the one case, the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In the one case, the tenth is collected by men who die; but in the other case, by him who is declared to be living.</Message></Annotation><v n="9-10" />Tagal ba'i Abraham bagi kasi sang Melkisedek satu bagian dari sapulu bagian dari itu barang, na, orang bisa pikir coba bilang, dia ju tanggong dia pung turunan yang balóm lahir dong. Deng bagitu, kotong bisa anggap dia su bayar memang dia pung cece Lewi pung satu bagian dari sapulu bagian.<bt>Because Gf Abraham divided out to Melkisedek one part from ten parts (= *tithe) from those things, na, one of ten parts from his things, someone might think that, he also carried/covered costs of his unborn descendants. In that way, we-inc can consider that he already paid beforehand his great-grandson Lewi's *tithe.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: One might even say that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: One might even say that Levi, who collects the tenth, paid the tenth through Abraham. Because when Melchizedek met Abraham, Levi was still in the body of his ancestor.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tagal ba'i Abraham bagi kasi sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Tagal ba'i Abraham bagi kasi sang Melkisedek satu bagian dari sapulu bagian dari dia pung barang tu, kotong bisa putus bagini: waktu ba'i Abraham kasi satu bagian dari sapulu bagian sang Melkisedek, dia su bayar memang dia pung cece Lewi dong pung satu bagian dari sapulu bagian.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:9-10" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang Yahudi anggap orang pung turunan dong pung bibit su ada di nene-moyang dong pung badan.<bt>Yahudi people consider that the seed of a person's descendant are already exisitng in their ancestor's body/s.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong parlú kapala agama model baru, tagal kapala agama model lama sonde mampu hapus buang batúl orang pung sala<bt>We-inc need a new model/type of *priest, because the old model of priest is incapable of truly wiping away a person's wrongs</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Waktu Lewi pung turunan dong jadi kapala agama, Tuhan pili sang ba'i Musa pung kaka Harun, ko jadi kapala agama paling tinggi yang partama. Kapala agama dong pung tugas, andia kasi tunju jalan ko orang bisa idop barisi, deng babae deng Tuhan. Biar dong bekin iko atoran sumua ju, ma kapala agama model ke Harun sonde mampu bekin dong barisi batúl. Andia ko dong parlú kapala agama laen, yang pung model sama ke Melkisedek.<bt>When Lewi's descendants became *priests, God2 chose Gf Musa's older-sibling Harun to become the first *high priest. The priests job/responsibilities were to show the way for people to live clean/holy and be in right relationship with God2. Even if they followed all the regulations, nevertheless a priest of the model/type of Harun was not capable of making them truly clean/holy. That is why they needed a different *priest, whose model/type was like Melkisedek. [EXEG: Miller]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If indeed perfection could have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If indeed perfection could have been attained through the Levitical priesthood (for [on the basis of it / under it] the law was given to the people), why was there still need for another priest to come--one like Melchizedek, not one named after Aaron?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu Lewi pung turunan dong jadi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Waktu Lewi pung turunan dong jadi kapala agama, Tuhan pili sang ba'i Musa pung kaka Harun, ko jadi kapala agama paling tinggi yang partama. Kapala agama dong pung tugas tu, andia tolong orang ko dong sonde ada pung sala lai. Ma biar bagitu ju, dong sonde bisa bekin bagitu, tagal kapala agama model ke Harun sonde mampu tolong sang dong. Andia ko dong parlú kapala agama laen, yang dia pung model sama ke Melkisedek.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Ma kalo kapala agama model baru ganti sang kapala agama model lama, na, atoran lama ju musti kaná ganti.<bt>But if the new type of priest replaces the old type of priest, na, the old regulations must also undergo/experience change/replacement.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For when there is a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For when there is a change of the priesthood, there must also be a change of the law.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Naa, su jalás, kapala agama model baru tu, andia Yesus. Te Dia lahir dari suku laen, bukan dari suku Lewi. Iko ba'i Musa pung atoran, kapala agama model ke Harun, cuma datang dari suku Lewi sa, sonde bole dari suku laen.<bt>Naa, it is already clear, the new type of priest is Yesus. Cuz (elaboration) was born from a different tribe, not the tribe of Lewi. According to Gf Musa's regulations, a *priest of Harun's type could only come from the tribe of Lewi, and may not come from a different tribe.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The one of whom these"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The one of whom these things are said belonged to a different tribe, and no one from that tribe has ever served at the altar.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ma samua orang tau bilang, kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus lahir dari suku Yahuda. Iko ba'i Musa pung atoran, sonde ada kapala agama dari itu suku.<bt>But everyone knows that our-inc Boss, Yesus Kristus, was born from the tribe of Yahuda. According to Gf Musa's regulations, there are no *priests from that tribe.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For it is clear that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For it is clear that our Lord descended from Judah, and in regard to that tribe, Moses said nothing about priests.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ma Tuhan Allah sonde pake lai itu atoran lama, tagal sakarang su ada Yesus, yang jadi kapala agama model baru, model ke Melkisedek.<bt>But God no longer uses those old regulations, because now there is already Yesus, who become a priest of the new model, of the type/model of Melkisedek.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And it is even clearer:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And it is even clearer: another priest like Melchizedek has appeared,</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Te iko ba'i Musa pung atoran, kapala agama model lama dong musti datang dari suku Lewi. Ma Yesus sonde datang dari itu suku. Biar bagitu ju, ma Tuhan Allah angka sang Dia ko jadi kapala agama model baru, tagal Dia ada kuasa ko idop tarús-tarús, deng sonde ada yang bisa bekin ancor sang Dia.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) according to Gf Musa's regulations, *priests of the old type must come from the tribe of Lewi. But Yesus didn't come from that tribe. Even that being the case, nevertheless God elevated/appointed Him to be a *priest of the new type, because He has the power/authority to live forever, and there is nobody who can destroy Him. [NOTE: Second "but" here could be awkward, but both seem necessary for the argument.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: One who has become a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: One who has become a priest, not on the basis of his ancestry, but on the basis of the power of an indestructible life.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Te Tuhan pung Tulisan ada tulis bilang,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2's Writings wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lu jadi kapala agama yang satu model deng Melkisedek dolu-dolu tu,<bt>"You are/will become a *priest of the same type/model/kind as the Melkisedek of long ago,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma Lu jadi kapala agama sampe salamanya.&gt;&gt;<bt>but (contrary to expectation) you will be a priest forever.” [NOTE to daughter translations: match with phrasing in Heb. 5:6]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For it is declared: &quot;You"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For it is declared: "You are a priest forever, just like Melchizedek."</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Dia pung arti bilang, atoran yang lama sonde ada pung kuasa ko tolong orang dong. Andia ko Tuhan Allah su kasi batal itu atoran lama, yang dolu Dia su kasi sang ba'i Musa.<bt>That means, they old regulation do not have the power/authority to help people. That is why God has already cancelled those old regulations, which He had formerly given to Gf Musa.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="atheteesis: legal technical term for when"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">atheteesis: legal technical term for when a formal arrangement is declared invalid or annulled. The verb it is based on also includes the idea of setting something aside or refusing to recognize it. LITERALLY: The former regulation is set aside because it was weak and useless<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Te biar orang idop deng bekin iko itu atoran lama dong, ma dong masi ada pung sala-sala. Andia ko sakarang, Tuhan su buka jalan yang lebe bae, ko biar kotong bisa idop badame deng Dia.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) even if/though a person lives and does according to those old regulations, nevertheless they still have their wrongs. That is why now, God2 has already opened a better way so that we-inc can live at peace/reconciled with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: (for the law made nothing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: (for the law made nothing perfect), and a better hope is introduced, by which we draw near to God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus tu, Kapala Agama yang lebe hebat dari kapala agama model lama dong<bt>Yesus is priest superior to *priests of the old type</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20-21" />Dolu, waktu Tuhan Allah angka Lewi pung turunan dong ko jadi kapala agama, Dia sonde janji, deng sonde angka sumpa apa-apa deng dong. Ma waktu Tuhan Allah angka Yesus jadi kapala agama, Dia janji bilang,<bt>Formerly, when God elevated/appointed Lewi's descendants to be *priests, He did not promise, and did not make/establish any sort of oath with them. But when God appointed Yesus to be *priest, He promised saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In addition, there is also"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In addition, there is also God's vow. There was no such vow when the others were made priests.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta ni, Bos yang hak parenta samua!<bt>"I am Boss/lord/master who has the say-so/ordering rights over everything/one!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta sumpa, Beta sonde akan roba apa yang Beta su janji.<bt>I swear an oath, (that) I will not change what I have promised.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta angka sang Lu jadi kapala agama,<bt>I appoint You-sg to be *priest,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko Lu kasi jalan Lu pung tugas tarús-tarús.&gt;&gt;<bt>so You can carry out Your job/responsibilities continually."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But he [Jesus] became a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But he [Jesus] became a priest with a vow, when God said to him, "The Lord has sworn, and will not change his mind, 'You are a priest forever.'"</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Deng Dia janji bagitu, Tuhan Allah pake Yesus ko jamin kasi kotong bilang, Dia ada mau ika janji yang lebe bae lai deng kotong.<bt>With Him promising like that, God uses/used Yesus to guarantee to us-inc that He is wanting to bind a promise which is even better for us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: [Because of this vow /"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: [Because of this vow / To such an extent], Jesus has become the guarantee of a better covenant.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Dolu kapala agama model lama musti kaná ganti tarús, tagal dong mati. Andia ko musti ada banya kapala agama dong.<bt>Formerly *priests of the old type must be replaced continually, because they die. That is why there needed to be many priests.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now there were many of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now there were many of those priests, since death prevented them from continuing in office.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Ma Yesus tu, satu kapala agama model baru yang idop tarús-tarús, deng Dia ju kasi jalan Dia pung tugas tarús-tarús. Andia ko sonde parlú ada orang yang ganti sang Dia.<bt>But Yesus is a *priest of the new type who lives continually, and He also carries out his job/responsibilities continually. That is why there is no need for someone to replace Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But because Jesus lives forever,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But because Jesus lives forever, he has a permanent priesthood.</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Tagal itu, Yesus bisa kasi salamat sang samua orang yang mau datang di Tuhan Allah lewat Dia. Dia bisa bekin bagitu sampe salamanya. Deng Dia jadi dong pung orang dalam yang salalu mangada sang Tuhan Allah ko tolong sang dong.<bt>Because of that, Yesus is able to save everyone who wants to come to God through/via Him. He is able to do that forever. And He is their insider who always fronts up/stands before God to help them. [EXEG: Ellingsworth]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore he is able to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore he is able to save completely those who come to God through him, because he always lives to intercede for them.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tagal itu, Yesus bisa kasi salamat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Tagal itu, Yesus bisa kasi salamat sang samua orang yang mau datang di Tuhan Allah. Deng Dia bisa sambayang kasi sang dong tarús-tarús.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Yesus tu, kapala agama paling tinggi yang paling cocok deng kotong. Tagal Dia tu, Orang barisi yang sonde ada pung sala apa-apa. Dia sonde sama deng manusia biasa yang cuma tau bekin sala-sala. Te Tuhan Allah su angka tinggi-tinggi sang Dia, lebe dari samua yang ada di bumi deng di sorga.<bt>That Yesus is a *high priest who is the best match for us-inc. Because He is a clean/holy/pure Person who has no wrongs/sins whatsoever. He is not the same as sinful humans He is not the same as normal humans, who only know/able to do wrong." Cuz (elaboration) God has lifted Him up very high (=exalted Him), above everything on earth and in heaven.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Such a high priest meets"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Such a high priest meets our need--one who is holy, blameless, pure [undefiled], set apart [separate] from sinners, exalted above the heavens.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Andia ko Yesus lebe bae dari samua kapala agama model lama. Dolu dong musti kasi korban binatang tiap hari, ko Tuhan Allah hapus buang dong pung sala-sala sandiri. Ais itu, baru dong bekin korban kasi orang dong. Ma Yesus sonde parlú bekin ulang-ulang bagitu, tagal Dia su sarakan Dia pung diri satu kali sa ko jadi korban. Itu su cukup ko Tuhan hapus buang samua orang pung sala-sala dong.<bt>That is why Yesus is better than all *priests of the old type. Formerly they had to sacrifice animals every day, so God would wipe away their own wrongs. After that, only-then could they do sacrifices for the people. But Yesus does not need to do that repeatedly, because He has already surrendered/turned over Himself just one time to be a sacrifice. That is enough for God2 to wipe away everybody's sins. [EXEG: sacrifices = animal sacrifices (Deibler)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Unlike the other high priests,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Unlike the other high priests, he does not need to offer sacrifices day after day, first for his own sins, and then for the sins of the people. He made a sacrifice once for all when he offered himself.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 9:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Iko ba'i Musa pung atoran, dong angka manusia biasa ko jadi kapala agama. Ma dong masi ada pung sala-sala. Andia ko Tuhan Allah bekin janji baru bilang, Dia mau angka Dia pung Ana ko jadi kapala agama paling tinggi. Te Dia pung Ana ni, iko tarús-tarús Dia pung mau.<bt>According to Gf Musa's regulations, they appointed normal humans to be *priests. But they still have the mistakes (wrong doings). That is why God made a new promise that He was going to appoint His Child to be *high priest. Cuz (elaboration) His Child, always followed/obeyed His will. [EXEG: There is a real clash of signals in this verse. At a high level, Gk is talking about replacing the old order/covenant (associated with Moses), with a new order/covenant (associated with His Son, the High Priest) “who has been made perfect forever” focusing on something extending through time. From an RL perspective, this new order/covenant and this on-going thing both evoke “promise”, not “oath”. “Oath” is only a momentary utterance that can be used to establish a promise, but the on-going substance is a “promise”, not an “oath”. So for RL reasons, we shift to “promise” like CEV and HCE do.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the law appoints men"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the law appoints men who are weak as high priests; but the vow, which came after the law, appointed the Son, who has been made perfect forever.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah pake Kristus ko ika janji baru yang lebe bae dari janji lama<bt>God used Kristus to bind a new promise which is better than the old promise</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1" />Jadi beta pung omong yang pantíng bagini: sakarang kotong su ada kapala agama paling tinggi yang lebe hebat dari yang dolu-dolu dong. Dia tu, andia Yesus. Dia dudu pegang parenta di sorga, di Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi pung sablá kanan.<bt>So (consequently), the important thing I have to say is this: now we-inc already have a * high priest who is greater/more impressive that those from long ago. He is Yesus. He is sitting holding rule/governing in heaven, at the right side of the Highest God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The point of what we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The point of what we are saying is this: We do have such a high priest, who sat down at the right hand of the throne of the Majesty in heaven,</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:1</note><v n="2" />Deng Dia kasi jalan Dia pung tugas di tampa sambayang yang asli. Itu tampa tu, Tuhan Allah sandiri yang bekin, bukan manusia yang bekin.<bt>And He is carrying out His job/responsibilities in the original place of prayer/worship. That place, God himself is the one who made it, not humans who made it. [EXEG: Ex. Summ. “the real thing, the original, not a copy”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** removed God from 1st sentence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** removed God from 1st sentence to avoid misread of God needing a place to pray</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="skeenee: for the heavenly &quot;tent&quot;, which"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">skeenee: for the heavenly "tent", which is hardly what you would use for a weekend family campout at the beach, the generic "place" seems more appropriate, since portability is not a factor. For the earthly one, portability was necessary. LITERALLY: and who serves in the sanctuary, the true tabernacle set up by the Lord, not by man.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Kapala agama paling tinggi biasa bawa pemberian deng korban ko kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Andia ko Yesus ju musti bawa korban.<bt>the *highest priest normally brings offerings and sacrifices to give to God. That is why Yesus must also bring sacrifice.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gifs &gt; presents? LITERALLY: Every high"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">gifs &gt; presents? LITERALLY: Every high priest is appointed to offer both gifts and sacrifices, and so it was necessary for this one also to have something to offer.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ma Yesus sonde kasi jalan Dia pung tugas di bumi. Tagal di bumi su ada kapala agama yang kasi pemberian deng korban sang Tuhan Allah, iko ba'i Musa pung atoran.<bt>But Yesus does not carry out His job/responsibilities on earth. Because on earth there are already *priests who give offerings and sacrifices to God, according to Gf Musa's regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If he were on earth,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If he were on earth, he would not be a priest, for there are already men who offer the gifts prescribed by the law.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Dong kasi jalan dong pung tugas di Tenda Sambayang, yang dia pung model iko tampa sambayang asli di sorga. Te waktu ba'i Musa mau bekin itu Tenda, Tuhan Allah kasi inga sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga bae-bae! Lu musti bekin batúl-batúl iko model yang Beta su kasi tunju sang lu di atas itu gunung!&gt;&gt;<bt>They carry out their job/responsibilities in the Tent of Prayer, whose model/type was according to the asli place of prayer/worship in heaven. Cuz (elaboration) Gf Musa wanted to make that Tent, God reminded/warned him saying, "Remember well! You-sg must truly make it according to the model which I have shown you on that mountain!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="skeenee: &quot;place&quot; generic as before LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">skeenee: "place" generic as before LITERALLY: They serve at a sanctuary that is a copy and shadow of what is in heaven. That is why Moses was warned when he was about to build the tabernacle, "See to it that you make everything according to the pattern shown you on the mountain."<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="8:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 25:40</note><v n="6" />Ma Yesus pung tugas jao lebe hebat dari kapala agama model lama dong. Te sakarang Tuhan Allah su ika janji yang lebe bae, tagal Dia ju pake Yesus jadi jambatan ko manusia bisa badame deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>But Yesus' job/responsibilities are far more impressive/greater than those of the old model of *priest. Cuz (elaboration) now God has already bound a better promise, because He also used Yesus to be a bridge/go-between so humans could be able to be at peace/reconciled with God. [EXEG: Gk has different lexemes for ‘promise’ and ‘covenant’, and English has the luxury of theologians ascribing a difference between a mere ‘promise’ and a ‘covenant’, even to the point of developing a “covenant theology”. But outside theological circles in English there wouldn't be much difference to your average younger speaker except that ‘covenant’ sounds archaic, if it's even known by the younger generation. In the lgs in the Timor region, we can up a promise a bit in degree of solemnity, formality, and duration, in the inceptive phase by “binding a promise” rather than merely “promising”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But the priestly ministry Jesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But the priestly ministry Jesus has [received / obtained] is as superior to theirs as the covenant of which he is mediator is superior to the old one, and is founded on better promises.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Dolu-dolu Dia ika janji deng ba'i Musa waktu Dia kasi turun itu atoran dong. Biar bagitu ju, ma manusia sonde bisa idop barisi batúl iko itu atoran. Tagal itu, dong sonde bisa babae deng Tuhan Allah. Andia ko sakarang, parlú ada janji yang lebe bae lai.<bt>Long ago, He bound a promise with Gf Musa when He handed down/established those regulations. Even that being the case, nevertheless humans are not able to live truly clean/holy/pure according to those regulations. Because of that, they are not able to be in reciprocally right relationship with God. That is why now there is a need for an even better promise.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="an: note &quot;neva get&quot; instead of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">an: note "neva get" instead of "neva have" - if no problem had ever developed, rather than if there had been no problem LITERALLY: For it there had been nothing wrong with the first covenant, there would have been no need for another.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te dolu Tuhan Allah togor sang Dia pung orang, tagal dong su langgar ulang-ulang Dia pung atoran lama. Waktu Dia su sonde tahan lai, ju Dia mara, ais Dia kasi tau bilang,<bt>Cuz formerly God scolded His people, because they had repeatedly transgressed His old regulations. When He could no longer stand it/restrain, He was angry, and so He said,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dengar bae-bae, te Beta ni, yang hak parenta samua!<bt>"Listen carefully, cuz I am the one with say-so/ordering rights over everything/one!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Pasti nanti Beta ika janji baru<bt>Surely I will (later) bind a new promise</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sonde lama lai te Beta ika"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Sonde lama lai te Beta ika janji baru</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng bangsa Isra'el,<bt>with the ethnic nation of Isra'el,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng suku Yahuda.<bt>and the tribe of Yahuda.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But God found fault with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But God found fault with the people, and said, "The time is coming," says the Lord, "when I will make a new covenant with the house of Israel, and with the house of Judah.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="9" />Itu janji yang nanti Beta ika deng dong tu,<bt>That promise that I will later bind with them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sonde sama deng itu janji yang dolu Beta su ika<bt>is not the same as that promise which I previously bound</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng dong pung nene-moyang dong.<bt>with their ancestors.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te dolu Beta pegang dong pung tangan,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) previously I held their hand,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko antar bawa sang dong kaluar dari tana Masir.<bt>to lead them out from the land of Masir.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma dong sonde bekin iko<bt>But they did not do according to</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">apa yang dong su janji deng Beta.<bt>what they had promised Me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Andia ko Beta su sonde mau toe sang dong lai.<bt>That is why I already do not want to pay attention/care about them anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: It will not be like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: It will not be like the covenant I made with their forefathers, when I took them by the hand to lead them out of Egypt, because they did not remain faithful to my covenant, and I turned away from them,' says the Lord."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />Itu janji yang Beta nanti ika deng bangsa Isra'el,<bt>That promise that I will bind with the nation/tribe of Isra'el,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dia pung isi bagini:<bt>its content is like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti Beta taro Beta pung atoran di dong pung dalam pikiran.<bt>"I will place My regulations in their inner thoughts. [EXEG: Upon review, I can't find good justification for the ov shift to 2p. So 10-12 restored to 3p to better reflect the Gk and the audience of the passage.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) pronouns changed in 10-12,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) pronouns changed in 10-12, note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nanti Beta tulis Beta pung parenta di dong pung dalam hati.<bt>I will write My commands in their inner livers.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ais Beta jadi dong pung Tuhan,<bt>Then I will be their God2,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng dong jadi Beta pung orang.<bt>and they will be My people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This is the covenant I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This is the covenant I will make with the house of Israel after that time, says the Lord. I will put my laws in their minds and write them on their hearts. I will be their God, and they will be my people.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Nanti dong sonde parlú ajar lai sang dong pung tamán,<bt>They will not need to teach their friends anymore,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng dong pung sodara bilang,<bt>and their siblings will say,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">&lt;Bosong musti kanál sang Tuhan!&gt;<bt>'You must know (personal acquaintence, not head knowledge) God2!'</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te dong samua kanál bae deng Beta,<bt>cuz (elaboration) all of you know Me well, [EXEG: OV: biar ko to te to better reflect Gk /hoti/ without clashing with vs. 12]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">mulai dari yang paling kici sampe yang paling bésar.<bt>beginning from the smallest/youngest/most insignificant to the largest/oldest/most important.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: No longer will a man"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: No longer will a man teach his neighbor, or a man his brother, saying, 'Know the Lord,' because they will all know me, from the least of them to the greatest.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="12" />Tagal Beta mau kasi tunju Beta pung rasa kasian sang dong,<bt>Because I want to/am going to show My mercy to them, [EXEG: NLT, also "to let their sins go unpunished” (BAGD, TH); Bruce has best higher level discussion of 8-12. Bruce thrust of 12 is about the “blotting out of their sins” by a God who is “a pardoning God, passing over transgression, unwilling to retain his anger, delighting in loving-kindness, treading his people’s iniquities underfoot, casting all their sins into the depths of the sea.” How 12 fits into 9-12 is vague, and can be problematic if not handled carefully (problems in earlier KM version). (9) old Israel didn't stick with their part of the deal, so I disregarded them; (10-11) new (millenium?) Israel will be faithful to the new covenant and will have a personal relationship/experience with me; (12) [Ellipsed: because of my commitment to this new covenant] [Ellipsed: when they repent of their sins] Because of my mercy, I will forgive them. CEG with CR.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) whole verse revised significantly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) whole verse revised significantly and note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Biar bosong bekin hal yang sonde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Biar bosong bekin hal yang sonde batúl, ma nanti Beta jato kasian sang bosong. better here.]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">andia ko Beta lupa buang dong pung sala-sala samua.&gt;&gt;<bt>that is why I will (completely) forget all their wrongs.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I will have mercy on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I will have mercy on their transgressions, and will remember their sins no more."</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:8-12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 31:31-34</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Waktu Tuhan omong bilang, Dia mau ika janji baru deng dong, dia pung arti, itu janji yang lama, su sonde laku lai. Sonde lama lai, te dia su ilang buang.<bt>When God spoke saying, He was going to bind a new promise with them, that meant, the old promise now no longer was in effect anymore. Soon, it would disappear.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;no good&quot; rather than &quot;poho&quot;, which"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">"no good" rather than "poho", which carries the idea of deteriorating and does not work well with "deal" LITERALLY: By calling this covenant "new," he has made the first one obsolete; an what is obsolete and aging will soon disappear.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus jadi korban yang lebe bae dari korban yang lama dong<bt>The Lord Yesus is a sacrifice which is better than the old sacrifices</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />Sakarang beta mau kasi inga bagini: waktu Tuhan Allah ika itu janji yang partama deng kotong pung nene-moyang dong, Dia ju kasi turun atoran ko dong kasi bangun tampa sambayang, ko dong bisa sémba sang Dia iko itu atoran pung mau.<bt>Now I want to remind you like this: when God bound that first promise with our-inc ancestors, He also handed down regulations so they could build a place of prayer, so they could worship Him according to the ways of those regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="men oun: continuation LITERALLY: Then indeed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">men oun: continuation LITERALLY: Then indeed the first covenant had regulations for worship and also an earthly sanctuary.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Di itu tampa sambayang tu, ada kintal deng tenda bésar satu. Di itu tenda pung kamar muka, ada tampa taro lampu, deng meja satu yang kapala agama dong pake ko taro roti yang dong kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Itu kamar muka tu, dong subu bilang, <span class="Italic">Tuhan Allah pung Kamar Barisi.</span><bt>In that place of prayer, there is a yard (Port. loan: kintal) and a big tent. In that tent's front room, there is a place to place lamp/s on a table, which the *priests use to place bread which they give to God. It is that front room, which they refer to as, <span class="Italic">God's Clean/Holy Room.</span></bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** picture added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** picture added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Needs picture? LITERALLY: A tabernacle was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">Needs picture? LITERALLY: A tabernacle was set up. In its first room were the lampstand, the table, and the consecrated bread. This was called the Holy Place.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 26:1-30, 25:23-40</note></p>
    <fig path="hk-lb\lb00259c.tif" rtfFormat="width:10cm;textWrapping:none" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ada ju satu kaen gorden bésar tagantong ko pele satu kamar laen yang dong subu bilang, <span class="Italic">Tuhan Allah pung Kamar Paling Barisi.</span><bt>There is also a large cloth curtain hung to block off another room which they refer to as <span class="Italic">God's Most Holy Room.</span></bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Behind the second curtain was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Behind the second curtain was a room called the Most Holy Place,</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 26:31-33</note><v n="4" />Di muka itu gorden, ada meja mas satu, ko bakar kamanyán wangi kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Deng di dalam itu Kamar Paling Barisi ada satu peti mas, yang dong subu bilang, <span class="Italic">Peti Janji.</span> Dalam itu peti, dong taro barang kuno ko kasi inga orang so'al Tuhan Allah pung janji yang Dia su ika deng dong. Di situ ada stoples mas satu, yang ta'isi deng roti <span class="Italic">manna.</span> Itu roti tu, roti yang dolu-dolu Tuhan Allah kasi turun dari langit, kasi sang kotong pung nene-moyang dong waktu dong lapar di tampa sunyi. Di itu peti ju ada ba'i Harun pung tongkat karíng yang dolu parná batunas. Deng ada ju itu batu plat yang Tuhan Allah pake ko ukir Dia pung atoran yang Dia kasi sang ba'i Musa tempo hari.<bt>In front of that curtain, there is a gold table, a place to burn aromatic incense to God. And inside that Most Holy Room is a gold trunk/box, which they refer to as <span class="Italic">Promise Trunk.</span> Inside that trunk, they place archaic/antique things to remind people about God's promise which He had bound with them. In that place there is a gold stoples/jar, which is filled with <span class="Italic">manna</span> bread. [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure ‘in that place’ has the jar inside the trunk, not just the room. Have them draw out the contents of vs. 2-5.] That is the bread which long ago God had sent down from the sky, to our ancestors when they were hungry in the empty land. In that trunk there is also Gf Harun's dry staff which had once (grown) off-shoots. And there are also the flat stones which God used to write His regulations which He gave to Gf Musa in those days. [EXEG: basis of location in relation to curtain, see discussion in Bruce, Ellingsworth, Miller, TH. Unknown cultural objects. Have to make lots of implicit info explicit. IS A FTN needed? What would it say?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rev 8:3 ; stoples (KM often"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">rev 8:3 ; stoples (KM often pronounces /toples/)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: which had the golden altar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: which had the golden altar of incense and the gold-covered chest [ark] of the covenant. This chest contained the golden jar of manna, Aaron's rod that had budded, and the stone tablets of the covenant.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 30:1-6, 25:10-16, 16:33, Daftar Sensus 17:8-10, Kaluar dari Masir 25:16, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 10:3-5</note><v n="5" />Di itu peti pung tutu ada dua patong yang hebat. Itu patong dong pung rupa sama ke Tuhan Allah pung ana bua basayap dari sorga yang ada badiri deng sayap tabuka lebar ko tutu ame itu peti, tagal itu tampa kasi tunju Tuhan Allah pung rasa kasian sang manusia. Ma sakarang, beta sonde ada waktu ko omong sampe alus-alus so'al itu barang dong.<bt>On the cover of that trunk there are two impressive statues. Those statues have the shape/form like God's winged underlings from heaven who are standing with their wings opened wide covering the trunk, because that place shows God's mercy/pity to humans. But now, I don't have time to tell in detail about those things. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [NOTE to daughter translations: these are /cherubim/ &gt; ana bua basayap, not /anggelos/ ana bua, so NOT same as ana bua biasa.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="The &quot;angels&quot; were statues. LITERALLY: Above"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">The "angels" were statues. LITERALLY: Above the chest were the cherubim of the Glory, overshadowing the place of atonement [mercy seat]. But we cannot discuss these things in detail now.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tagal itu tampa su jadi bukti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">tagal itu tampa su jadi bukti yang kasi tunju Tuhan Allah pung hati bae sang manusia.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:5" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani bilang, Tuhan pung ana bua basayap dari sorga di sini, nama &lt;<span class="Italic">kerubim</span>&gt;. Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga biasa, dong subu bilang, &lt;<span class="Italic">anggelos</span>&gt;. Dong sonde basayap. Lia ju, <span class="Italic">Carita Mula-mula</span> 3:24, deng <span class="Italic">Kaluar dari Masir</span> 25:18-22.<bt>The Yunani language writings say, God2's winged underlings from heaven here are '<span class="Italic">kerubim</span>'. God's common/normal underlings from heaven, they refer to as '<span class="Italic">anggelos</span>'. They are not winged. Also see Genesis 3:24. and Exodus 25:18-22.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Dong pung cara ator barang dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tenda Sambayang tu, memang bagitu. Ais kapala agama dong maso-kaluar tiap hari pi itu kamar muka ko kasi jalan dong pung tugas di situ.<bt>Their way of arranging/organising things inside God's Tent of Prayer was really like that. then the *priests would enter-exit every day into the front room to carry out their job/responsibilities there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When everything had been arranged"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When everything had been arranged like this, the priests entered regularly into the outer room to carry on their ministry.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 18:2-6</note><v n="7" />Ma cuma kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos bésar sa yang bole maso pi dalam Tuhan Allah pung Kamar Paling Barisi tu. Deng dia sonde bole maso sambarang waktu, te dia cuma bisa maso satu taon satu kali. Deng kalo dia maso, dia musti bawa binatang korban pung dara, ko pi parcík di itu Peti Janji pung tutu. Itu dara pung maksud, ko biar Tuhan Allah hapus buang itu kapala agama deng dia pung orang dong pung sala samua, biar sala yang dong bekin deng sonde sadar ju.<bt>But only the *high priest2 was allowed to enter into God's Most Holy Room. And he was not allowed to enter just any old time, cuz (reason) he could only enter once a year. And if/when he entered, he must take the blood of a sacrificed animal, to go sprinkle/ pour on the cover of that Promise Trunk. The purpose of that blood, was so that God would wipe away all the wrongs of that *priest and his people, even the wrongs that they had done without being aware.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But only the high priest"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But only the high priest entered the inner room, and that only once a year, an never without blood, which he offered for himself and for the sins the people had committed in ignorance.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 16:2-34</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Tuhan Allah su pake Dia pung Roh Barisi ko kasi mangarti sang kotong bilang, kalo itu gorden masi pele jalan maso pi Kamar Paling Barisi, dia pung arti bilang, manusia masi balóm bisa maso pi Tuhan pung muka, salama atoran lama dong masi jalan.<bt>God has already used His Holy Spirit to give understanding to us that, according to the old regulations, if that curtain was still blocking the entrance into the Most Holy Room, that would mean that, humans could still not be able to enter before God2, as long as the old regulations were still in force/valid. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Holy Spirit was showing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Holy Spirit was showing by this that the way into the Most Holy Place had not yet been opened as long as the first tent was still standing.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan Allah su pake Dia pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Tuhan Allah su pake Dia pung Roh Barisi ko kasi mangarti sang kotong, bilang, kalo itu gorden masi pele jalan maso pi di Kamar Paling Barisi, dia pung arti, bilang, manusia masi balóm bisa maso pi di Tuhan pung muka.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Te itu samua jadi conto yang Tuhan pung Roh pake, ko ajar sang kotong yang ada idop sakarang ni. Dolu kotong pung nene-moyang dong bawa dong pung persembahan deng binatang korban kasi pi kapala agama, ko Tuhan Allah hapus buang dong pung sala-sala. Ma biar dong bawa korban bam-banya bagitu ju, itu korban dong sonde bisa bekin dong pung hati jadi barisi, deng sonde bisa kasi ilang dong pung rasa sala di dong pung hati.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) all that is an example which God2's Spirit uses to teach us-inc who are living now. Formerly our ancestors brought their offerings and animal sacrifices to the *priest, so God would wipe away their wrongs. But even if they bring many sacrifices like that, those sacrifices cannot make their livers become clean/holy/pure, and cannot cause to disappear the sense/feeling of wrong in their livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Masmur 51:18-21"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Masmur 51:18-21</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This is an illustration for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This is an illustration for the present time, indicating that the gifts and sacrifices being offered were not able to clear the conscience of the worshiper.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Jadi apa yang dong bekin tu, cuma iko atoran agama sa. Ada atoran yang parenta bilang, dong sonde bisa makan ini, deng sonde bisa minum itu. Ada atoran laen bilang, dong musti cuci dong pung diri deng dong pung alat iko atoran pung mau. Padahal itu atoran dong samua, cuma ator orang pung bagian luar sa, te sonde bisa ator orang pung dalam hati. Biar bagitu ju, ma itu atoran dong musti jalan tarús, sampe Tuhan Allah ganti deng atoran baru.<bt>So (consequently), what they have done, is only to follow religious regulations. There are regulation/s which command that they cannot eat this, and cannot drink that. There are other regulation/s which say they must wash themselves and their tools/instruments according to the ways of the regulations. Whereas in fact, all those regulation merely manage/regulate the outside part of a person, cuz (elaboration) they cannot manage/regulate a person's inner liver. Even that being the case, nevertheless those regulation must/had to keep on going, until God replaced them with new regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They are only a matter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They are only a matter of food and drink and various ceremonial washings -- external regulations applying until the time of the new order.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ma sakarang su ada itu Orang yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang dari dolu. Dia tu, Kristus. Dia su datang ko jadi kotong pung kapala agama paling tinggi, deng Dia su bekin hal bae kasi sang kotong.<bt>But now there already is that person whom God had promised beforehand from long ago. He is Kristus. He has come to be our-inc *highest priest, and He has already done good things for us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:11" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling bae dong tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia <span class="Italic">su</span> bekin hal bae kasi sang kotong.&gt;&gt; Ma ada tulisan saparu lai yang tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia <span class="Italic">mau</span> bekin hal bae kasi sang kotong.&gt;&gt;<bt>The best Yunani language writings write saying, “He has done good things for us.” But there are some other writings which say, “He is going to do good things for us.”</bt></note>Dia kasi jalan Dia pung tugas, sama ke kapala agama model lama, ma Dia karjá di tampa sambayang yang jao lebe hebat. Dia pung tampa sambayang tu, sonde ada di bumi, te bukan manusia yang bekin itu tampa.<bt>He carries out His job/responsibilities, like the *priests of the old model, but He works in a place of prayer which is far more impressive. That place of prayer of His, does not exist on earth, cuz it wasn't humans that made that place. [EXEG: contents of this verse located in heaven (Miller).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ktisis just &quot;this world&quot; LITERALLY: When"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">ktisis just "this world" LITERALLY: When Christ came as high priest of the good things that are already here, he went through the greater and more perfect tabernacle that is not man-made, that is to say, not a part of this creation.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Kristus ju maso pi dalam itu Kamar Paling Barisi, ko mangada sang Tuhan Allah sama ke kapala agama paling tinggi model lama dong bekin satu taon satu kali. Deng waktu Dia maso, Dia ju bawa dara ko kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Ma ada dia pung beda. Te Kristus sonde bawa dara dari binatang korban. Yang Dia bawa tu, andia Dia pung dara sandiri, tagal Dia su mati ko jadi korban kasi sang kotong. Ma Kristus bawa maso Dia pung dara satu kali sa, ko bekin kotong bebas dari sala, sampe salamanya.<bt>Kristus also enters into the Most Holy Room, to face God like the *high priests of the old model did once a year. And when He enters, He also brings blood to give to God. But there is a difference. Cuz (elaboration) Kristus doesn't bring blood from an animal sacrifice. What He brings, is His own blood, because He died (perfective) to be/become a sacrifice for us-inc. But Kristus has brought in His blood just one time to make us free from sin, forever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He did not enter by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He did not enter by means of the blood of goats and calves; but he entered the Most Holy Place once for all by his own blood, having obtained eternal redemption.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Jadi Kristus pung dara tu, memang lebe hebat dari binatang pung dara. Te iko ba'i Musa pung atoran, orang yang bekin sala dong, kamomos, deng sonde pantas maso ko sémba sang Tuhan Allah. Musti pi kapala agama ko bekin korban, ko biar itu korban pung dara bekin barisi kambali sang dong. Ada banya korban yang minta kambing pung dara deng sapi pung dara. Ada ju satu atoran yang bilang, kalo orang sonto orang mati, dia su jadi kamomos di Tuhan pung muka. Kalo itu orang mau jadi barisi kambali, kapala agama musti ame abu sisa abis bakar sapi ténak. Ais dia bawa itu abu, ko pi siram di itu orang kamomos, ko biar dia jadi barisi kambali.<bt>So (consequently), Kristus' blood, really is more impressive/greater than the blood of animals. Cuz (elaboration) according to Gf Musa's regulations, people who do wrong are filthy/defiled, and not worthy/appropriate to enter (implied: into a house of worship) to worship God. They must go to a priest to make a sacrifice, so that the blood of that sacrifice can make them clean again. There were many sacrifices that required the blood of goats and the blood of cows. There was also a regulation that said if a person touched a dead person, he was already dirty/filthy/ defiled before God2. If that person wanted to become clean/pure/holy again, the *priest must take the ashes leftover from burning up a juvenile cow. Then he brought those ashes, to go sprinkle/pour on that defiled person, so that he could become clean/pure again. [EXEG: the defilement was due to contact with the dead (Miller, Ex. Summ.) Bruce, Miller, Ellingsworth; higher structure modelled on CEV. Ellipsed proposition put in under guidance of MC. MTTs and UNSs weren't getting the picture without it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note expanded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note expanded</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;clean outside&quot; would sound like some"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">"clean outside" would sound like some kind of disease, not ritually or morally clean. LITERALLY: The blood of goats and calves, and the ashes of a heifer sprinkled on those who are ceremonially unclean, sanctify them, so they are outwardly clean.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kristus pung dara tu, memang lebe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Kristus pung dara tu, memang lebe hebat dari binatang pung dara. Ada atoran yang Tuhan Allah kasi sang kotong pung nene-moyang dong bilang, kalo orang sonto orang mati, dia su jadi kamomos di Tuhan pung muka. Kalo itu orang mau jadi barisi kambali, dia musti pi di kapala agama. Ais, kapala agama musti ame kambing pung dara, sapi pung dara, deng abu sisa abis bakar sapi ténak. Ais dia bawa itu dara deng abu, ko pi siram di itu orang kamomos pung kapala, ko biar dia jadi barisi kambali.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 16:15-16, Daftar Sensus 19:9,17-19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Naa! Kalo binatang pung dara bisa bekin barisi orang pung badan luar yang kamomos, lebe-lebe lai deng Kristus pung dara! Te Dia pung dara tu, su bekin kotong talapás dari sala-sala dong, deng ju bekin barisi kotong pung dalam hati. Te kotong pung sala bekin kotong tapisa buang dari Tuhan. Waktu Kristus mati, Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang idop tarús, ada tolong sang Dia ko Dia sarakan Dia pung diri kasi sang Tuhan, sama ke binatang korban yang sonde ada pung cacat sadiki ju. Jadi sakarang kotong su bisa sémba deng batúl sang Tuhan Allah yang idop tarús.<bt>Naa! If the blood of an animal is able to make clean/pure the outside part of a defiled person, how much even more the blood of Kristus (statement, not rhetorical question)! Cuz (elaboration) His blood has made us freed from wrongs, and also makes clean our inner livers. Cuz (elaboration) our wrongs make us (be) cut off/separated off from God2. When Kristus died like that, God's Spirit who lives forever, was helping Him so He could turn over/surrender Himself to God2, like an animal sacrifice which has not even a little blemish. So (consequently) now we-inc can already truly worship God who lives forever. [EXEG: NLT. Note TH discussion of ‘dead works’ makes no sense in light of Miller.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note expanded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note expanded</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="like Verse 9. TERM: apollymi: &quot;cut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">like Verse 9. TERM: apollymi: "cut us off from God" or active "cut ourself off from God."<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: How much more, then, will the blood of Christ, who through the eternal Spirit offered himself unblemished to God, cleanse our consciences from acts that lead to death, so that we may serve the living God!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Tagal Kristus pung dara yang paling hebat tu, andia ko Tuhan Allah pake sang Dia, ko ator janji baru kasi samua orang yang Tuhan Allah su pange ame ko jadi Dia pung orang. Te waktu Kristus mati ko kasi salamat orang, Dia ju tabús ame kotong pung nene-moyang dari sala yang dong bekin dolu-dolu, waktu Tuhan Allah ika janji lama deng dong. Tagal itu, dong ju su bisa idop tarús-tarús deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>Because of Kristus' blood which is most impressive, that is why God used Him, to arrange a new promise for all the people whom God had called to be/become His people. Cuz (elaboration) when Kristus died to save people, He also *redeemed/ransomed our ancestors from the wrongs which they had done long ago, when God bound the old promise with them. Because of that, they also can live forever with God. [EXEG: Careful about noise from the English word ‘mediator’. The Gk word can have the force of 1) “go-between” (which most people default to), or 2) the one who arranges (LN “guaranteeing the certainty of the arrangement”). The first sense doesn't actually fit this context, so TB ‘perantara’ really skews the focus. TEV “the one who arranges” is much better in this context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For this reason Christ is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For this reason Christ is the mediator of a new covenant, that those who are called may receive the promised eternal inheritance--now that he has died as a ransom to set them free from the sins committed under the first covenant.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Beta pake conto orang tarima pusaka, sama ke satu bapa bekin surat warisan ko nanti kasi pusaka sang dia pung ana. Ma itu ana baru bole pegang ame itu pusaka, kalo dia pung bapa su mati.<bt>I use the example of a person receiving inheritance, like a father makes a will (letter of inheritance2) to later give an inheritance to his child. But that child can only hold/take possession of that inheritance, if his father has died.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In the case of a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In the case of a will, it is necessary to prove the death of the one who made it,</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Te kalo itu bapa masi idop, dia pung ana balóm bisa tarima pusaka yang bapa su janji di itu surat warisan.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) when that father is still alive, his child is not yet able to receive that inheritance which the father has already promised in that will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: because a will is in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: because a will is in force only when somebody has died; it never takes effect while the one who made it is living.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Bagitu ju deng Tuhan Allah pung janji partama yang Dia ika deng kotong pung nene-moyang. Dong baru bisa tarima ame apa yang Tuhan janji tu, kalo ada satu yang mati lebe dolo. Andia ko dong pung korban pake binatang pung dara ko jadi bukti ada yang su mati.<bt>It is also like that with God's first promise which He bound with our ancestors. They can only receive what God has promised, if there is one who dies first. That is why their sacrifices used the blood of animals as proof that there was some(thing/one) that had died. [NOTE to daughter translators: blood is introduced in vs.18 as example of broader principle in 17, and flowing on into 19. So don't replace it with ‘death’ here by treating it as metonymy--it needs to be blood here. See NLT.] [EXEG: CEV undertranslated here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV untertranslated !@"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">CEV untertranslated !@</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This is why even the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This is why even the first covenant was not put into effect without blood.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Tempo hari, ba'i Musa kumpul kotong pung nene-moyang dong, ko dia kasi tau parenta samua yang ada di itu atoran yang Tuhan su kasi turun. Ais itu, ba'i Musa bunu bekin mati sapi deng kambing, ko ame dong pung dara, ais campor deng aer. Dia ju pake tali mera ko ika tangke daon alus. Ais dia colo pi dalam itu dara, ko kabás-kabás pi atas Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan, deng pi atas rakyat dong samua.<bt>At that time, Gf Musa gathered our ancestors, so he could tell them all the commands which were in those regulation that God2 had handed down. After that, Gf Musa killed cows and goats, to get their blood, then mix it with water. He also used a red string/rope to tie the stems/stalks of fine leaves. Then he dipped them into that blood, to shake/brush it on God's Writings, and on all the populace/people. [NOTE to daughter translations: Look at entry and picture for ‘hisop’ in Kamus Alkitab bhs Kupang, and discuss best wording for tying a bunch of these together.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note and footnote added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** note and footnote added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: When Moses had proclaimed every"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: When Moses had proclaimed every commandment of the law to all the people, he took the blood of calves and goats, together with water, scarlet wool and branches of hyssop, and sprinkled the scroll and all the people.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:19" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani bilang ini daon dong pung nama, andia ὕσσωπος (<span class="Italic">hussopos</span>). Baca entri di <span class="Italic">Kamus Pengantar Alkitab bahasa Kupang</span> untuk ‘hisop’.<bt>The Yunani language Bible says the name of these leaves is ὕσσωπος (<span class="Italic">hyssopos</span>). Read the entry in the <span class="Italic">Introductory Bible Dictionary of the Kupang language</span> for ‘hisop’.</bt></note><v n="20" />Waktu ba'i Musa kabás-kabás itu dara, dia ju omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini dara ni, jadi tanda bilang, Tuhan Allah ada ika janji deng bosong. Kalo bosong bekin iko Dia pung parenta samua, nanti Dia ju kasi samua yang Dia su janji.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Gf Musa brushed that blood, he also spoke saying, "This blood is a sign that God is binding a promise with you-pl. If you do according to all His commands, He will also give everything that He has promised."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERM: Mark 14:24 blood of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">TERM: Mark 14:24 blood of the covenant. LITERALLY: He said, "This is the blood of the covenant, which God has commanded you to keep."<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:19-20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 24:6-8</note><v n="21" />Ba'i Musa ju kabás-kabás dara pi di Tenda Sambayang, deng samua alat di situ yang dong pake ko sémba sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Gf Musa also brushed blood at/on the Tent of Prayer, and all the instruments there which they used to worship God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In the same way, he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In the same way, he sprinkled with the blood both the tabernacle and everything used in its ceremonies.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 8:15</note><v n="22" />Te iko Tuhan pung atoran, amper samua yang kamomos, musti bekin barisi pake dara. Tagal itu, kalo manusia mau jadi barisi dari dong pung sala, na, musti ada korban pung dara.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) according to God's regulations, almost everything that is filthy/defiled, must be made clean/pure using blood. Because of that, if humans want to become clean from their wrongs, na, there must be blood from a sacrifice. [EXEG: Gk ‘nearly/almost’ two views 1) nearly everything, or 2) one might almost say... We go with first as does TB. See Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In fact, the law require"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In fact, the law require that nearly everything be cleansed with blood, and without the shedding of blood there is no forgiveness.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 17:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Apa yang beta carita so'al kotong pung nene-moyang deng dong pung Tenda Sambayang tu, itu samua cuma conto sa, ko biar kotong bisa mangarti Tuhan Allah pung tampa sambayang yang asli di sorga. Te kalo kapala agama model lama mau maso pi dalam itu Tenda ko sémba sang Tuhan Allah, dong musti bekin barisi samua-samua dolo, pake binatang korban pung dara. Tuhan Allah pung tampa sambayang di sorga ju musti barisi. Ma musti pake dara korban yang lebe hebat dari binatang pung dara.<bt>What I am narrating about our ancestors and their Tent of Prayer, all that is merely an example, so that we-inc can understand God's original/real place of prayer/worship in heaven. Cuz (elaboration) if a *priest of the old model wants to go into that Tent to worship God, they must make everything clean/pure/holy first, using the blood of an animal sacrifice. God's place of prayer in heaven must also be clean/pure/holy. But blood must be used from a sacrifice which is even more impressive than an animal's blood.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: It was necessary, then, for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: It was necessary, then, for the copies of the heavenly things to be purified with these sacrifices, but the heavenly things themselves with better sacrifices than these.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Itu Kamar Paling Barisi yang Kristus maso tu, bukan kamar di Tenda Sambayang yang manusia bekin. Te itu Tenda di bumi tu, cuma conto dari yang asli sa. Ma Kristus maso langsung di sorga ko bela sang kotong di Tuhan Allah pung muka.<bt>That Most Holy Room which Kristus enters, is not a room in the Tent of Prayer which humans made. Cuz (elaboration) that Tent on earth is only an example of the asli. But Kristus enters directly in heaven to defend us before God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Like 9:8 LITERALLY: For Christ did"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">Like 9:8 LITERALLY: For Christ did not enter a man-made sanctuary that was only a copy of the true one; he entered heaven itself, now to appear for us in God's presence.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Dolu kapala agama paling tinggi musti maso ulang-ulang tiap taon pi itu Kamar Paling Barisi, deng bawa binatang pung dara kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Ma Kristus sonde bagitu. Te Dia cuma parlú maso satu kali sa, deng bawa Dia pung dara sandiri.<bt>Formerly the *highest priest had to enter repeatedly each year into that Most Holy Room, and take animal's blood to God. But Kristus is not like that. Cuz (elaboration) He only needs to enter once, and brings His own blood.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Nor did he enter heaven"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Nor did he enter heaven to offer himself again and again, the way the high priest enters the Most Holy Place every year with blood that is not his own.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Te kalo Dia musti maso tiap taon sama ke kapala agama yang model lama tu, dia pung arti bilang, Dia musti mati ulang-ulang kali mulai dari dunya pung mula-mula sampe sakarang, ko biar Dia hapus buang tiap orang pung sala-sala. Ma Dia sonde bekin bagitu. Te pas dia pung waktu Dia mati jadi korban cuma satu kali sa, ko angka buang samua sala yang orang bekin.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if He must enter each year like the old/former *priest, that means that He must die repeatedly beginning from the earth's beginnings until now in order to wipe away all (individual) people's wrongs. But He does/did not do that. Cuz (elaboration) just at the right time He became a sacrifice one time only, to get rid of all wrongs which people did/do. [EXEG: does Gk “end of the ages” refer to 1) the end of the world, or 2) Christ's work on earth? both Ex.Summ #1 and #3 are saying essentially the same thing: Christ's appearance on earth/earthly ministry/sacrifice (no meaningful difference in the big picture) is the climax of history that introduces a new (final?) era that is ‘present’ to the writer of Hebrews. But there is so much information left implicit that I would never get there from the (literal &amp; undertranslated) wording of NRSV/NIV/NLT/GW/ESV “at the end of the age/s”, CEV “near the end of time”, the nonsensical TEV “when all ages of time are nearing the end”, NET “at the consummation of the ages” which all evoke to my ears “the end of the world” (reinforced by the “from the foundation of the world” phrase in the previous clause, and the similar phrasing in Matt—which does refer to the end times.), as does the Indonesian phrasing in this verse – none of which actually fit the context of the point of these verses. This phrasing is one of the worst skewing of focus I recall seeing. The NCV “Just at the right time” and JBP “now, at this point in time, the end of the present age” or something like “now at the pinnacle of history” seem to fit the context much better, but the NCV loses the imagery of the phrasing (which ‘end of the age’ I think badly interferes with getting the point to my English ears). The NCV rendering is supported by TH. NLT1 is much better as a meaning-based translation for this verse than NLT2 (a disappointing retreat toward the literal and the awkward). Another problem is with “he would have had to suffer again and again since the foundation of the world” which seems to have an implied/ellipted proposition on the order of “to account for the sins of all people throughout history”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Christ would have had"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Christ would have had to suffer many times since the creation of the world. But now he has appeared once for all at the end of the ages to do away with sin by the sacrifice of himself.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Su jalás manusia mati satu kali sa. Ma ais itu dia musti datang mangada di Tuhan Allah pung muka ko Tuhan pareksa sang dia.<bt>It is clear (perfective) that humans die only once. But after that s/he must come and face/report to authority before God so God2 examines him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Just as man is destined"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Just as man is destined to die once, and after that to face judgment,</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Bagitu ju, Kristus. Dia mati deng sarakan Dia pung diri ko jadi korban satu kali sa. Deng Dia ju nanti datang kambali. Ma Dia sonde urus orang pung sala lai, tagal Dia su bekin beres itu tugas. Ma yang Dia mau urus nanti tu, andia Dia mau kasi salamat sang samua orang yang ada baharap sang Dia.<bt>It is the same with Kristus. He died and turned over/surrendered Himself to become a sacrifice only once. And He will also come back again. But He does not arrange/deal with people's wrongs anymore, because He has already fully taken care of that responsibility. But what He is going to deal with/handle/manage later then, is that He wants to save everyone who is/has been hoping/trusting in Him. [EXEG: Bruce, Miller]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: so Christ was sacrificed once"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: so Christ was sacrificed once to take away the sins of many people; and he will appear a second time, not to bear sin, but to bring salvation to those who are waiting for him.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma Dia sonde urus orang pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Ma Dia sonde urus orang pung sala lai, tagal Dia su bekin beres itu tugas tu. Ma yang Dia urus, andia Dia mau kasi berkat sang samua orang yang ada baharap sang Dia.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:12</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus mati satu kali sa, ko orang bisa idop babae deng Tuhan Allah sampe salamanya<bt>Kristus died just one time, so people could live in right-relationship with God forever</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Kalo kotong mau mangarti batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung mau, itu atoran yang Dia kasi sang kotong pung nene-moyang dong masi kurang jalás. Te itu cuma bayang-bayang dari hal-hal bae yang Tuhan mau kasi sang kotong. Jadi biar orang iko itu atoran dong, deng bawa binatang korban tarús-tarús ju, itu sonde bisa bekin barisi batúl dong pung sala-sala.<bt>If we-inc want to truly understand the will/ways of God, those regulation which He gave to our ancestors are still unclear. Cuz (elaboration) they are only a shadow of the good things that God2 wants to give us. So even if/though people follow those regulations, and keep bringing animal sacrifices, that can not make their wrongs truly/completely clean/holy/pure.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The law is only a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The law is only a shadow of the good things that are coming--not the realities themselves. For this reason it can never, by the same sacrifices repeated endlessly year after year, make perfect those who draw near to worship.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Te kalo itu atoran bisa bekin ilang batúl dong pung sala-sala, na, dong sonde bawa binatang korban lai, tagal dong su sonde rasa sala di dong pung hati lai. Padahal sonde bagitu.<bt>Cuz if those regulations can make their wrongs truly/really dissapear, na, they would not bring animal sacrifices anymore, because they no longer feel wrong in their livers anymore. Whereas in fact it is not like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If it could, would they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If it could, would they not have stopped being offered? For the worshipers would have been cleansed once for all, and would no longer have felt guilty for their sins.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Te tiap taon dong maen minta ulang-ulang ko Tuhan Allah hapus buang dong pung sala-sala,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) each year they keep asking repeatedly for God to wipe away their wrongs,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But those sacrifices are an"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But those sacrifices are an annual reminder of sins.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />tagal sonde mungkin binatang pung dara ada pung kuasa ko angka buang batúl orang pung sala-sala.<bt>because it is not probable/possible that the blood of animals has power/authority, to truly get rid of people's wrongs. [EXEG: Bruce, Miller]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: because it is impossible for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: because it is impossible for the blood of bulls and goats to take away sins.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-6" />Andia ko Kristus omong bagini waktu Dia datang di ini dunya:<bt>That is why Kristus spoke like this when He came to this world:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah!<bt>"God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan sonde sanáng deng itu binatang korban deng persembahan laen yang dong bawa.<bt>God2 is not happy with the animal sacrifices and other offerings that they bring.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong horo bekin mati binatang bam-banya,<bt>They ritually slaughter a great many animals,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko jadi korban.<bt>to be sacrifices.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ais dong bakar binatang bam-banya,<bt>And then they burn/roast a great many animals,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko minta ampon.<bt>to ask forgiveness.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar bagitu ju, ma Tuhan pung hati sonde sanáng.<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless God2's liver is not happy.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia ko Tuhan suru sang Beta datang di ini dunya,<bt>That is why God2 ordered Me to come to this world,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko jadi manusia sama ke dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>to become human like them."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, when Christ came into"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, when Christ came into the world, he said, "Sacrifice and offering you did not desire, but a body you prepared for me; with burnt offerings and sin offerings you were not pleased.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais Kristus ju omong bilang,<bt>Then Kristus also spoke saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tuhan! Beta su ada di sini!<bt>"Gos2/Lord! I am already here!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta datang ko bekin iko Tuhan pung mau,<bt>I came to do according to God2's will,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sama ke Tuhan pung jubir su tulis memang so'al Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>like God2's *spokesman/prophet has written beforehand about Me."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then I [Christ] said, 'Here"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then I [Christ] said, 'Here I am--it is written about me in the scroll--I have come to do your will, O God'"</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:5-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 40:7-9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Jadi, yang Kristus omong partama tu, andia:<bt>So (consequently), what Kristus had said first was:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tuhan sonde sanáng deng itu binatang korban deng persembahan laen yang dong bawa.<bt>"God2 is not happy with the animal sacrifices and other offerings which they brought.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong horo bekin mati binatang bam-banya,<bt>They ritually slaughter a great many animals,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko jadi korban.<bt>to be sacrifices.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ais dong bakar binatang dong,<bt>And then they burn those animals,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko minta ampon.<bt>to ask foregiveness.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar bagitu ju, ma Tuhan pung hati sonde sanáng.&gt;&gt;<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless God2's liver is not happy."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Jadi biar dong su bekin iko parsís deng ba'i Musa pung atoran dong, ma Tuhan Allah pung hati sonde sanáng.<bt>So (consequently) even though they did exactly according to Gf Musa's regulations, nevertheless God's liver is not happy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: First he said, &quot;Sacrifices and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: First he said, "Sacrifices and offerings, burnt offerings and sin offerings you did not desire, nor were you pleased with them" (although the law required them to be made).</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Waktu Kristus omong bilang,<bt>When Kristus spoke saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta datang ko bekin iko Tuhan pung mau.&gt;&gt;<bt>"I came to do according to God2's will/way."</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia pung arti bilang, Kristus datang ko hapus buang jalan yang lama, ais ganti deng jalan yang baru.<bt>That means that Kristus came to wipe away the old way, and then replace it with a new way.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then he [Christ] said, &quot;Here"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then he [Christ] said, "Here I am. I have come to do your will." He sets aside the first to establish the second.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Te Tuhan pung mau, andia Yesus Kristus jadi korban ko mati satu kali kasi sang kotong manusia. Deng bagitu, Dia bekin kotong jadi orang barisi sampe salamanya.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2's will is that YK became a sacrifice to die one time for we-inc humans. In that way, He made us-inc become clean/holy/pure people forever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And by that will, we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And by that will, we have been made holy through the sacrifice of the body of Jesus Christ once for all.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Tiap hari, itu kapala agama model lama dong maen kasi jalan dong pung tugas, deng maen horo bekin mati binatang korban dong. Padahal itu korban dong sonde parná ada kuasa ko angka buang batúl orang pung sala.<bt>Each day, those *priest of the old model kept carrying out their job/responsibilities, and kept ritual killing animal sacrifices. Whereas in fact, those sacrifices have never had the power/authority to truly get rid of people's wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hesteeken: take his place, show up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">hesteeken: take his place, show up for work LITERALLY: Day after day every priest stands and performs his religious duties; again and again he offers the same sacrifices, which can never take away sins.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 29:38</note><v n="12" />Ma kotong pung Kapala Agama Paling Tinggi, andia Kristus, sarakan Dia pung diri ko mati jadi korban kasi sang kotong. Lewat Dia jadi korban satu kali sa, Dia su buka jalan ko bisa angka buang abis kotong manusia pung sala samua. Ais itu, baru Dia pi dudu di Tuhan Allah pung sablá kanan, di tampa yang paling hormat.<bt>But our-inc *high priest, that is Kristus, surrendered/ handed over Himself to die as a sacrifice for us. By Him becoming a sacrifice just one time, He has opened the way to be able to completely take away all our all of our human wrongs. After that, then He went (and) sat at God's right side, in the place of highest respect/ honour.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But when this priest had"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But when this priest had offered for all time one sacrifice for sins, he sat down at the right hand of God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma Kristus tu, kapala agama model"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Ma Kristus tu, kapala agama model baru. Dia mati ko jadi korban cuma satu kali sa. Deng bagitu, Dia su angka buang abis manusia pung sala dong samua. Ais itu, baru Dia pi dudu di Tuhan Allah pung sablá kanan, di tampa yang paling hormat.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Di situ, Dia ada tunggu sampe Tuhan Allah bekin Dia pung musu dong ta'alok sang Dia.<bt>In that place, He is waiting until God makes His enemies surrender/be in subjection to Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERM: footstool. Regularized? LITERALLY: Since that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">TERM: footstool. Regularized? LITERALLY: Since that time he waits for his enemies to be made his footstool,<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:12-13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:1</note><v n="14" />Dia pung korban yang satu kali tu, bekin putus tarús-tarús sala pung kuasa kasi orang yang Kristus ada bekin barisi dong.<bt>That one-time sacrifice of His, continually breaks/severs the power/authority of sin/wrong for the people whom Kristus is making clean/holy. [EXEG: NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: because by one sacrifice he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: because by one sacrifice he has made perfect forever those who are being made holy.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te Dia sarakan Dia pung Diri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Te Dia sarakan Dia pung Diri satu kali sa. Deng bagitu, orang yang Dia su cap bilang dong su sonde ada pung sala lai, Dia bisa bekin barisi tarús-tarús dong pung dalam hati.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Tuhan Allah pung Roh Barisi ju ada kasi tau itu hal yang sama kasi kotong. Te Dia parná omong bilang,<bt>God's Holy Spirit has also told/explained/made known that same matter to us-inc. Cuz (elaboration) He once spoke saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Holy Spirit also testifies"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Holy Spirit also testifies to us about this. First he says,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="16" />&lt;&lt;Bosong pung Bos ada kasi tau bagini:<bt>"You-pl Boss explains/makes known like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta ika janji baru deng Beta pung orang dong,<bt>I bind a new promise with My people. [EXEG: “after that time” undertranslated as ‘new promise’. = after God's anger was over (Miller, Heb. 8:8)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta taro Beta pung atoran di dong pung pikiran,<bt>I place My regulations in their thoughts.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Beta tulis Beta pung parenta di dong pung dalam hati.&gt;&gt;<bt>and I write my commands in their inner livers.'" [NOTE to daughter translation: check with MTTs and UNSs if your lg has an equivalent of /dong pung dalam hati/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: &quot;This is the covenant I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: "This is the covenant I will make with them after that time, says the Lord. I will put my laws in their hearts, and I will write them on their minds."</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 31:33</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais Dia kasi tau tamba bilang,<bt>Then He adds further saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Nanti Beta sonde inga lai dong pung sala dong.<bt>"I don't remember their wrongs anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Beta lupa buang dong pung bekin-bekin,<bt>And I have (completely) forgotten their deeds, [NOTE to daughter translations: KM /bekin-bekin/ is ONLY negative. Reflect that with s.t. like “their bad deeds”.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">waktu dong langgar Beta pung atoran dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>when they transgressed My regulations."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then he adds: &quot;Their sins"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then he adds: "Their sins and lawless acts I will remember no more."</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 31:34</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Naa. Dia pung arti bilang, kalo Tuhan Allah su hapus buang orang pung sala dong, orang su sonde parlú bawa korban lai, ko bekin dingin Tuhan pung hati.<bt>Naa [+shift (to conclusion)]. That means that if God has already wiped away people's wrongs, people do not need to bring sacrifices anymore in order to cool God's liver" [EXEG: See NLT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And where these have been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And where these have been forgiven, there is no longer any sacrifice for sin.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong su sonde usa taku-taku datang mangada sang Tuhan Allah<bt>We-inc do not need to be fearful coming before God</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Jadi bagini, sodara dong! Yesus su kasi tumpa Dia pung dara ko bekin dingin Tuhan Allah pung hati. Andia ko sakarang kotong su sonde usa taku-taku lai datang mangada sang Dia di Dia pung Tampa Paling Barisi di sorga.<bt>So it's like this, siblings! Yesus has spilled His blood (common figure of speech in region relating to bloodshed/death for a cause, such as political revolution or reform) to cool God's liver. That is why now, we do not need to be fearful anymore about coming before Him in His Most Clean/Holy Place in heaven. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, brothers, since we have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, brothers, since we have confidence to enter the [Most] Holy Place by the blood of Jesus,</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Inga itu Kamar Paling Barisi lama tu! Di situ, ada gorden bésar yang pele ko orang sonde bole maso mangada langsung di Tuhan Allah. Ma deng Yesus pung mati tu, Dia buka jalan baru, ko orang bisa ba'omong langsung deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>Remember that old Most Clean/Holy Room! There, there was a large curtain which blocked off so that people may not enter directly before/fronting up to God. But with/by Yesus' death, He opened a new way/path, so that people are able to talk directly with God. [EXEG: ‘living way’ = effective way for people to reach God (Miller).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERM: sarkos. Discuss in Introduction? LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">TERM: sarkos. Discuss in Introduction? LITERALLY: by a new and living way opened for us through the curtain, that is, his body,<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Lebe-lebe lai, Yesus ju jadi kapala agama yang talalu hebat, yang layani deng ator Tuhan Allah pung isi ruma dong.<bt>Even more than that, Yesus is also the most amazing *priest. who serves and oversees/guides God's household/family2. [NOTE to daughter translations: check to make sure the “household” word in your lg focuses on the people, not the things.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and since we have a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and since we have a great priest over the house of God,</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Tagal itu jadi kotong pung hak, na, mari kotong maso ko mangada deng ba'omong langsung deng Tuhan Allah. Ma kotong musti parcaya batúl sang Dia deng hati lurus. Te Yesus pung mati su bekin barisi kotong pung dalam hati, sampe kotong su sonde pikir hal-hal jahat lai. Deng kotong musti idop barisi ju, sama ke kapala agama model lama dong musti mandi dolo baru maso layani sang Tuhan.<bt>Because it is our right, na, let us enter before God to speak directly with Him. But we must truly believe in Him with a straght/righteous liver. Cuz (elaboration) Yesus'death has cleansed/purified our inner livers, to the point that we no longer think about evil things. And we must also live clean/holy, like priests of the old model had to bathe first before they entered to serve God2. [EXEG: Bruce, Miller, Ellingsworth] [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK to make sure the /sama ke/ is communicating a comparison, not a return to the old way of doing things. Potential ambiguity.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aleethinees kardias: sincere hearts LITERALLY: let"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">aleethinees kardias: sincere hearts LITERALLY: let us draw near to God with a sincere heart in full assurance of faith, having our hearts sprinkled to cleanse us from a guilty conscience, and having our bodies washed with pure water.<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tagal itu, kotong musti ba'omong langsung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Tagal itu, kotong musti ba'omong langsung deng Tuhan Allah, te kotong parcaya batúl-batúl sang Dia deng hati lurus. Te Yesus su bekin barisi kotong pung dalam hati, sampe kotong su sonde pikir hal-hal jahat lai. Deng Dia su bekin barisi sang kotong batúl-batúl sama ke kapala agama model lama dong kabás samua-samua deng dara.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 8:30, 16:4, Yeskial 36:25</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Mari ko kotong ju pegang kuat-kuat samua hal yang kotong mangaku so'al Tuhan Allah. Deng kotong ju musti baharap sang Dia deng sonde usa pikir-pikir, te Dia pasti bekin iko Dia pung janji.<bt>Let us also hold firmly to everything that we have confessed/acknowledged about God. We must hope in Him without anxiety, cuz (elaboration) He will surely do according to His promise. [EXEG: hope we profess/confess = God faithful to keep His promises (NLT).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="MESOLECTAL: ragu-ragu *** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">MESOLECTAL: ragu-ragu *** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Let us hold unswerving to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Let us hold unswerving to the hope we profess, for he who promised is faithful.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Deng mari kotong cari-cari jalan ko buju-buju kotong pung sodara orang parcaya, ko biar kotong samua kasi tunju sayang bam-banya deng karjá hal bae macam-macam.<bt>And let us-inc be looking for ways to be persuading/coaxing/enticing/cajoling our fellow believers, so that all of us show/demonstrate much love and do various sorts of good things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And let us consider how"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And let us consider how we may [spur / stimulate] one another on toward love and good deeds.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais kotong ju musti taro kira"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Ais kotong ju musti taro kira satu deng satu tarús-tarús, ko biar kotong samua bekin hal bae macam-macam, deng kasi tunju sayang bam-banya. Kotong ju musti kokoe satu deng satu tarús-tarús, ko biar kotong samua bekin hal bae macam-macam, deng kasi tunju sayang bam-banya.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Te beta su dengar ada orang saparu yang sonde mau bakumpul lai deng dong pung sodara orang parcaya dong. Ma jang bagitu! Te bosong musti bakumpul ko kasi kuat satu deng satu pung hati. Lebe-lebe lai, tagal Tuhan pung waktu datang kambali su deka-deka. Kasi inga sang dong bagitu!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I have heard that there are some people who don't want to gather anymore with their fellow believers. But it should not be like that! Cuz (reason, elaboration) you-pl must gather to strengthen/encourage each other's livers. Even more than that, because God2's time for coming back is already very near. Remind them like that!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Let us not give up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Let us not give up meeting together, as some are in the habit of doing, but let us encourage one another--and all the more as you see the Day approaching.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Sodara sayang dong! Kotong su tau sampe alus-alus so'al Yesus Kristus pung jalan yang batúl. Ma kalo kotong bale balakang sang Yesus, deng idop bekin sala tarús-tarús, na, dia pung arti bilang, su sonde ada korban laen lai yang bisa hapus buang kotong pung sala dong.<bt>Dear siblings! We already know in detail about YK true way. but if we turn our backs on Yesus, and habitually keep doing wrong, na, that means that there is no other sacrifice which is able to wipe away our-inc wrongs. [DISCOURSE: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If we deliberately keep on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If we deliberately keep on sinning after we have received the knowledge of the truth, no sacrifice for sins is left.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Kotong cuma tunggu deng taku-taku, tagal Tuhan Allah datang kasi hukum sang kotong. Te api naraka yang manyala hebat su siap ko mau kasi ancor abis samua orang yang malawan sang Dia.<bt>We can only wait with fear because God will come and punish us. Cuz (elaboration) the fires of *hell which are burning fiercely are ready to completely destroy everyone who opposes/rebels against Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: if personification in last sentence is a problem, remove “which” and “is ready” /yang ... su siap... mau/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: but only a certain fearful"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: but only a certain fearful expectation of judgment, and of raging fire that will consume the enemies of God.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 26:11</note><v n="28" />Dolu kalo ada satu orang yang tola buang ba'i Musa pung atoran, deng ada dua-tiga orang yang jadi saksi bagitu, itu orang yang bekin sala tu, musti kaná hukum mati, deng sonde ada pung ampon lai.<bt>Formerly, if there was one person who rejects Gf Musa's regulations, and there were two-three people who were witnesses like that, that person who had done wrong, must get death punishment, and there was no more forgiveness. [EXEG: Most sources say this is Gk word “reject, refuse to obey, regard as invalid”, not merely ‘violate, transgress. NRSV is an exception on this.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** violate &gt; reject (2009) note"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** violate &gt; reject (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Anyone who rejected the law"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Anyone who rejected the law of Moses died without mercy on the testimony of two or three witnesses.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 17:6, 19:15</note><v n="29" />Ma sakarang, kalo ada orang yang bekin hina Tuhan Allah pung Ana, itu sama ke dia pandang enteng Yesus pung dara, yang Dia su kasi tumpa ko bekin barisi itu orang. Deng dia sonde toe deng Tuhan Allah pung janji, yang Dia ika deng itu orang pake itu dara. Deng dia ju bekin mara sang Tuhan Allah pung Roh, yang su kasi tunju hati bae sang itu orang. Bayangkan sa! Te orang macam bagini tantu pikol hukuman yang jao lebe barát lai dari orang yang tola buang ba'i Musa pung atoran.<bt>But now, if there is a person who shows contempt for God's Child, that is the same as if he scorns/belittles Yesus' blood, which He has spilled (for a cause) to make that person clean/pure/holy. And s/he doesn't care about God's promise, which He bound with that person using that blood. And s/he also angers God's Spirit, who has shown/demonstrated goodness/ grace/ kindness/generosity to that person. Just imagine! Cuz (elaboration) people of this sort will surely bear a punishment which is far heavier/severe than people who rejected gf Musa's regulations. [EXEG: Miller]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** violated &gt; rejected in last"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** violated &gt; rejected in last sentece to match vs.28 (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: How much more severely do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: How much more severely do you think a man needs to be punished who has trampled the Son of God under foot, who has treated as an unholy thing the blood of the covenant that sanctified him, and who has insulted the Spirit of grace?</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 24:8</note><v n="30" />Tuhan Allah parná omong bilang,<bt>God once spoke saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta ada pung hak, ko balas orang pung jahat.<bt>"I have the right to avenge/pay back people's evil.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Beta pasti bekin iko bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>And I will surely do according to that." [NOTE: CHECK: mesolectal /pasti/ &gt; KM /tantu/ "surely" Usually has to shift to a different slot in the sentence.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Deng ada tulis lai bilang,<bt>And it is also written that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah tu, yang hak parenta samua.<bt>"God is the one with say-so/ordering rights over everything/one.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nanti Dia kasi jato hukuman sang Dia pung orang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>He will hand down punishment to His people." [EXEG: judge = punish (Ex. Summ.)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For we know him who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For we know him who said, "Vengence is mine. I will repay." That's what God said. And again, "The Lord will judge his people."</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 32:35, 36</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Inga te Tuhan Allah idop tarús-tarús! Orang pasti ngarí, kalo Tuhan su tangkap ame sang dong!<bt>Remember that God lives forever! People will surely be horrified, if/when God2 has captured/caught/arrested them! [NOTE: CHECK: mesolectal /pasti/ &gt; KM /tantu/ "surely" Usually has to shift to a different slot in the sentence.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: It is a [dreadful /"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: It is a [dreadful / terrifying] thing to fall into the hands of the Living God!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Bosong musti inga waktu bosong baru mulai mangarti so'al Kristus, ais bosong pung pikiran jadi taráng. Te itu waktu, biar bosong dapa sangsara deng susa bam-banya, ma bosong batahan deng parcaya tarús sang Kristus.<bt>You-pl must remember when you first began to understand about Kristus, and (result) your thinking became clear. Cuz at that time, even though you got a lot of difficulty2/suffering and trouble/difficulty1, nevertheless you endured and/by continued to believe in Kristus. [EXEG: suffer because believed in Kristus (Deibler).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Remember those earlier days after"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Remember those earlier days after you had received the light, when you endured in a great struggle of suffering.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te itu waktu, bosong dapa sangsara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Te itu waktu, bosong dapa sangsara deng susa bam-banya dari orang laen, tagal bosong pung parcaya sang Kristus.</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Ada orang yang bekin hina sang bosong, deng bekin malu sang bosong di orang banya pung muka. Deng, kalo ada yang bekin bagitu sang bosong pung tamán orang parcaya dong, na, bosong ju tolong sang dong.<bt>There were people who treated you-pl with contempt, and shamed you before many people. And, if there were those who did those things to your fellow believers, na, you helped them. [EXEG: Gk. ‘partners’ undertranslated in OV. NLT, NRSV.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Sometimes you were publically exposed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Sometimes you were publically exposed to insult and persecution; at other times you stood side by side with those who were so treated.</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Bosong rasa kasian deng kasi tunju hati bae sang orang yang kaná lempar maso dalam bui. Kalo orang pancuri bawa bosong pung barang, bosong tarima deng hati tanáng sa, tagal bosong su tau bilang, bosong ni nanti tarima hal-hal yang jao lebe bae, yang orang sonde bisa pancuri bawa.<bt>You-pl felt pity/mercy and showed goodness/ kindness/ grace/generosity to people who were thrown into prison. If/when people stole your things/ possessions, you just accepted it with calm/peaceful livers, because you already knew that you would later receive things that are far better, which people cannot steal.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You sympathized with those in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You sympathized with those in prison, and joyfully accepted the confication of your property, because you knew that you yourselves had better and lasting possessions.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma biar dong tangkap ame sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Ma biar dong tangkap ame sang bosong ko buang pi dalam bui, bosong pung hati bae sang dong. Biar dong pancuri bawa bosong pung barang ju, bosong tarima sa, tagal bosong su tau, bilang, bosong ni nanti tarima hal-hal yang jao lebe bae, yang orang sonde bisa pancuri bawa.</Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Andia ko bosong musti pegang kuat-kuat bosong pung parcaya. Te nanti Tuhan balas bam-banya kasi sang bosong.<bt>That is why you-pl must hold firmly to your belief. Cuz (elaboration) later God2 will repay many things to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So do not throw away"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So do not throw away your confidence; it will be richly rewarded.</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Jadi batahan sa! Te kalo bosong su bekin iko Tuhan pung mau tarús, nanti bosong tarima samua yang Dia su janji kasi sang bosong.<bt>So (consequently) just endure/persevere! Cuz (elaboration) if you have been following/obeying all of God2's will, you will receive everything that He has promised you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You need to persevere, so"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You need to persevere, so that when you have done the will of God, you will receive what he has promised.</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Tuhan pung jubir dong su tulis so'al itu Orang yang mau datang bilang,<bt>God2's spokespeople have written about the Person who is going to come saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Sonde lama lai, te itu Orang yang mau datang, su muncul datang.<bt>"It will not be much longer, cuz (reason) that Person who is going to come, will have come.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jang pata samangat, te Dia sonde tunggu-tunggu.<bt>Don't lose hope/interest, cuz (elaboration) He does not wait around/delay.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For in just a very"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For in just a very little while, "He who is coming will come, and will not delay.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="38" />Orang yang pung hati lurus,<bt>The person whose liver is straight/righteous, [NOTE to daughter translations: can use either /hati lurus/ or /hati barisi/ here, as long as it links lexically with how they normally talk about it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti dapa salamat,<bt>will be/get saved,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal dia parcaya sang Beta.<bt>because s/he believes in Me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma kalo ada yang ondor diri dari Beta,<bt>But if there is someone who withdraws/retreats from Me,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma kalo dia bale balakang dari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Ma kalo dia bale balakang dari Beta,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta pung hati sonde sanáng.&gt;&gt;<bt>My liver will not be happy."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But my righteous one will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But my righteous one will live by faith. And if he shrink back, I will not be pleased with him."</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:37-38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Habakuk 2:3-4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ma kotong ni, bukan orang yang ondor diri dari Tuhan Allah. Te orang macam bagitu, nanti tapisa buang dari Dia. Ma kotong ni, orang yang parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Ais kotong dapa salamat ko idop tarús deng Dia.<bt>We-inc are not people who withdraw/retreat from God. Cuz (elaboration) people of that sort, will be cut off/separated off from Him. But we are people who believe in God. So we will be/get saved to live continually with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But we are not of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But we are not of those who shrink back and are destroyed, but of those who believe and are saved.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong musti parcaya tarús sang Tuhan Allah, sama ke orang dolu-dolu<bt>We must keep believing in God, like the people of long ago</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />Kalo kotong parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, dia pung arti bilang, kotong yakin tarús sang Dia. Te kalo Dia su janji mau bekin satu hal, na, kotong tau bilang, Dia pasti bekin iko itu janji. Biar kotong balóm tarima apa-apa ju, kotong parcaya tarús sa.<bt>If we-inc believe in God, that means we continue to hope/trust in Him. Cuz (elaboration) if He has promised to give something to us, we know that He will surely [NOTE: CHECK] do according to what He has promised. Even if we have not yet received anything, we just keep believing. [EXEG: Gk sense of ‘hope’ here carries more confidence/assurance (LN) than just “wishful thinking” without a lot of substance, which is often how it is used in English and lgs in this region, So this had to be restructured from an earlier version under the guidance of a consultant, to strengthen the intended meaning that wasn't getting through.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) revised, note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) revised, note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now faith is being sure"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now faith is being sure of what we hope for and certain of what we do not see.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo kotong parcaya sang Tuhan Allah,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Kalo kotong parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, dia pung arti, bilang, kotong baharap tarús sang Dia. Te kalo Dia su janji mau kasi satu hal sang kotong, kotong tau, bilang, Dia pasti bekin iko Dia pung janji tu. Biar kotong balóm tarima apa-apa ju, kotong parcaya tarús sa.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ada dari kotong pung nene-moyang dong yang memang parcaya bagitu. Tagal itu, Tuhan Allah ju tarima bae sang dong.<bt>There are those among our ancestors who really believed like that. Because of that, God accepted them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This is what the ancients"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This is what the ancients were commended for.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ini bumi deng langit yang kotong ada lia sakarang ni, kotong parcaya bilang, Tuhan Allah yang bekin ini samua. Ma Dia sonde bekin pake barang yang su ada, yang manusia bisa dapa lia. Samua yang ada ni, jadi tagal Dia omong pake Dia pung Kata-kata sa.<bt>This earth and sky which we now see, we believe that God is the one who created all this. But He did not create it using things that already existed, which humans could see. Everything that exists here, jadi (came into being) because He spoke just using His Words/Sayings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aorata: Shouldn't imply that there are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">aorata: Shouldn't imply that there are things out there that we can't see, but that God used as the raw material for making the things we can see. Important philosophically. LITERALLY: By faith we understand that the universe was formed at God's command, so that what is seen was not made out of what was visible.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 1:1, Lagu Puji dong 33:6, 9, Yohanis 1:3</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Habel [\s2]<bt>Habel</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Habel parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Tagal itu, dia bawa pemberian yang lebe bae dari dia pung kaka Kaen. Tuhan Allah tarima bae sang Habel deng dia pung pemberian tu, tagal dia pung hati lurus. Jadi biar dia su lama mati, ma kotong masi bisa balajar dari dia, tagal dia pung parcaya.<bt>Habel believed in God. Because of that he brought a better offering than his elder-sibling Kaen. God accepted Habel and his offering, because of his straight/right/just liver. So (consequently), even though he has been long dead, we-inc can still learn from him, because of his belief. [EXEG: Gk ‘commended’ = speak well of, accept, receive approval (LN, NRSV] [NOTE: the term glossed here and in following verses as "accepted" could also be glossed "accepted favourably".]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith Abel offered God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith Abel offered God a better sacrifice than Cain did. By faith he was commended as a righteous man, when God spoke well of his offerings. And by faith he still speaks, even though he is dead.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 4:3-10</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Henok [\s2]<bt>Henok</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Henok ju parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Tagal itu, Tuhan ju angka nae sang dia bawa pi sorga, ko biar dia sonde usa mati. Orang ju cari-cari sang dia, ma sonde dapa katumu, tagal Tuhan su angka nae sang dia. Tuhan tarima bae sang dia, te Tuhan ada bilang, &lt;&lt;Henok ni, orang yang bekin sanáng Beta pung hati.&gt;&gt;<bt>Henok also believed in God. Because of that God2 also took him up to heaven, so that he didn't need to die. People kept looking for him, but they didn't find him, because God2 had taken him up. God2 accepted him, cuz God2 was saying, "This Henok, is a person who makes My liver happy." [EXEG: Gk ‘commended’ = speak well of, accept, receive approval (LN, NRSV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith Enoch was taken"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith Enoch was taken from this life, so that he did not experience death; he could not be found, because God had taken him away. For before he was taken, he was commended as one who pleased God.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 5:21-24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Jadi bagini, sodara dong! Su jalás Tuhan Allah sonde tarima bae orang yang sonde parcaya sang Dia. Te orang yang mau datang di Tuhan Allah, dia musti parcaya bilang, Tuhan tu memang ada. Deng dia ju musti parcaya bilang, Tuhan mau tolong orang yang datang cari sang Dia.<bt>So it's like this, siblings! It is clear that God does not accept people who do not trust in Him. Cuz people who want to come to God, they must believe saying, God is really exists. And he must believe that God will help people who come to Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And without faith it is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And without faith it is impossible to please God, because anyone who comes to him must believe that he exists and that he rewards those who earnestly seek him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Noh [\s2]<bt>Noh</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Noh ju parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Tagal itu, Noh parcaya sang Tuhan waktu Dia kasi tau memang bilang, &lt;&lt;Noh! Inga, é! Nanti Beta kasi ancor buang ini dunya pake banjer bésar yang manusia balóm parná lia.&gt;&gt; Biar Noh balóm parná lia macam bagitu ju, dia dengar-dengar sang Tuhan Allah, deng bekin kapal ko kasi salamat dia pung isi ruma dong. Tagal dia pung parcaya tu, Tuhan anggap dia orang hati lurus. Ma samua orang yang sonde parcaya, Tuhan kasi hukum barát sang dong.<bt>Noh also believed God. Because of that, Noh believed God2 when He told (him) beforehand saying, "Noh! Remember, é! I will destroy this world using a large flood which humans have never yet seen." Even though Noh had never seen that sort, he obeyed God, and made a ship to save his household. Because of that belief of his, God2 considered Him to be a person with a straight/right/just liver. But everyone who didn't believe, God2 punished them heavily.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009b) his companions &gt; everyone"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009b) his companions &gt; everyone (last sentence) ; 1st sentence also revised</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith, Noah, when warned"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith, Noah, when warned about things not yet seen, in holy fear built an ark to save his family. By faith he condemned the world and became heir of the righteousness that comes by faith.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tagal itu, Tuhan kasi tau memang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Tagal itu, Tuhan kasi tau memang sang dia, bilang, &lt;&lt;Noh!</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 6:13-22</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ba'i Abraham kasi tenga dia pung kampong asal [\s2]<bt>Gf Abraham left his village of origin</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ba'i Abraham ju parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Tagal itu, Tuhan Allah pange sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bram, é! Kaluar kasi tenga lu pung kampong ko pi satu tampa yang nanti Beta kasi tunju sang lu. Te itu tana nanti jadi pusaka kasi lu pung turunan dong.&gt;&gt; Dengar bagitu ju, dia bekin iko Tuhan pung mau, biar dia sonde tau mau pi mana.<bt>Abraham also believed in God. God called him saying, "Bram, é! Go out leaving behind your-sg village to go to a (specific) place which I will point out to you. Cuz (elaboration) that land will become an inheritance to your descendants." Hearing that, he did according to God2's will/way, even though he didn't know where he was going.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CHECK Abe vs. Bram"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">CHECK Abe vs. Bram</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith Abraham, when called"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith Abraham, when called to go to a place he would later receive as his possession, obeyed and went, even though he did not know where he was going.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 12:1-5</note><v n="9" />Waktu dia sampe di itu tana, ju dia kasi badiri dia pung tenda, ko tenga sama ke orang luar di itu tana yang Tuhan su janji mau kasi sang dia. Ais dia pung ana Isak deng dia pung cucu Yakob tenga di situ ju, te Tuhan su janji kasi itu tana ko jadi dong pung pusaka.<bt>When he arrived at that land, he erected his tent, to live as a foreigner on that land which God2 had promised to give to him. then his child Isak and his grandchild Yakob also lived there, cuz (elaboration) God2 had promised to give that land to be their inheritance.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith he made his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith he made his home in the promised land like a stranger in a foreign country; he lived in tents, as did Isaac and Jacob, who were heirs with him of the same promise.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 35:27</note><v n="10" />Dia baharap ko nanti dia idop di satu kota yang talalu hebat. Te Tuhan Allah sandiri yang bekin gambar ko kasi bangun itu kota.<bt>He hoped that he would later live in a city which was so amazing. Cuz (elaboration) God himself is the one who made the picture to build that city.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For he was looking forward"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For he was looking forward to the city with foundations, whose architect and builder is God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Mama Sara [\s2]<bt>Mama Sara [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Sara, andia ba'i Abraham pung bini, parcaya sang Tuhan Allah ju. Biar dia balóm parná barana, deng su tua kakaluk ju, ma Tuhan bekin ko dia bisa jadi nene-moyang kasi satu bangsa bésar. Te dia parcaya bilang, Tuhan Allah pasti bekin iko apa yang Dia su janji.<bt>Sara, Gf Abraham's wife, also believed in God. Even though she had never born a child, and was already old and wrinkled, nevertheless God2 made it so he could could become the ancestor to a great ethnic group. Cuz (elaboration) she believed that, God would surely do according to what He had promised. [EXEG: Who has the faith here, Abraham or Sarah? Apparently it could be either according to the Greek and ES (#1) seems about equally divided in support of one or the other. For consistency in the higher level structure, we go with “she”. NLT cleverly splits the middle.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith Sarah, even though"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith Sarah, even though she was sterile and past the age, received power to start a lineage, because she considered him faithful who had made the promise.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 18:11-14, 21:2</note><v n="12" />Tagal itu, biar dia su tua ganggók ju, dia masi bisa barana ame turunan bam-banya, sampe sonde ada orang yang bisa itong ame sang dong. Te dong pung banya sama ke bintang di langit, deng pasir di pante.<bt>Because of that, even though she was already old and wrinkled, she was still able to give birth and have many descendants, to the point that nobody is able to count them (successfully). Cuz (elaboration) their quantity is like the stars in the sky, and sand on the beach.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And so from this one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And so from this one man, and he as good as dead, came descendants as numerous as the stars in the sky, and as countless as the sand of the seashore.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 15:5, 22:17, 32:12</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ba'i-ba'i yang parcaya deng baharap satu tana pusaka [\s2]<bt>The forefathers who were believing and hoping for a land of inheritence</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Kotong pung nene-moyang ba'i Abraham, ba'i Isak, deng ba'i Yakob ju parcaya tarús sang Tuhan Allah sampe dong mati. Ma dong balóm tarima itu tana pusaka yang Tuhan su janji. Biar bagitu ju, ma dong baharap tarús deng hati sanáng, tagal dong su lia itu tana dari jao. Te dong su mangaku bilang, dong cuma orang asing yang tenga tahan di ini dunya.<bt>Our-inc ancestors Gf Abraham, Gf Isak, and Gf Yakob also continued to believe in God until they died. But they had not yet received that land of inheritence that God2 had promised. Even that being the case, nevertheless they continued to hope with a happy liver, because they had already seen that land from afar. Cuz (elaboration) they had already confessed/ acknowledged that they were only foreigners living temporarily on this earth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: All these people were still"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: All these people were still living by faith when they died. They did not receive the things promised; they only saw them and welcomed them from a distance. And they admitted that they were foreigners and strangers on earth.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 23:4, 1 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 29:15, Lagu Puji dong 39:13</note><v n="14" />Padahal, su jalás orang yang omong macam bagitu, dong su rindu dapa satu tampa ko jadi dong pung tana milik.<bt>Whereas in fact, it is already clear that people who speak like that, they already yearn to get a place to be land that they own.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: People who say such things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: People who say such things show that they are looking for a country of their own.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Andekata kalo itu tana pusaka yang kotong pung ba'i dong su rindu tu, andia ba'i Abraham pung tana asal, na, pasti dong ada banya kasampatan ko pulang pi situ.<bt>If perchance [+hypothetical] that land of inheritence that our forefathers had yearned for, that is Gf Abraham's land of origins, na, surely they had many opportunities to go back home there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If they had been thinking"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If they had been thinking about the country they had left, they would have had opportunity to return.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ma itu tana pusaka yang dong su rindu tu, andia tana pusaka yang lebe hebat di sorga. Tagal itu, Tuhan Allah tarima bae sang dong ko dong jadi Dia pung orang. Te Dia su siap memang satu kota kasi sang dong di sorga.<bt>But that homeland which they yearned for, was a much more impressive land of inheritence in heaven. Because of that, God accepted them to be His people. Cuz (elaboration) He had already prepared beforehand a city for them in heaven.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Instead, they were longing for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Instead, they were longing for a better country--a heavenly one. Therefore, God is not ashamed to be called their God, for he has prepared a city for them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ba'i Abraham sarakan dia pung ana Isak [\s2]<bt>Gf Abraham surrendered/turned over/gave up his child Isak</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17-18" />Ba'i Abraham ju parcaya mati sang Tuhan Allah waktu Tuhan ada uji dia pung parcaya. Tagal itu, dia bekin iko Tuhan pung parenta ko sarakan dia pung ana Isak jadi korban.<bt>Gf Abraham also totally believed (Fig: believed dead) in God when God2 was testing his belief. Because of that, he did according to God2's command to give up his child Isak to be a sacrifice.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 22:1-14</note>Padahal dolu Tuhan su janji so'al itu ana bilang, &lt;&lt;Dari lu pung ana Isak ni, nanti lu dapa turunan bam-banya, sampe dong jadi bangsa yang hebat.&gt;&gt;<bt>Whereas in fact, previously God2 had already promised about that child saying, "From your-sg child Isak, you will later get a great many descendants, to the point that they become a great ethnic group."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Note perfect (affects still valid today)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">Note perfect (affects still valid today) and imperfect [was in the process] tenses prosenenokhen: does not include the idea of 'give up' that the English word 'sacrifice' includes<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>monogenees: unique, one of a kind. Isaac was Abraham's biological son, but he was the only one Abraham recognized legally and socially as his own. Semantic chunks verses 17-19: Abraham/ Made the sacrifice of Isaac (well-known as an example/ When he was put to the test/ He was in the process of sacrificing his only son/ This is the person who had been given the Promises. To him it had been said, "..."/ He figured that God was able to raise the dead/ and it is just as if that is where he got him back from.)<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>LITERALLY: By faith Abraham, when God tested him, offered Isaac as a sacrifice. He who had received the promises was about to sacrifice his one and only son, even though God had said to him, "Through Isaac shall your promised offspring come."</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 21:12</note><v n="19" />Ma ba'i Abraham su pikir kata, Tuhan Allah ada kuasa ko kasi idop kambali orang mati. Memang batúl, te itu waktu su sama ke dia dapa kambali dia pung ana yang su jadi korban.<bt>But Gf Abraham had already thought that God had the powerauthority to bring back to life dead people. That is really true, cuz (elaboration) at that time it was the same as if he got back his child who had been a sacrifice.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Abraham reasoned that God could"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Abraham reasoned that God could raise the dead, and figuratively speaking, he did receive Isaac back from death.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Memang batúl tu, te itu waktu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Memang batúl tu, te itu waktu su sama ke dia pung ana Isak mati, ais dia idop kambali.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ba'i Isak [\s2]<bt>Gf Isak</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ba'i Isak ju parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Tagal itu, dia minta ko biar nanti Tuhan kasi berkat sang dia pung ana Yakob deng Esau.<bt>Gf Isak also believed in God. Because of that he asked God to bless his children Yakob and Esau in the future.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith Isaac blessed Jacob"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau in regard to their future.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 27:27-29, 39-40</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ba'i Yakob [\s2]<bt>Gf Yakob</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ba'i Yakob ju parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Tagal itu, waktu dia su amper mati, dia badiri bongko-bongko pegang dia pung tongkat, ko sémba sang Tuhan. Ais dia minta Tuhan kasi berkat sang dia pung cucu dari dia pung ana Yusuf.<bt>Gf Yakob also beleived in God. Because of that, when he was already almost dead, he stood leaning holding his staff, to worship God2. And then he asked God2 to give blessing to his granchildren from his child Yusuf.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bongko-bongko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">bongko-bongko</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith Jacob, when he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith Jacob, when he was dying, blessed each of Joseph's sons, and worshiped as he leaned on the top of his staff.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 47:31--48:20</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ba'i Yusuf [\s2]<bt>Gf Yusuf</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ba'i Yusuf ju parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Waktu dia su amper mati, dia parcaya bilang, Tuhan Allah nanti bawa kaluar Dia pung orang Isra'el dong dari tana Masir. Andia ko dia janji sang dong, ko dong musti bawa pulang dia pung tulang, kalo nanti dong jalan kasi tenga tana Masir.<bt>Gf Yusuf also believed in God. When he was about to die, he believed that God would later take out His Isra'el people from the land of Masir. That is why he promised (also means made s.o. promise) that they must bring home his bones when they went leaving behind the land of Masir.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith Joseph, when his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith Joseph, when his end was near, spoke about the exodus of the Israelites from Egypt and gave instructions about his bones.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 50:24-25, Kaluar dari Masir 13:19</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ba'i Musa pung mama-bapa [\s2]<bt>Gf Musa's parents (doublet)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ba'i Musa pung mama-bapa ju parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Waktu dia pung mama barana abis sang dia, ju dong sambunyi sang dia sampe tiga bulan, tagal dong lia dia pung badan montok. Deng dong sonde taku sang raja negrí Masir, biar dia su parenta dia pung orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Bunu bekin mati memang samua ana laki-laki yang lahir dari orang Ibrani!&gt;&gt;<bt>Gf Musa's parents also believed in God. When his mother had given birth to him, they then hid him for three months, because they saw he had a healthy/attractive body. And they were not afraid of the raja of the country of Masir, even though he had commanded his people saying, "Kill off every male child who is born to the Ibrani people!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="badan montok = ?? (for LEX)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">badan montok = ?? (for LEX)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith Moses' parents hid"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith Moses' parents hid him for three months after he was born, because they saw he was no ordinary child, and they were not afraid of the king's edict.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 2:2, 1:22</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ba'i Musa [\s2]<bt>Gf Musa</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Waktu ba'i Musa su bésar datang, dia ju parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Te dolu raja Masir pung ana parampuan su angka sang dia ko jadi dia pung ana. Biar bagitu ju, ma dia sonde mau orang anggap dia tu, raja Masir pung kelu.<bt>When Gf Musa had grown up, he also believed in God. Cuz (elaboration) previously the raja of Masir's daughter had elevated/adopted him to be her child. Even that being the case, nevertheless he did not want people to consider him the raja of Masir's family.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith Moses, when he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith Moses, when he had grown up, refused to be known as the son of Pharaoh's daughter.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 2:10-12</note><v n="25" />Te dia pikir, lebe bae dia idop susa sama-sama deng Tuhan pung orang dong, daripada dia idop sanáng deng hal jahat yang cuma batahan sabantar sa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) he thought it would be better to live in difficulty together with God2's people, than for him to live happily/easily with evil things that only last momentarily.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="MESOLECTAL = daripada;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">MESOLECTAL = daripada;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He chose to be mistreated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He chose to be mistreated along with the people of God rather than to enjoy the pleasures of sin for a short time.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Dia kasi biar orang bekin hina sang dia, tagal dia baharap sang Kristus, andia Orang yang Tuhan Allah su janji mau kirim datang. Dia batahan bagitu, tagal dia tau Tuhan nanti balas kasi sang dia upa yang jao lebe bae dari samua harta yang ada di tana Masir.<bt>He allowed people to treat him with contempt, because he was hoping in Kristus, the Person whom God had promised to send. He endured/persevered like that, because he knew that God2 would repay him with a reward/compensation that is far better than all the wealth/possessions that existed in the land of Masir.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He regarded disgrace for the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He regarded disgrace for the sake of Christ as of greater value than the treasures of Egypt, because he was looking ahead to his reward.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang bekin hina sang dia, tagal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Orang bekin hina sang dia, tagal dia iko sang Kristus. Dia batahan bagitu, tagal dia tau Tuhan nanti balas kasi sang dia deng hadia yang jao lebe bae dari samua harta yang ada di tana Masir.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ba'i Musa ju parcaya sang Tuhan Allah waktu dia minta isin sang raja Masir ko antar bawa kotong pung nene-moyang dong jalan kaluar dari dia pung tana. Biar raja su mara mau mati, ma ba'i Musa sonde taku sang dia. Ba'i Musa parcaya tarús sang Tuhan Allah yang sonde kantara, sama ke Musa su lia sandiri sang Dia.<bt>Gf Musa also believed in God when he asked permission from the raja of Masir to lead our ancestors out from his land. Even though the raja was already furious, nevertheless Gf Musa was not afraid of him. Gf Musa kept believing in the invisible God, just like he had seen Him directly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith he left Egypt,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith he left Egypt, not fearing the king's anger; he persevered because he saw him who is invisible.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 2:15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ba'i Musa ju parcaya sang Tuhan waktu dong su siap mau jalan kaluar dari tana Masir. Te dia bekin iko Tuhan pung parenta, deng suru kotong pung nene-moyang dong bekin Paska partama deng bunu domba ko jadi binatang korban. Ais dong ame itu domba pung dara ko taro tanda di dong pung ruma dong. Itu malam ju, Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga datang bunu bekin mati samua ana sulung di tana Masir. Ma dia sonde maso pi bunu di kotong pung nene-moyang dong pung ruma-ruma, tagal dia lia itu dara di dong pung pintu.<bt>Gf Musa also believed in God2 when they were ready to go out from the land of Masir. Cuz (elaboration) he did according to God2's commands, and ordered our ancesotrs to do the first Paska and killed a sheep to be an animal sacrifice. Then they took the blood of that sheep to place/put a sign on their houses. That (same) night, God2's angel came and killed all the oldest children in the land of Masir. But he didn't go in to kill in our ancestors houses, because he saw that blood on their doors. [EXEG: doorways, Bruce, Miller] [NOTE to daughter translations: If you have a good word for ceremonial sprinkling, put it in the last sentence, “...lia itu dara (yang dong su percik) di dong pung pintu.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith he kept the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith he kept the Passover and the sprinkling of blood, so that the destroyer would not touch their firstborn.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 12:21-30</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong pung nene-moyang dong [\s2]<bt>Our-inc ancestors</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Waktu kotong pung nene-moyang dong kaluar dari tana Masir, dong ju parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Tagal dong pung parcaya, Tuhan balá aer di Laut Mera, ko dong jalan manyabráng deng salamat di tana karíng. Ma tantara Masir yang buru sang dong, mati tanggalám waktu dong coba lewat di situ.<bt>When our ancestors went out from the land of Masir, they also believed in God. Cuz (elaboration) God2 split open/apart the water in the Red Sea, so they walked crossing safely on dry land. But the Masir soldiers who chased/hunted them, died drowning when they attempted to cross there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith the people passed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith the people passed through the Red Sea as on dry land; but when the Egyptians tried to do so, they were drowned.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 14:21-31</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Mama Rahab [\s2]<bt>Mama Rahab</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Waktu kotong pung nene-moyang dong su maso di tana Kana'an, dong ju parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Te dong iko Dia pung parenta, deng jalan kuliling kota Yeriko pung tembok luar sampe tuju hari. Ju itu tembok rubu buang memang.<bt>When our ancestors had entered the land of Kana'an, they also believed in God. Cuz (elaboration) they followed His commands, and walked around the city of Yeriko's outer wall for seven days. Then that wall fell down (serial verb construction implies: completely and suddenly).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith the walls of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith the walls of Jericho fell, after the people had marched around them for seven days.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yosua 6:12-21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ada ju Rahab yang dolu jadi parampuan nakal di itu kota. Tagal dia parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, andia ko dia tarima bae-bae orang Isra'el pung mata-mata, deng kasi sambunyi sang dong di dia pung ruma. Ais Tuhan kasi ancor samua orang Yeriko, tagal dong sonde mau dengar sang Dia. Ma Tuhan kasi salamat sang Rahab, tagal dia pung parcaya.<bt>There was also Rahab who had been a whore/prostitute in that city. Because she believed in God, that's why she received well the spies of the people of Isra'el, and hid them in her house. Then God2 destroyed all the people of Yeriko, because they didn't want to listen to/obey Him. But God2 saved Rahab, because of her belief/faith.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By faith the prostitute Rahab,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By faith the prostitute Rahab, because she welcomed the spies, was not killed with those who were disobedient.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yosua 6:22-25, 2:1-21</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Banya orang laen ju parcaya sang Tuhan Allah [\s2]<bt>Many other people also believed in God</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Beta masi bisa omong panjang lai, so'al orang laen yang parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Ma beta sonde ada waktu ko carita alus-alus so'al Gideon, Barak, Simson, Yefta, Daud, Samuel, deng Tuhan Allah pung jubir yang laen dong.<bt>I could still talk at length about other people who believed in God. But I don't have the time to narrate in detail about Gideon, Barak, Simson, Yefta, Daud, Samuel, and God's other spokespeople/prophets.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And what more shall I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And what more shall I say? I do not have time to tell about Gideon, Barak, Samson, Jephthah, David, Samuel and the prophets,</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Tukang Putus Parkara dong6:11--8:32, 4:6--5:31, 13:2--16:31, 11:1--12:7, 1 Samuel 16:1--1 Raja-raja dong 2:11, 1 Samuel 1:1--25:1</note><v n="33" />Dong samua parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Tagal itu, ada yang manáng lawan raja-raja. Ada yang pegang parenta deng hati lurus, ko bela orang yang sonde ada pung sala, deng kasi hukum orang yang sala. Ada yang tarima apa yang Tuhan su janji. Deng ada yang kasi kala singa.<bt>They all believed in God. Because of that, there were those who conquered the raja's. There were those who rule/govern with a straight liver, to defend people who had no wrongs (=innocent), and punish the people who were wrong (=guilty). There were those who received what God2 had promised. And there were those who beat lions.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: who by faith conquered kingdoms,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: who by faith conquered kingdoms, administered justice, and gained what was promised; who shut the mouths of lions, basileias: the whole governmental system, not just the king<span class="Italic">(33)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 6:1-27</note><v n="34" />Ada yang kasi mati api yang manyala bésar. Ada yang Tuhan kasi salamat dari orang yang mau bunu sang dong pake kalewang. Ada yang sonde kuat, ma Tuhan Allah kasi kuat sang dong. Ada yang Tuhan bekin ko dong jadi hebat baparáng, sampe dong puku kasi ondor tantara musu dari tampa laen dong.<bt>There were those who extinguished fires with big flames. There were those whom God2 saved from people who wanted to kill them using swords. There were those who were not strong, but God strengthened them. There were those whom God2 made to be outstanding in war, to the point that they beat back the enemy soldiers from other places.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: quenched the fury of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: quenched the fury of the flames, and escaped the edge of the sword; whose weakness was turned to strength; and who became powerful in battle and routed foreign armies.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 3:1-30</note><v n="35" />Ada ju mama-mama yang tarima kambali dong pung kelu, yang Tuhan su kasi idop kambali.<bt>There were also mothers who received their families (members) back, whom God2 had brought back to life.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma ada yang kaná siksa, tagal dong parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Dong lebe suka mati, ko biar dong jang bale balakang sang Tuhan. Te dong sonde putus hubungan deng Dia. Jadi dong ada baharap bilang, nanti Tuhan angka sang dong ko dapa idop yang lebe bae lai di sorga.<bt>But there were those who experienced torture/ persecution, because they believed in God. They preferred to die, so that they would not turn their back on (=reject) God2. Cuz (elaboration) they did not want to break off/separate their connection/ relationship with Him. So (consequently), they were hoping that God2 would later elevate them/raise them up to get an even better life in heaven. [EXEG: NLT, Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="UBS says it is better to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">UBS says it is better to not begin a new paragraph in the middle of the verse, but de in the middle of 35 is the only conjunction in the whole series, and it is adversative. LITERALLY: Women received back their dead, raised to life again. Others were tortured and refused to be released, so that they might gain a better resurrection.<span class="Italic">(35)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ada ju mama-mama yang tarima kambali"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Ada ju mama-mama yang tarima kambali dong pung kelu, yang Tuhan su kasi idop kambali. Ada yang kaná siksa, ma dong sonde mau tarima waktu orang kasi bebas sang dong, tagal dong parcaya bilang, nanti dong dapa idop yang lebe bae lai di sorga.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 17:17-24, 2 Raja-raja dong 4:25-37</note><v n="36" />Ada yang kaná ejek, deng kaná firuk. Ada laen lai yang kaná gepe dong pung kaki pake kayu pasung dalam bui.<bt>There are those who were scoffed at, and those who were beaten/whipped. There were still others whose feet were clamped in stocks inside prison. [NOTE to daughter translations. should be as in Acts 16:24]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kayu pasung = stocks"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">kayu pasung = stocks</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Some faced jeers and flogging,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Some faced jeers and flogging, while still others were chained and put in prison,</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 22:26-27, 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 18:25-26, Yeremia 20:2, 37:15, 38:6</note><v n="37" />Ada yang mati, tagal kaná lempar deng batu. Ada yang mati, tagal orang gargaji balá dong pung badan. Ada yang mati, tagal kaná bunu deng kalewang. Ada yang idop miskin deng cuma pake pakean dari kulit binatang, tagal orang siksa deng bekin susa sang dong, sampe usir buang sang dong,<bt>There are those who died, because they were stoned with rocks. There were those who died, because people sawed splitting their bodies. There were those who died, because they were killed with a sword. There were those who live in poverty and only wore clothes from animal skins, because people tortured/persecuted and cause difficulty for them, to the point that they evicted/chased them out,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epristheesan: Acts 19:13 'go all ova'."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">epristheesan: Acts 19:13 'go all ova'. thlibomenoi, kakoukhoumenoi: reversed order sounds better in Pidgin.<span class="Italic">(37) (37) </span>LITERALLY: They were stoned; they were sawed in two; they were put to death by the sword. They went about in sheepskins and goatskins, destitute, persecuted and mistreated--</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 24:21</note><v n="38" />ko dong lari pi tenga di tampa sunyi, di gunung-gunung, di goa-goa, deng di lobang-lobang dalam tana. Orang anggap reme sang ini orang dong, deng usir dong pi tenga di tampa sonde bae. Padahal dong pung parcaya talalu hebat, sampe orang yang ada di ini dunya sonde pantas tenga sama-sama deng ini orang dong.<bt>so they fled going to live in empty land, in the mountains, in caves, and in holes in the ground. People scorned these people, and chased them out to go live in places that were not good. Whereas in fact, their belief was very impressive, to the point that this world's best place/s, to the point that the people in this world are not deserved to live among these people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sentence order shift: Pidgin discourse puts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">Sentence order shift: Pidgin discourse puts conclusion last, not in the middle. LITERALLY: the world was not worthy of them. They wandered in deserts and mountains, and in caves and holes in the ground.<span class="Italic">(38)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Tuhan puji sang dong samua ni, tagal dong parcaya sang Dia. Ma sampe dong pung mati ju, dong balóm tarima apa yang Tuhan su janji.<bt>God2 commended all those people, because they believed in Him. But until they died, they had not yet received what God2 had promised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: These were all commended for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: These were all commended for their faith, yet none of them received what had been promised.</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Dia mau bekin iko Dia pung janji, pake jalan yang lebe bae. Tagal Dia mau ko kotong samua bisa idop tarús sama-sama deng Dia: andia kotong yang sakarang su kanál sang Kristus, deng dong yang su mati dolu-dolu.<bt>He will do according to His promise, using a better way. Because He wanted all of us to live continually together with Him; that is, we who now know Christ personally and those who died long ago. [EXEG: Otomi BT; ‘something better’ = Jesus (Ellingsworth, Miller).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peri: not &quot;for&quot;, but &quot;involving&quot;. LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">peri: not "for", but "involving". LITERALLY: God had planned something better for us, so that only together with us would they be made perfect.<span class="Italic">(40)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Jadi karmana deng kotong yang idop sakarang? Kotong su sama ke orang yang iko lomba lari. Kotong pung nene-moyang dolu-dolu dong yang parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, dong sama ke panonton yang badiri kuliling ko kasi samangat sang kotong. Ma kalo kotong masi ta'ika deng sala-sala dong, itu bekin kotong pung lari jadi barát. Andia ko kotong musti angka buang itu sala dong samua, ko biar kotong bisa lari ukur kuat. Te Tuhan Allah sandiri su pili sang kotong ko iko ini lomba, jadi kotong musti batahan ko lari tarús sampe di garis finis.<bt>So (consequently), what about we-inc who are living now? We are like people who participate in a running race. Our ancestors who believed in God long ago, are like viewers who are standing around to encourage us/cheer us on (not "strengthen liver", but "give enthusiasm"). But if we are still bound to/by wrongs, that makes our running heavy. That is why we must throw away all those wrongs, so that we can run with all our strength (Idiom: measuring strong). Cuz (elaboration) God himself has chosen us to participate in this race, so we must endure/persevere to keep running until the finish line.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, since we are surrounded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, since we are surrounded by such a large cloud of witnesses, let us throw off everything that hinders, and the sin that so easily entangles, and let us run with perseverance the race marked out for us.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Deng kotong musti lari deng mata sonde lia kiri-kanan, ma lia sang Yesus sa. Te Dia yang buka jalan ko kotong bisa parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Deng Dia nanti tolong ko kotong bisa parcaya tarús-tarús sampe abis. Inga, ko sonde? Waktu Yesus sangsara di kayu palang, orang olok-olok sang Dia, ma Dia batahan tarús. Te Dia tau kalo Dia pung sangsara su abis, nanti Dia pung hati jadi sanáng. Itu batúl. Te waktu Dia su mati abis, ju Tuhan Allah angka sang Dia ko dudu di Tuhan pung sablá kanan, ko Dong dua parenta sama-sama.<bt>And we must run with eyes not looking left-right, but just looking at Yesus. Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who opened the way for us-inc to be able to believe in God. And He will help so we can continue believing until the end. Do you remember, or not? When Yesus was suffering on the cross, people kept scoffing at Him, but He kept persevering. Cuz (elaboration) He knew that when His suffering was finished, His liver would be happy. That's true. Cuz (elaboration) when He had died, God elevated/appointed Him to sit at Go2's right side, for the two of Them to govern together. [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK that it's not a problem that Christ died, and then God took him up to heaven here (his corpse?) Resurrection is left implicit. Many local discourse patterns require the missing step to be filled in. This problem was brought to our attention by MTTs.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Let us fix our eyes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Let us fix our eyes on Jesus, the Pioneer and Perfecter of our faith, who for the joy set before him endured the cross, scorning the shame, and sat down at the right hand of the throne of God.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Biar orang bekin jahat sang Dia, ma Dia batahan tarús. Jadi bosong jang lupa sang Yesus pung sangsara ni, ko biar bosong ju bisa batahan tarús, deng jang cape.<bt>Even though people did evil to Him, nevertheless He kept persevering. So (consequently), you-pl should not forget Yesus' sufferings, so that you can also keep persevering, and not grow weary.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Consider him who endured such"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Consider him who endured such opposition of sinful people against himself, so that you will not grow weary and lose heart.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah mau togor ko ajar sang kotong, sama ke satu bapa ajar dia pung ana<bt>God wants to scold and teach/instruct us, like a father teaches his child</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Bosong su lawan hal jahat dong, ma bosong balóm lawan karás sampe bosong pung dara tapo'a. Batúl, aa?<bt>You-pl have opposed evil things, but you have not yet opposed so hard that your blood has spilled. That's true, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In your struggle against sin,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In your struggle against sin, you have not yet resisted to the point of shedding your blood.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Mangkali bosong su lupa Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata yang Dia su kasi tau sang bosong, sama ke satu bapa ada omong deng dia pung ana bilang,<bt>Perhaps/probably you have forgotten God's Words/Sayings which He has made known to you, like a father speaking to his child saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ana, é!<bt>"Child, é!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kalo kotong pung Bos ada hukum ko ajar sang lu, ko biar lu idop iko jalan yang batúl,<bt>If our-inc Boss/lord/master punish in order to teach you-sg, so that you live according to the right path,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">na, lu jang anggap enteng!<bt>na, you should not disparage/belittle it/him!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng kalo Dia ada togor ko ajar sang lu,<bt>And if He is scolding/admonishing/warning in order to teach you,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">na, lu pung hati jang ilang.<bt>na, your liver should not disappear (=discouraged, depressed, disappointed).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati tatutu = unreceptive ***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">hati tatutu = unreceptive ***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Have you forgotten the word"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Have you forgotten the word of encouragement that addresses you as sons: "My son, do not make light of the Lord's correction, and do not lose heart when he rebukes you, paideia: upbringing, training, instruction, discipline, correction<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>elegkhoo: proof, (punishment, discipline)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="na, lu pung hati jang tatutu."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">na, lu pung hati jang tatutu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="6" />Te kotong pung Bos togor ko ajar orang yang Dia sayang.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) our-inc Boss scold/admonish/warn in order to teach/correct/ punish people whom He loves.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te Bos mara, tagal Dia sayang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Te Bos mara, tagal Dia sayang sang lu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Memang samua orang yang Dia tarima jadi Dia pung ana,<bt>Really every person whom He accepts as His child,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Dia pasti togor ko ajar sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>He will surely scold/admonish/warn in order to teach them."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: because the Lord disciplines those"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: because the Lord disciplines those whom he loves, and he reproves everyone he accepts as a son" mastigow: punish, chastise, reprove<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="12:5-6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ayub 5:17, Kata-kata Mutiara 3:11-12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Jadi, kalo Tuhan Allah ada togor ko ajar sang bosong ko idop iko jalan yang batúl, na, batahan sa. Dia bekin bagitu, tagal bosong su jadi Dia pung ana. Te tiap bapa musti togor ko ajar dia pung ana, sampe itu ana tau idop iko jalan yang batúl.<bt>So (consequently), if God is scold in order to teach you-pl to live according to the right path, na, just endure/persevere. He does that, because you have become/are His child(ren). Cuz (elaboration) each father must scold in order to teach his child, to the point that that child knows (how to) live according to the right way.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Endure correction; God is treating"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Endure correction; God is treating you as sons. For what son is not disciplined by his father?</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te kalo Tuhan Allah sonde togor ko ajar sang bosong sama ke Dia pung ana yang laen dong, dia pung arti bilang, bosong ni, bukan Dia pung ana.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if God does not scold to teach you-pl like His other children, that means that you are not His children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If you are not disciplined"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If you are not disciplined (and everyone is), then you are illegitimate children, and not true sons.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Kotong biasa kasi hormat sang kotong pung bapa barana di ini dunya, tagal dia togor ko ajar sang kotong waktu kotong masi kici. Itu su batúl. Ma lebe-lebe lai, kotong musti dengar-dengar sang Tuhan Allah, tagal Dia tu, kotong pung Bapa di sorga, deng Dia mau togor ko ajar kotong ko idop iko Dia pung jalan yang batúl.<bt>We-inc normally show respect to our birth father on this earth, because he teaches/instructs us when we are still small. That is true. But even more than that, we must obey (listen-listen) to God, because He is our Father in heaven, and He wants to teach us to live according to His true/right/correct path.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Moreover, we have all had"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Moreover, we have all had human fathers, who diciplined us, and we respected them for it. How much more should we submit to the Father of [our] spirits [/our spiritual Father], and live!</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Kotong pung bapa barana togor ko ajar kotong cuma sabantar sa, iko apa yang dia anggap bae. Ma Tuhan Allah lebe tau apa yang kotong parlú balajar. Andia ko Dia togor ko ajar kotong ko idop barisi sama ke Dia.<bt>Our birth fathers teach us for only a moment (limited period of time), according to what he considers to be good. But God knows better what we need to learn. That is why He teaches us to live clean/pure/holy like Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Our fathers disciplined us for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Our fathers disciplined us for a little while as they thought best; but God disciplines us for our good, that we may share in his holiness.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Memang sonde enak kalo kaná togor. Ma lama-lama ju kotong pung hati jadi tanáng, tagal kotong su tau idop iko Tuhan pung mau.<bt>It really is not nice/pleasant if we experience scolding/reprimand. But eventually our livers are also calm/inner peace, because we know (how to) live according to God2's will/ways.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: No discipline seems pleasant at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: No discipline seems pleasant at the time, but painful. Later on, however, it produces a harvest of righteousness and peace for those who have been trained by it.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12-13" />Sodara dong! Bekin kuat bosong pung tangan yang su cape, deng bekin ringan bosong pung kaki yang su barát. Jang lari babengko-re'o, ma lari lurus tarús, ko dong yang su tar bisa-bisa lai, ju dapa samangat ko bisa lari tarús. Bosong musti bekin kuat bosong pung hati ko batahan tarús deng parcaya sang Kristus.<bt>Siblings! Strengthen your hands that are tired, and lighten your feet that are already heavy. Don't run crooked (doublet: =weaving back and forth?), but keep running straight, so those who a unable to continue on anymore. You-pl must strengthen/encourage your livers to keep enduring/persevering believing in Kristus. [EXEG: continuing the running metaphor (Miller, Deibler).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paremenas: listless, drooping paraluw: coming loose|i(12)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">paremenas: listless, drooping paraluw: coming loose<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: Therefore, strengthen your feeble arms and weak knees. LITERALLY: Make level paths for your feet, so that the lame may not be disabled, but rather healed.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="12:12-13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 35:3; Kata-kata Mutiara 4:26</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang tola buang Tuhan Allah pung hati bae sang bosong<bt>Don't reject God's good liver to you</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Sodara yang parcaya sang Kristus! Bosong musti pasang kaki ko idop badame satu deng satu. Deng usaha karás ko idop barisi. Te orang yang sonde barisi, sonde bisa lia sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Siblings who believe in Kristus! You-pl must strive/work hard/make every effort (Idiom: fasten feet) to live at peace (=right relationships) with each other. And try hard to live clean/pure/holy. Cuz (elaboration) a person who does not live clean/pure/ holy, cannot see God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eireeneen: different sense from 11. Is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">eireeneen: different sense from 11. Is this a section break or not? holiness 10, peace 11, peace-holiness chiasm 14<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: Make every effort to live at peace with all people, and to be holy. Without holiness no one will see the Lord.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sodara yang parcaya sang Kristus! Bosong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Sodara yang parcaya sang Kristus! Bosong musti pasang kaki ko idop manis satu deng satu. Deng usaha karás ko idop barisi. Te orang yang sonde barisi, sonde bisa lia sang Tuhan Allah.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Kasi samangat satu deng satu ko biar jang sampe ada dari bosong yang ondor diri sampe sonde rasa Tuhan Allah pung hati bae. Jaga bae-bae ko jang kasi biar ada rasa saki hati yang muncul di bosong pung teng-tenga. Te itu sama ke racon yang pait, yang bekin rusak banya orang.<bt>Encourage one another so that there are none among you-pl who withdraw/retreat to the point that they do not taste/experience God's goodness/grace/ kindness/ generosity. Guard/watch carefully to not allow the feeling of pained liver (=hate, resentment, anger) to arise/appear in your-pl midst. Cuz (elaboration) that is like bitter poison which causes damage to many people. [NOTE: bitterness is used as a metaphor for painful life experiences.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Deng ati-ati deng jaga = seems"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Deng ati-ati deng jaga = seems forced to me (CEG) ***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: See to it that no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: See to it that no one misses the grace of God, and that no bitter root grows up to cause trouble and defile many.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kasi samangat satu deng satu ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Kasi samangat satu deng satu ko biar jang sampe ada yang dari bosong yang bale balakang kasi tenga Tuhan Allah pung hati bae. Deng ati-ati deng jaga ko jang ada yang bekin kamomos. Te orang model bagitu, su sama ke racon yang bekin rusak tamán-tamán laen dong.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 29:18</note><v n="16" />Deng ati-ati, deng jaga ko jang ada yang maen serong. Ais ati-ati deng jaga ko jang ada yang idop sonde toe sang Tuhan Allah, sama ke Esau. Esau tu, ba'i Isak pung ana sulung. Satu hari, Esau pulang deng parú karoncong. Dia minta makanan satu piring dari dia pung adi Yakob, deng bayar pake dia pung hak sulung.<bt>And be careful and guard so that there are none who are playing off-track (usually implies sexual). And2 be careful guard so that there are none who live ignoring/not caring about God, like Esau (did). Esau, was gf Isak's oldest child. One day, Esau came home with a strumming stomach (=hunger). He asked for a plate of food from his younger-sibling Yakob, and paid using his elder-sibling rights.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: See that no one is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: See that no one is sexually immoral, or is godless like Esau, who for a single meal sold his inheritance rights as the oldest son.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 25:29-34</note><v n="17" />Ma sonde lama ju, kotong tau Esau su manyasal. Te waktu bapa Isak mau minta Tuhan kasi berkat ana sulung sang Esau, Isak su sonde bisa minta lai, tagal Esau su kasi buang deng parcuma dia pung hak. Andia ko biar dia manangis makarereu ju, dia sonde bisa dapa kambali apa yang dolu dia su buang.<bt>But not long after that, we-inc know that Esau already regretted (his action). Cuz (elaboration) when father Isak wanted to ask God2 to give the blessing of the eldest child to him, Isak was no longer able to ask for it, because Esau had already given away that right of his. That is why even though he wept bitterly, he could not get back what he had earlier thrown away.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi buang = Is this really"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">kasi buang = Is this really KM? seems like angka buang or lapas buang would be more natural (CEG)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Afterward, as you know, when"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Afterward, as you know, when he wanted to inherit this blessing, he was rejected. He could bring about no change of mind, though he sought the blessing with tears.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 27:30-40</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Bagini, sodara dong! Kotong su bisa datang di Tuhan Allah pung muka, iko jalan baru yang Dia su buka kasi sang kotong. Ma dolu-dolu kotong pung nene-moyang dong balóm bisa bagitu. Te waktu Tuhan Allah ba'ika janji deng dong, dong ada deka deng satu gunung, nama Sinai. Di atas itu gunung ada api manyala. Ada angin ribut ju. Deng itu gunung ju tatutu deng galáp buta, sampe bekin dong taku mau mati.<bt>It's like this, siblings! We-inc can already come before God, following the new path which He has opened for us. But long ago our ancestors were not yet able to do that. Cuz (elaboration) when God was binding a promise with them, they were near a mountain named Sinai. On that mountain there was a fire flaming. There was also stormy wind. And that mountain was also covered with pitch dark (Idiom: blind dark), to the point of making them terrified. [EXEG: gloom = darkness that is frightening (LN).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You have not come to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You have not come to a mountain that [can be touched--NIV / that you can feel--TEV] and that is burning with fire; to darkness, gloom, and storm;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tampa di bumi yang manusia bisa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">tampa di bumi yang manusia bisa lia deng mata sandiri.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Dong ju dengar tarompet pung bunyi, ais Tuhan pung suara yang hebat kaluar dari itu gunung. Dengar Tuhan pung omong ju, dong tamba taku, sampe minta sang ba'i Musa bilang, &lt;&lt;Aduu! Botong su sonde bisa tahan dengar ini suara lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>They also heard the sound of a trumpet (loan), and then God2's incredible voice came out from that mountain. Hearing God2's speaking (sound, or what He was saying), they were increasingly afraid, to the point that they asked Gf Musa saying, "Aduu! We-exc can no longer stand to hear/listen to this voice!"</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: to a trumpet blast, or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: to a trumpet blast, or to such a voice speaking words, so that those who heard it begged that no further word be spoken to them,</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:18-19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 19:16-22, 20:18-21, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 4:11-12, 5:22-27</note><v n="20" />Dong memang sonde bisa tahan, tagal apa yang Tuhan parenta, talalu barát. Te Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde ada yang bole inja ini gunung! Biar manusia ko, binatang! Te sapa yang inja ini gunung, musti kaná lempar deng batu sampe mati.&gt;&gt;<bt>They really couldn't endure it, because what God2 was commanding, was too heavy (=difficult). Cuz (elaboration) He told them, "There is nobody who may step on this mountain! Whether human or, animal! Cuz (elaboration) whoever steps on this mountain, must be stoned to death."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: because they could not bear"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: because they could not bear what was commanded: "If even an animal touches the mountain, it must be stoned."</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 19:12-13</note><v n="21" />Apa yang dong lia di itu gunung, memang ngarí batúl. Sampe ba'i Musa sandiri ju gamatar dingin.<bt>What they saw on that mountain was really horrible. To the point that Gf Musa himself was also trembling in fear (Idiom: shaking cold).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The sight was so terrifying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The sight was so terrifying that Moses said, "I am trembling with fear."</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 9:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ma sakarang jalan pi Tuhan su tabuka, deng kotong su bisa ba'omong langsung deng Dia. Sakarang kotong datang di satu gunung, nama Sion. Deng di situ ada kota Yerusalem. Bukan kota Yerusalem di bumi, ma kota Yerusalem baru di sorga, andia Tuhan Allah pung tampa tenga. Di situ ada Tuhan pung ana bua di sorga bam-banya, sampe ribu-ribu, yang maen bekin pesta rame-rame.<bt>But now they way to God2 is already open, and we-inc can talk directly to Him. Now we come to a mountain named Sion. And there, there is the city of Yerusalem. Not the city of Yerusalem on earth, but a new city of Yerusalem in heaven, that is the place where God lives. In that place, there are many of God2's angels, to the point of thousands, who continually/repetitively make festive celebrations. [EXEG: city of the living God = city where God lives (Ex.Summ.)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But you have come to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But you have come to Mount Zion, to the heavenly Jerusalem, the city of the living God. You have come to thousands upon thousands of angels in joyful assembly,</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Itu kota ju su jadi tampa bakumpul kasi samua orang yang parcaya sang Kristus. Te Tuhan su bekin daftar ko tulis dong pung nama satu-satu di sorga. Di situ ju ada Tuhan Allah, yang nanti pareksa deng nilei samua orang pung idop. Deng di situ ju, ada bakumpul samua orang yang dolu-dolu Tuhan Allah tarima bae, tagal dong parcaya sang Dia. Di situ dong jadi sampurna.<bt>That city has also become a gathering place for all people who believe in Kristus. Cuz (elaboration) God2 has made a list to write each of their names in heaven. At that place, there is also God, who will investigate/examine and evaluate everyone's lives. And also in that place, there are gathered everyone whom formerly God accepted, because they believed in Him. There (location), they become complete/perfect. [EXEG: “spirits of righteous men” = OT believers (Ex.Summ.); eklesia = used a term that would differentiate NT from OT saints = believe in Christ] [Note to daughter translations: concept of ‘complete/perfect’ is not easy in these lgs. CHECK carefully.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) added last sentence to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">*** (2009) added last sentence to correct omission. notes added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekkleesiaai proototokoon: not Jesus as the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">ekkleesiaai proototokoon: not Jesus as the Firstborn, but the assembly of people to all of whom God has given the same status as if they were all his firstborn children. pneumasin? Not the Bon Festival or the Day of the Dead<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>LITERALLY: to the church of the firstborn, whose names are written in heaven. You have come to God, the judge of all men, to the spirits of righteous men made perfect,</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Deng di situ ju ada Yesus, yang jadi jambatan kasi Tuhan Allah deng manusia. Yesus mati kasi tumpa Dia pung dara, ko biar Tuhan bisa ika janji baru deng kotong. Andia ko Yesus pung dara tu, bekin dingin Tuhan Allah pung hati. Ma ini laen dari Habel pung dara di Carita Mula-Mula. Te waktu Kaen bunu sang Habel, Habel pung dara yang tapo'a tu, bekin panas Tuhan Allah pung hati, sampe Dia kasi jato hukuman sang Kaen.<bt>And in that place there is also Yesus, who is a/the bridge between God and humans. Yesus died spilling His blood (implies for a purpose/cause), so that God2 could bind a new promise with us-inc. That is why Yesus' blood cools God's liver (Idiom: causes anger (=hot) to dissipate). But this is different from Habel's blood in that story of first beginnings (=Genesis). Cuz (elaboration) when Kaen murdered Habel, Habel's blood which had been poured out, made God's liver hot (=angry), to the point that He handed down punishment to Kaen.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proserchomai: You now have a relationship"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">proserchomai: You now have a relationship with Jesus rantismou: metonym for sacrifice<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>TERM: Make the deal go into effect. 1 Cor 11:25 "Dis cup mean dat God wen make one new kine deal fo you guys, an I gotta bleed an mahke fo make um happen lidat. " OK. LITERALLY: to Jesus, the mediator of a new covenant, and to the sprinkled blood that speaks a better word than the blood of Abel.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="12:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 4:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Pasang talinga bae-bae ko dengar apa yang Tuhan Allah mau omong kasi sang bosong. Jang bekin sama ke kotong pung nene-moyang dong, yang tola buang ba'i Musa pung omong, waktu dia jadi Tuhan Allah pung jubir di ini dunya. Ais Tuhan kasi jato hukuman sang dong. Apalai deng kotong! Kalo kotong sonde mau dengar Dia pung omong dari sorga, pasti Dia kasi hukuman lebe barát sang kotong!<bt>Fasten your ears well to listen to what God wants to say to you-pl. Don't do the same as our ancestors, who rejected what Gf Musa had to say, when he was God's spokesman on this earth. Then God2 handed down punishment to them. Even more with us-inc! If we do not want to listen to/obey what He has to say from heaven, surely He will hand down an even heavier punishment to us!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Moses needs to be introduced by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">Moses needs to be introduced by name to make the tie back to v. 21. chreematizonta: divine oracle. Content is not specifically positive or negative except as context requires.<span class="Italic">(25) (25) </span>LITERALLY: See to it that you do not refuse him who speaks. If they did not escape when they refused him who warned them on earth, how much less will we [escape], if we turn away from him who warns us from heaven?</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:22</note><v n="26" />Waktu kotong pung nene-moyang dong badiri di gunung Sinai, Tuhan pung suara yang hebat bekin tana sampe tagoyang. Sakarang Dia ada janji bilang,<bt>When our ancestors were standing on Sinai mountain, God2's incredible voice made the ground shake. Now He is promising saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Nanti Beta bekin tana tagoyang satu kali lai,<bt>"I will make the ground shake one more time,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma bukan cuma tana sa yang tagoyang,<bt>but it will not be only the ground that is shaken,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">te langit ju iko tagoyang.&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) the sky will also (participate) in being shaken."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: At that time his voice"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: At that time his voice shook the earth, but now he has promised, "Once more I will shake, not only the earth, but the heavens."</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hagai 2:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Waktu Tuhan omong bilang, Dia mau bekin samua tagoyang &lt;&lt;satu kali lai&gt;&gt;, dia pung arti bilang, Tuhan mau kasi tagoyang samua yang Dia su bekin di langit deng di bumi, sampe yang sonde bisa batahan, nanti ilang buang. Te yang bisa batahan sa, yang nanti tenga tarús.<bt>When God2 said that He was going to make everything shake "one more time", that meants that God2 wanted to shake everything that He had made in the sky and on the earth, to the point that they couldn't stand it/endure, disappearing. Cuz (elaboration) that which is able to endure, will later remain continually/forever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;shake da earth&quot; OR &quot;make da"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">"shake da earth" OR "make da earth shake"? "shake" OR "shake up"?<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>Doesn't hang together. "Da stuff dat no shake" should be things like faith and love. Adding "ony" helps. OK. LITERALLY: The words "once more" indicate the removing of what can be shaken--that is, created things--so that what cannot be shaken may remain.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Tuhan Allah ada pegang parenta di sorga. Itu sonde bisa ancor. Aman sa! Tagal Dia mau tarima ko bosong maso jadi Dia pung orang di situ, na, mari ko kotong minta tarima kasi sang Dia, sémba sang Dia, deng angka tinggi-tinggi sang Dia tagal Dia pung hebat!<bt>God is ruling/governing in heaven. That cannot be destroyed/brought to ruin. It's safe (no external threats)! Because He wants to receive you as His people there, na, let us-inc give thanks to Him, worship Him, and elevate Him on high because of His amazingness/greatness! [EXEG: “receiving a kingdom” Ellingsworth = citizens - occupying an eternally safe “place” where God reigns for ever with Christ at his right hand.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, since we are receiving"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, since we are receiving a kingdom that cannot be shaken, let us be thankful, and so worship God acceptably with reverence and awe,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan mau angka kotong ko dudu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z">Tuhan mau angka kotong ko dudu parenta sama-sama deng Dia di sorga sampe salamanya. Andia ko kotong musti minta tarima kasi sang Dia, deng sémba sang Dia, tagal Dia pung hebat talalu!</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Ma kotong ju musti ati-ati, tagal Tuhan Allah pung mara, sama ke api yang bakar buang samua sampe abis.<bt>But we must also be careful, because that God's anger, is like fire which burns everything up until it is gone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: for our God is a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:24Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: for our God is a consuming fire.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 4:24</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong musti idop babae satu deng satu<bt>We must live in right relationships to one another</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />Naa, sodara sayang dong! Ada barapa hal yang beta mau kasi inga sang bosong.<bt>Naa, dear siblings! There are several matter that I want to remind/warn you-pl about.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Jang lupa basayang tarús sang bosong pung sodara orang parcaya dong.<bt>Don't forget to mutually-love continually your fellow believers. [EXEG: NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="menetoo: Rienecker thinks it implies that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">menetoo: Rienecker thinks it implies that there was a problem, but that doesn't fit with either the letter as a whole, or the other advice in this chapter. LITERALLY: Keep on loving each other as brothers.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Jang lupa buka hati ko tarima orang yang bosong sonde kanál di bosong pung ruma. Te ada barapa sodara yang parná tarima orang bagitu, tau-tau te itu orang dong, Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga.<bt>Don't forget to open your livers (=be receptive) to receive people you do not know into your homes. Cuz (elaboration) there are some siblings who have once received people like that, it turned out that those people were God's angels (from heaven).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="buka hati &gt; buka tangan ?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z">buka hati &gt; buka tangan ?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="asyndeton = for example (vs 2-7)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">asyndeton = for example (vs 2-7) make house: does it mean long time? or just 'stay'?<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: Do not forget to entertain strangers, for by so doing some people have entertained angels without knowing it.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 18:1-8, 19:1-3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Jang lupa taro mata sang orang di bui, te dong kaná tangkap tagal dong parcaya sang Kristus. Andia ko bosong musti tolong sang dong, sama ke bosong sandiri yang kaná tangkap.<bt>Don't forget to pay attention to (Idiom: place eyes) people in prison, cuz (elaboration) they have been arrested because they believe in Kristus. That is why you-pl must help them, just like you yourselves have been arrested. [EXEG: Bruce, Ell. Miller, CEV]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Deng jang lupa tolong orang yang kaná siksa. Urus sang dong deng bae-bae, sama ke bosong sandiri yang tarima itu sangsara.<bt>And don't forget to help people who are being persecuted/tortured. Take care of their (needs) carefully, just like it is you yourselves who are receiving that difficulty.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Body&quot; metonymy OK here, &quot;you are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">"Body" metonymy OK here, "you are capable of feeling the same thing". LITERALLY: Remember those in prison as if you were their fellow prisoners, and those who are mistreated as being yourselves also in the body.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Kawin laki-bini tu, barisi. Ma jang sampe kawin yang barisi tu jadi kamomos. Te Tuhan Allah tantu kasi jato hukuman sang samua orang yang maen serong deng orang yang bukan dong pung laki ko dong pung bini.<bt>Marriage between a husband-wife, is clean/pure/holy. But may it not be that marriage which is clean becomes dirty/filthy/defiled. Cuz (elaboration) God will surely hand down punishment to everyone who plays off-track with a person who is not their husband or wife.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Marriage is honorable, and the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Marriage is honorable, and the marriage bed [pure / undefiled], for God will judge the adulterer and all the sexually immoral.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Jang rakus doi. Ma bosong musti idop puas deng apa yang bosong punya. Te Tuhan Allah su omong bilang,<bt>Don't be greedy for money. But you-pl must live satisfied with what you have. Cuz (elaboration) God has spoken saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta sonde akan lupa sang bosong.<bt>"I will not forget you-pl.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta sonde akan kasi tenga sang bosong.&gt;&gt;<bt>I will not leave/abandon you."</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Keep yourselves free from love"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Keep yourselves free from love of money and be content with what you have, because God has said, "I will never leave you; I will never abandon you."</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 31:6, 8, Yosua 1:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Jadi kasi kuat bosong pung hati, sama ke orang parná tulis bilang,<bt>So (consequently) strengthen/encourage your livers, just like someone once wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tagal beta pung Bos mau tolong sang beta,<bt>"Because my Boss wants to help me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">andia ko beta sonde taku.<bt>that is why I am not afraid.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te sonde ada satu orang ju,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) there is not even one person,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang bisa ganggu batúl sang beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>who can truly disturb/bother/abuse me." [EXEG: Ex.Summ. Miller “harm”] [NOTE to daughter translations: Be careful to avoid untrue statements like “nobody can cause me trouble/difficulty”. From context, force of this statement should be in the direction of “nobody can truly disturb my confidence/assurance (of salvation), even though they might disrupt my life or torture me” “nobody can distance me from God”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So we say with confidence,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So we say with confidence, "The Lord is my helper; I will not be afraid. What can man do to me?"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="yang bisa bekin susa sang beta.&gt;&gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z">yang bisa bekin susa sang beta.&gt;&gt; [NOT true]</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 118:6</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang kambali iko atoran agama yang lama, ma parcaya tarús sang Kristus<bt>Don't go back and follow the old religious regulations, but keep believing in Kristus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Jang lupa bosong pung pamimpin dong yang parná ajar Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata sang bosong. Pikir bae-bae dong pung jalan idop, deng conto dong pung parcaya. Te apa yang dong parcaya tu, andia:<bt>Don't forget your-pl leaders who have taught you God's Words/Sayings. Think carefully at the way the live (moral, social, relational, values), and example their beliefs. Cuz (elaboration) what they believe is: [NOTE to daughter translations: If finding a generic and/or gender inclusive word for “leaders” is too problematic, leave it implicit and just use “people”, so as to not skew the focus. Gk is verbal focusing on the function, not nominal or institutional.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Remember your leaders, who spoke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Remember your leaders, who spoke the word of God to you. Consider the outcome of their way of life and imitate their faith.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="8" />Yesus Kristus tu, sonde parná baroba.<bt>Yesus Kristus never changes.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dari mula-mula, sampe sakarang, deng sampe salamanya,<bt>From the very beginning, until now, and until forever,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Dia tatáp sama.<bt>He remains the same.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Jesus Christ is the same"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Jesus Christ is the same yesterday and today and forever.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Tagal itu, bosong jang iko-iko arus deng ajaran yang sala. Tuhan Allah kasi kuat bosong pung hati, tagal Dia su kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong. Bukan tagal bosong iko atoran so'al makan-minum. Te atoran bagitu sonde ada pung guna.<bt>Because of that, you-pl should not just go along with the currents, and with wrong teachings. God strengthens/encourages your livers, because He has shown/ demonstrated His goodness/grace/ kindness/ generosity to you. Not because you followed the regulations about eating-drinking. Cuz (elaboration) regulations like that have no use.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do not be carried away"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do not be carried away by all kinds of strange teachings. It is good for our hearts to be strengthened by grace, not by ceremonial foods, which have no value to those who eat them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dolu-dolu, di Tuhan Allah pung Tenda Sambayang pung kintal, ada satu meja korban kasi binatang korban dong. Kapala agama yang layani di situ ada pung hak ko makan daging sisa dari itu meja. Ma sakarang kotong ada meja yang laen.<bt>Long ago, in that yard in God's Tent of Prayer there is a table, a place to sacrifice animals. The *priests who serve there, have the rights to eat the leftover meat from that table. But now we have a different table.</bt><note reference="13:10" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ada orang yang bilang, ini so'al meja parjamuan, padahal sonde. Ini meja ni kasi tunju Tuhan Yesus pung korban mati di kayu palang. Kotong balas itu korban deng kotong bawa persembahan puji-pujian tarús ko kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Lia ayat 15 di bawa.<bt>There are people who say this is about the communion table, but it's not. This table points to the Lord Yesus' sacrificial death on the cross. We respond to that sacrifice by bringing offerings of praise continually to God. See verse 15 below.</bt></note>Deng kapala agama model lama sonde ada hak makan di situ.<bt>And *priests of the old model have no rights to eat there. [NOTE: because of the collocation with ‘eat’, in KM we go to ‘table’ here, rather than ‘sacrifice table (altar)’.] [EXEG: TH, Bruce, Miller, Ellingsworth are all unanimous that this is not talking about communion (a position held until recently by the Catholics), but in the context of vs.10-17, is clearly about Christ's sacrifice being qualitatively different to the old system, and evoking a different kind of response.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We have an altar from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We have an altar from which those who minister at the tabernacle have no right to eat.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Dolu tiap taon kapala agama paling tinggi bawa dara dari binatang korban ko pi taro dalam Tuhan Allah pung Kamar yang Paling Barisi. Deng bagitu, Tuhan lupa buang dong pung sala-sala dong. Ais dong bawa itu binatang, ko bakar di luar kampong.<bt>Formerly each year the *highest priest brought blood from animal sacrifices to go place it inside God's Most Holy Room. In that way, God2 (completely) forgets their wrongs. Then they take that animal, to burn/roast outside the village. [DISCOURSE: NATURALNESS: Should this and next few verses be changed from mesolectal /di luar kampong/ &gt; /di balakang kampong/?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The high priest carries the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The high priest carries the blood of animals into the Most Holy Place as a sin offering, but the bodies are burned outside the gate.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 16:27</note><v n="12" />Bagitu ju deng Yesus. Dia ju jadi korban ko Tuhan Allah bisa hapus buang manusia pung sala. Deng waktu Dia sangsara, dong ju hela bawa sang Dia, ko pi bunu sang Dia di luar kota Yerusalem.<bt>It's the same way with Yesus. He also became a sacrifice so God could wipe away human's wrongs. And when He was suffering, they also dragged Him off, to go kill Him outside the city of Yerusalem.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And so Jesus also suffered"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And so Jesus also suffered outside da city gate to make his people holy through his own blood.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Tagal itu, mari ko kotong pi di Yesus, ko parcaya tarús sang Dia. Biar orang bekin hina sang kotong ju, ma kotong musti siap tarima, sama ke Dia ju tarima.<bt>Because of that, let us-inc go to Yesus, to keep believing in Him. Even though people treat us with contempt, nevertheless we must be prepared to accept it, just like Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Let us, then, go to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Let us, then, go to him outside the camp, bearing the disgrace he bore.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Te kotong cuma tenga tahan di ini dunya. Ma kotong ada baharap ko tenga di satu kota baru di sorga sampe salamanya.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we are only living temporarily on this earth. But we are hoping to live in a new city in heaven forever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For here we do not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For here we do not have an enduring city, but we are looking for the city that is to come.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Tagal Yesus su jadi korban kasi kotong, andia ko kotong su sonde parlú bawa binatang korban lai ko kasi sang Dia. Ma ada persembahan laen yang kotong musti bawa tarús ko kasi sang Tuhan Allah, andia persembahan puji-pujian yang angka tinggi-tinggi Dia pung nama.<bt>Because Yesus has become a sacrific for us, that is why we no longer need to bring animal sacrifices to give to Him. But there are other offerings which we must keep bringing to God, that is, offerings of praises which lift up/exalt His name.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Through Jesus, therefore, let us"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Through Jesus, therefore, let us continually offer to God a sacrifice of praise--the fruit of lips that confess his name.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Deng jang lupa bekin hal bae kasi orang laen. Kalo dong parlú apa, na, tolong sa. Te itu samua ju jadi sama ke persembahan yang bekin sanáng Tuhan Allah pung hati.<bt>And do not forget to do good things to/for other people. If they need something, na, just help. Cuz (elaboration) all that is also like an offering which makes God's liver happy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And do not forget to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And do not forget to do good and to share with others, for God is pleased with such sacrifices.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Bosong musti dengar-dengar sang samua orang yang urus sang bosong. Te dong jaga bosong pung jiwa siang-malam. Nanti dong musti tanggong-jawab dong pung karjá di Tuhan Allah pung muka. Jadi dengar bae-bae sang dong, ko dong bisa karjá deng lapor deng hati sanáng. Jang sampe dong lapor deng hati ancor, tagal bosong su kasi tenga Yesus Kristus pung jalan idop. Te deng bagitu, bosong su sonde ontong lai.<bt>You-pl must obey/submit (listen-listen) to every person who is managing/looking after/taking care of/dealing with you. Cuz (elaboration) they guard/watch over you soul day-night (=at all times). They will have to give an accounting for their work before God. So (consequently) listen to them carefully, so they can work and report with a happy liver. May it not be that they report with a crushed liver/dismay, because you have left behind/abandoned Yesus Kristus' way of life. Cuz (elaboration) in that way, you have no more reward/benefit. [EXEG: (Focus). QUESTION: does the ‘with joy’ attach to the ‘watching over’ or the ‘reporting’? A: My reading of the Gk is that “with joy” covers both/all aspects of the complex action of “watching over” as those who will be “reporting”, and this vagueness of anaphoric referent “do this” is reflected nicely in both the NRSV and NLT renderings. I also believe reading both aspects better accounts for the pos-neg “with joy” and “not with sighing”. Unfortunately the Ex.Summ. is much more definitive than many of the translations are, and it does not consider this possibility of the broader scope. Miller suggests the neg “with groaning” is in relation to “giving an account”. Ellingsworth agrees, but splits them, saying “with joy” refers to “keeping watch”, whereas “groaning” refers to shame if they have to give a negative account. I find that less than credible given the grammar of the Greek and the nature of pos-neg pairing. In RL cultures here, joy would be associated primarily with the social action of “reporting”, but if they report with joy, that strongly implies that they are thoroughly enjoying the “watching over” bit behind the reporting. I think the NIV is much narrower here than is the Greek.] [NOTE to daughter translations: /jiwa/ is problematic in two ways. Some lgs don't have a clear word for it, and if they do it is primarily associated with talking about dead people, not ones still alive. Avoid “guard your lives” as that gives permission for abuse of authority. ALT: “guard you day-night in your lives with God1”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Obey your leaders and submit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Obey your leaders and submit to their authority. They keep watch over you as men who must give an account. Obey them so that their work will be a joy, not a burden, for that would be of no advantage to you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yang tulis ini surat ni, ada ucap sukur deng sambayang kasi orang Ibrani<bt>The one who write this letter says thanks and prays for the Hebrews</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Tolong sambayang tarús kasi sang botong. Te botong pung hati memang lurus, deng botong mau bekin hal bae tarús.<bt>Please keep praying for us-exc. Cuz (elaboration) our livers are really straight/right/just, and we want to do good things continually.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Pray for us. We are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Pray for us. We are sure that we have a clear conscience and desire to live honorably in every way.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Lebe-lebe lai, tolong sambayang ko beta bisa kambali capát pi bosong.<bt>Even more than that, please pray so I can return quickly to you-pl.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I especially urge you to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I especially urge you to pray that I may be restored to you soon.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20-21" />Tuhan Allah yang bekin tanáng kotong pung hati. Beta minta Dia tolong sang bosong, ko bosong bisa bekin iko Dia pung mau samua. Beta ju minta ko Dia tolong kotong samua, ko jadi orang yang bekin sanáng Dia pung hati. Te Tuhan Allah su pake Yesus Kristus pung dara yang tatumpa, ko ika janji baru deng kotong. Itu janji jalan tarús sonde putus-putus. Ais Tuhan Allah kasi idop kambali kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus. Sakarang Yesus ada jaga deng piara sang kotong sama ke gambala yang paling hebat. Andia ko kotong angka tinggi-tinggi Dia pung nama, deng puji tarús-tarús sang Dia! Itu batúl.<bt>God is the one who calms (inner peace) our-inc livers. I ask Him to help you, so you can do according to all of His will/ways. I also ask Him to help us-inc all, to become people who make His liver happy. Cuz (elaboration) God has used Yesus Kristus' blood which has been spilled, to bind a new promise with us. That promise continues in effect forever. So/then, God brought back to life our Boss, Yesus Kristus. Now, Yesus is nurturing us like the best/most amazing shepherd. That is why we lift His name high/exalt Him, and keep praising Him! That's right. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [NOTE to daughter translations: Great Shepherd here should collocate with what shepherds do with sheep, not with what kings do to sugjects, so err towards the “best (good)” rather than “best (strongest)”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: May the God of peace,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: May the God of peace, who through the blood of the eternal covenant brought back from the dead our Lord Jesus, that great Shepherd of the sheep, LITERALLY: equip you with everything good for doing his will, and may he work in us what is pleasing to him, through Jesus Christ, to whom be glory forever and ever. Amen.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Saloom<bt>Greetings/leave-takings</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Sodara sayang dong! Beta minta ko bosong tarima bae beta pung nasiat ni deng hati tabuka. Te ini surat ni, cuma pende sa.<bt>Dear Siblings! I ask for you-pl to receive well this advice of mine with an open liver (=receptive). Cuz (elaboration) this letter of mine, is short.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Brothers, I urge you to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Brothers, I urge you to bear with my word of exhortation, for I have written you only a short letter.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Ada kabar yang beta mau ko bosong samua tau. Andia: kotong pung sodara Timotius su kaluar dari bui. Kalo dia datang capát di beta, nanti botong dua sama-sama pi bosong.<bt>There is news that I want all of you to know. That is: our-inc sibling Timotius has gotten out of prison. If he comes quickly to me, the two of us-exc will go together to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I want you to know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I want you to know that our brother Timothy has been released. If he arrives soon, I will come with him to see you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Beta titip salam kasi bosong pung pamimpin dong, deng salam kasi bosong samua yang parcaya sang Yesus Kristus. Sodara-sodara dari propinsi Italia ju ada titip dong pung salam.<bt>I send greetings to your-pl leaders, and greetings to all of you who believe in Yesus Kristus. The siblings in the propinsi of Italia also send greetings their greetings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Greet all your leaders and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Greet all your leaders and all God's people. Those from Italy send you their greetings.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Beta minta ko Tuhan Allah kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong samua.<bt>I ask that God continue to show His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to all of you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Grace be with you all."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:06:25Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Grace be with you all.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bagitu sa!<bt>That's all!</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>